name: Joe Biden
text: Congratulations to the Duke and Duchess of Sussex, Prince Harry and Meghan Markle, on the birth of their baby boy! The truth is there’s no better job than being a parent. Jill and I wish you the best of luck on your next chapter.

name: Joe Biden
text: On Saturday, Jill and I visited Columbia, South Carolina, to discuss how we’ll build an inclusive middle class where everyone — regardless of race, gender, sexual orientation, religion or disability — comes along. Thank you to everyone who joined us, we’ll be back soon!

name: Joe Biden
text: Nevada, we’re taking our campaign to Henderson tomorrow, May 7th! Head to https://www.mobilize.us/joebiden/event/91903/?force_banner=true&share_context=event-detail-page-modal&share_medium=copy_link … to RSVP and come join us.

name: Joe Biden
text: On this first day of Ramadan, Jill and I wish peace and happiness to Muslims around the world celebrating the holy month. Ramadan Kareem.

name: Joe Biden
text: Our country may seem more divided than ever, but I know our best days are still ahead. It’s time we lift our heads up and remember who we are. If you’re ready to get to work, join our campaign today.

name: Joe Biden
text: We’re in the battle for the soul of this nation, but I’ve never been more optimistic about our future. If we work together, I know we can get this country back on track. Join our campaign:

name: Joe Biden
text: America is an idea that has grown stronger through the unique contributions of Latinos. @latinovictoryus works tirelessly to empower the community — congrats on 5 years.

name: Joe Biden
text: We’re kicking off this campaign on May 18th—and we need #TeamJoe’s help. Sign up to host a house party to tune in with your friends and family: https://www.mobilize.us/joebiden/event/create/ …

name: Joe Biden
text: Thank you for the warm welcome, Columbia! It’s always great to be back in South Carolina.

name: Joe Biden
text: I’ve seen the selfless heroism of firefighters firsthand — they run toward danger and risk their lives every single day for strangers. On International Firefighters' Day, I extend my deepest gratitude to all the men and women who keep our communities safe.

name: Joe Biden
text: Tough, resilient, and always full of hope — that’s the America I know and that’s the America we must restore. It’s time to dig deep, take action, and fight for the soul of this nation. Join our campaign and let’s get to work.

name: Joe Biden
text: Since we launched our campaign last week, we’ve seen Americans in every corner of the country step up and say they’re in. Will you join us? Head to http://JoeBiden.com/join  and be part of our team.

name: Joe Biden
text: Last year, Floridians voted to restore voting rights to those who served their time for felonies. But today, Florida's Senate votes on a bill that would instead create a modern-day poll tax, suppressing the vote of tens of thousands of Americans. This is unacceptable.

name: Joe Biden
text:
On Holocaust Remembrance Day, let us pause and reflect on the millions of Jews who lost their lives at the hands of the Nazi regime.

The events of the last few months remind us that it’s not enough to just say never again—we must speak up and act against hate.

name: Joe Biden
text: This country wasn’t built by Wall Street bankers and CEOs and Hedge Fund Managers. It was built by you — the great American middle class. I’m thankful for all the support this week from union membership and their families, including the IAFF.

name: Joe Biden
text: Today, the House votes on #HR9, the #ClimateActionNow Act, which restores our commitment to the #ParisAgreement. We need to face facts on climate change. It’s already here. It is a major threat to our future and we simply cannot wait to take action.

name: Joe Biden
text: Happy 48th Birthday to @Amtrak and the incredible men and women whose tireless work every day keeps the trains running and our country moving.

name: Joe Biden
text: I’m the proud husband of a teacher and know first-hand the impact of their work. Teachers around the country and in South Carolina deserve to earn a living wage and have smaller class sizes so that America can continue to out-educate and lead the world. #AllOutMay1

name: Joe Biden
text: The violence in Venezuela today against peaceful protesters is criminal. Maduro's regime is responsible for incredible suffering. The U.S. must stand with the National Assembly & Guaidó in their efforts to restore democracy through legitimate, internationally monitored elections.

name: Joe Biden
text: It's no secret that I love ice cream. I enjoyed stopping by The Cone Shoppe in Monticello for some chocolate/vanilla twist soft serve and the chance to talk with some Iowans after our first campaign stop.

name: Joe Biden
text: It was great to see many of our first responders and union leaders in Cedar Rapids today. This country was built by hard working Americans like you, and I look forward to being back soon!

name: Joe Biden
text: Today, The House will hold it's first hearing on the Equal Rights Amendment in 36 years. It's way past time to give all people protection under the Constitution--human rights should never be caught up in the whims of whichever political party is in power. We need the #ERANow.

name: Joe Biden
text: Serving as @BarackObama's Vice President was a privilege and an honor. We share the belief that America is a place where ordinary people do extraordinary things and anything is possible.

name: Joe Biden
text: Folks, we’re just getting started! I’ll be heading to Iowa next. Visit http://JoeBiden.com/events  for event details and to RSVP. Hope to see you soon!

name: Joe Biden
text: We must turbocharge our efforts to address climate change that threatens communities across the country. Through clean, renewable energy and cleaner, safer, faster transportation, America will not only help the environment but provide millions of good-paying middle-class jobs.

name: Joe Biden
text: Whether you’re covered through your employer, on your own, or not at all - you should have a choice to buy into a public option health plan like Medicare.

name: Joe Biden
text: The Affordable Care Act was a huge step forward for this country. Now we have to finish the job and make health care a right, not a privilege, and give everyone the peace of mind they deserve.

name: Joe Biden
text: By making post-secondary education and training affordable to and making sure the economy works not only for folks with a four-year degree but also for those who complete on-the-job training and trade programs, too.

name: Joe Biden
text: Twelve years of education is not enough. In order to rebuild a strong middle class, we must provide skills needed to do the jobs of the 21st Century.

name: Joe Biden
text: We need to get rid of the capital gains loophole for multimillionaires. I’m going to change it so millionaires and billionaires don’t pay lower tax rates than teachers and firefighters. We need to reward work in this country, not just wealth.

name: Joe Biden
text: Companies continue to squeeze every last penny out of workers, making it harder and harder for Americans to make ends meet. It’s way past time we make a $15 minimum wage the law of the land.

name: Joe Biden
text: This country wasn’t built by Wall Street bankers and CEOs and hedge fund managers. It was built by you. The great American middle class. That’s the story of America and together we can rebuild the backbone of this nation.

name: Joe Biden
text: As I shared in Pittsburgh today, there are three reasons I’m running for President - to restore the soul of our nation, rebuild its backbone - the middle class, and unify all Americans. If you stand with me, join our campaign:

name: Joe Biden
text: I'm sick of this President badmouthing unions. Labor built the middle class in this country. Minimum wage, overtime pay, the 40-hour week: they exist for all of us because unions fought for those rights. We need a President who honors them and their work.

name: Joe Biden
text: I couldn't be more proud to have the International Association of Fire Fighters on my team. Unions built the middle class in this country—and as President, I'll fight to strengthen them and grow the backbone of this country.

name: Joe Biden
text: I've said it before and I'll say it again. To speak to the middle class, we need to reject the super PAC system. That's exactly what this campaign is doing. https://www.huffpost.com/entry/joe-biden-rejects-help-from-new-super-pac_n_5cc47617e4b08e4e3482b2b1?49 …

name: Joe Biden
text: Join me in Pittsburgh tomorrow for a discussion on my plan to build a middle class where everyone comes along. RSVP to let me know you’ll be there:

name: Joe Biden
text: Iowa, I'm headed to town this week! Let me know you'll join us by RSVPing at https://www.joebiden.com/events

name: Joe Biden
text:
Dick Lugar was among the most decent men I have ever known. Kind, loyal, dedicated beyond measure to the service of the American people. Dick Lugar was my dear friend. 

Jill and I send our condolences to his wife Charlene and the entire Lugar family.

name: Joe Biden
text: Wishing everyone in the Orthodox Christian community a peaceful and joyful Easter celebration with friends, family and loved ones. God Bless.

name: Joe Biden
text:
Jill and I are devastated to hear about today’s shooting at the Chabad Poway synagogue. No one should have to worship in fear.

As a country, we must speak out against bigotry and gun violence. We’re in the battle for the soul of this nation—and it’s on all of us to act.

name: Joe Biden
text: I have a message for #TeamJoe: Thank you!

name: Joe Biden
text: I had the privilege to thank one of our grassroots donors. It's because of supporters like Josh we're able to make this campaign a reality and bring this country together.

name: Joe Biden
text:
Thank you to the women of @TheView for the conversation today. It’s always a pleasure to sit down with you at the table. #TheView 

Credit: ABC/Lorenzo Bevilaqua

name: Joe Biden
text: Looking forward to joining the women of @TheView today for my first live interview since announcing my 2020 campaign for President. Tune in 11e|10c|p on @ABCNetwork. #TheView

name: Joe Biden
text: UPDATE: We’re about to close the books on an AMAZING first day of our campaign. It’s not too late to be a part of it. Chip in before midnight to be a Day One donor. http://www.joebiden.com/donate  #Joe2020

name: Joe Biden
text: Our campaign is off to a great start thanks to thousands of Americans who have made donations. If you haven’t had the chance just yet, I hope you will join us too! Head to http://www.joebiden.com/donate  to make a donation today. #Joe2020

name: Joe Biden
text: Folks, earlier today I announced that I’m running for President of the United States. The strength of this movement depends on you. Head over to http://www.joebiden.com/donate  to make a donation today. #Joe2020

name: Joe Biden
text: Our country is being put to the test, but I’ve never been more optimistic about America. Together we can do this. Make a Day One donation to join us. https://www.joebiden.com/donate  #Joe2020

name: Joe Biden
text:
Hoy estoy anunciando mi candidatura para presidente de los Estados Unidos. Somos los Estados Unidos de America - y juntos no hay nada que no podamos hacer. Únete a nuestra campaña: http://www.joebiden.com 
#Joe2020

name: Joe Biden
text: The core values of this nation… our standing in the world… our very democracy...everything that has made America -- America --is at stake. That’s why today I’m announcing my candidacy for President of the United States. #Joe2020

name: Cory Booker
text: The gun industry should be held accountable for its role in the gun violence epidemic. We need to end legal immunity and help survivors seek justice. https://coryb.kr/2V32Ncq

name: Cory Booker
text: One hundred Americans are killed with guns every day. Gun violence is shattering our communities—but we don't have to live that reality. Text ENOUGH to 40203 to learn more about my plan to end the epidemic and how you can take action.

name: Cory Booker
text:
As we were filming in my neighborhood, three men were injured in a shooting a block away. When I say my fight to end gun violence is personal, this is why. 
https://coryb.kr/2V32Ncq

name: Cory Booker
text:
Rick (again) welcome to the Senate. 

May we do better at what our nation needs more of:

More grace & less gratuitous jabs. 
More debating ideas & less demeaning people. 
More kindness & more kindness. 

I'm far from perfect in this. But I'll do better. Let's talk n person soon.

name: Cory Booker
text: During this special month, I want to wish a blessed Ramadan to our Muslim family across the world. May you find spiritual fulfillment and renewal as you celebrate this holy time. Ramadan Kareem!

name: Cory Booker
text: Starting on Day One in office, I’ll take executive action to crack down on gun manufacturers & dealers, close dangerous loopholes, & invest in communities impacted by the epidemic of gun violence. We need to take real measures to protect our country & support survivors.

name: Cory Booker
text: In many states the same commonsense rule that forbids an abusive spouse or ex-spouse to buy a gun does not apply to current or ex-dating partners. That doesn't make sense. My plan to end gun violence would close the “Boyfriend Loophole” once and for all. https://coryb.kr/2V32Ncq

name: Cory Booker
text: We have to keep guns out of the wrong hands. https://coryb.kr/2V32Ncq

name: Cory Booker
text:
We need an aggressive approach to end the epidemic of gun violence in our country. My new plan would:

Keep guns out of the wrong hands
Hold gun manufacturers accountable
Bring the fight to the NRA

name: Cory Booker
text: We're live! Tune in now for a conversation on environmental justice.

name: Cory Booker
text: Tonight at 8pm ET, I’ll be hosting a Facebook Live town hall to discuss environmental issues threatening our communities. We won’t have justice until everyone has access to clean water and air. Hope you can join us: https://www.facebook.com/corybooker/videos/1409397605867782 …

name: Cory Booker
text: Thanks to the thousands of new supporters who donated to my campaign this week! We qualified for the first debate—but now the DNC wants to raise the donor threshold for future debates. Can you help us hit our next 70k donor milestone by chipping in $1?

name: Cory Booker
text: May the Fourth be with you, Jake.

name: Cory Booker
text: My family knew Tyrone well, his kindness was infectious. He was a mentor, a leader, and a champion for his community. This is a huge loss for Nevada, my thoughts are with his family and friends at this time.

name: Cory Booker
text: A note to her competition: Stop tweeting and start competing.

name: Cory Booker
text: Molly, I can’t thank you enough for being the donor that got us to our 65K milestone. I appreciate your support (and Ruud’s amazing dinosaur jacket).

name: Cory Booker
text: Profiting from your own cruel policies. This is disgusting.

name: Cory Booker
text: To every donor, supporter, those who spread the word—THANK YOU! Together, we hit our 65,000 donor threshold last night, which means my spot on the debate stage is secured! Thanks to everyone who made this happen, I'm so grateful to have you in my corner. http://corybooker.com/sixtyfive

name: Cory Booker
text: Tune in!

name: Cory Booker
text: Cash bail doesn't work, it never has & it's time to end it.

name: Cory Booker
text: Honoring the six million Jews murdered in the Holocaust must include a vow to fight anti-Semitism whenever and wherever it shows up. Hate will not deter us from working to create a world where this never happens again. We will never forget. #HolocaustRemembranceDay #YomHaShoah

name: Cory Booker
text: I tried to tell you all!

name: Cory Booker
text: Madalyn, thank you for chipping in to our campaign! Rumor has it we're getting closer to our threshold of 65,000 donors to reach the debate stage...http://corybooker.com/sixtyfive

name: Cory Booker
text: Today I want to shout out my friend @AmolSinha, Exec. Director of @ACLUNJ & a South Asian American leader who champions justice by advocating for all—fighting for our rights with compassion & kindness. I’m proud to have Amol as a leader in my home state—NJ is better for it.

name: Cory Booker
text: In honor of #APAHM this year, we're highlighting individuals who are using their work to advocate for API communities while encouraging visibility and representation.

name: Cory Booker
text: We’re less than 2,000 donors away from hitting the 65,000 donor threshold needed to qualify for the debates. I know we can do this today. Who’s in? http://corybooker.com/sixtyfive

name: Cory Booker
text: The third report in five months of an undocumented minor dying in U.S. custody. We can't be the country that continues to let this happen. Our immigration detention system needs a radical overhaul before more kids die.

name: Cory Booker
text: Today marks the start of Asian Pacific American Heritage Month. As we celebrate the history & achievements of API communities in the coming weeks, we must also remember to do so throughout the year—inclusion isn't a monthly exercise. It requires consistency & purpose. #APAHM

name: Cory Booker
text: Flooding along the Mississippi has devastated communities and leveled homes and levees. As people begin to rebuild, know that this team will be right there beside you. If you're hoping to help, the Red Cross is providing support to those who need it http://rdcrss.org/2LcXtDl

name: Cory Booker
text: Attorney General Barr answers to the American people—not to President Trump—and over the past 24 hours it’s become clear that he lied to us and mishandled the Mueller Report. He needs to step down. Add your name if you agree: https://coryb.kr/2vyZ63U

name: Cory Booker
text: Teachers often have to work two jobs to make ends meet. Classrooms are too big, resources slim. As they march in South Carolina, let’s renew our call for education investment; teachers should be able to do their jobs without the burden of inadequate support & debt. #AllOutMay1

name: Cory Booker
text: One day isn't enough to honor workers around the country, but the best way we can lift them up is by fighting for fair wages, better contracts, health care benefits & just treatment. On #MayDay, let's all pay tribute to those who sacrificed so that we may have workers' rights.

name: Cory Booker
text: San Diego, Baltimore and now Charlotte. If we're not doing everything we can to stop dangerous people from buying guns, we're not doing nearly enough.

name: Cory Booker
text:
Stripping asylum seekers of their right to due process is:
Racist
 Inhumane
Unconstitutional
Take your pick. Either way, it's wrong and we need to end it.

name: Cory Booker
text: I'm reintroducing the Dignity for Detained Immigrants Act because it's morally wrong to extend cruelty to asylum seekers instead of refuge. Indefinite detention is an inhumane system. And it must end now.

name: Cory Booker
text: This is heartbreaking. What John Singleton did for the film canon, what he represents for Black America and what he meant to young filmmakers who came after him can't be overstated. He's a genius and a trailblazer who we won't soon forget.

name: Cory Booker
text: Fue un placer hablar con @jdbalart y @PaulinaSodi. Gracias por la oportunidad!

name: Cory Booker
text: We can't say we care about gun safety reform & then ignore cities where gun violence is shattering communities daily. Baltimore experienced a mass shooting yesterday & it deserves our attention. Gun violence is a national epidemic—our outrage can't be determined by zip codes.

name: Cory Booker
text: This is brilliant. Congratulations to @supermajority on its launch—the power of women is unmatched and we are all indebted to them for the progress made in this country. I cannot wait to see how you transform this nation!

name: Cory Booker
text: I welcome any opportunity to talk about how faith guides me, but I cannot—in good conscience—attend an event put on by an organization that preaches bigotry and sows hate against the LGBTQ community. That's why I am declining an invitation to the Family Leader's July 12 summit.

name: Cory Booker
text: What greater civil right is there than access to clean air? Or clean water? Big thanks to South Carolina for hosting me last week as I rolled out the first planks of my environmental justice plan during the Justice For All tour. https://www.thestate.com/news/politics-government/article229713679.html …

name: Cory Booker
text: Democracy does indeed die in the dark. Judge Damon Keith spent a lifetime bringing truth and justice to light to preserve our country. We won’t forget it. My thoughts are with his family during this difficult time.

name: Cory Booker
text: This is what you call a lie.

name: Cory Booker
text: Ensuring people have access to affordable housing isn’t just a smart investment in our economy—it’s the right thing to do.

name: Cory Booker
text: Thank you David! Grateful for your friendship and your commitment to serving your community.

name: Cory Booker
text: There's something so special about towns like Hampton. Glad I got a chance to visit and speak with you all!

name: Cory Booker
text: Praying for comfort and healing for the Chabad of Poway congregation today, as we deal with yet another mass shooting at a house of worship, fueled by anti-Semitism. Gun safety reform needs to happen—now.

name: Cory Booker
text: Laura, you are doing important work. Thank you for the birthday wishes!

name: Cory Booker
text: Clarendon County, South Carolina, thank you so much for the birthday song (and the vegan cupcakes). This is 50.

name: Cory Booker
text: Today’s the day! If you’re completing 50 minutes of community service to help me celebrate my 50th birthday, share your photos on social media and use #Cory2020—I want to see the impact you’re making in your community!

name: Cory Booker
text: God only made so many perfect heads—gotta let them shine!

name: Cory Booker
text: Nothing humbles me more than sharing moments like this one. Lupe invited me into her home, shared her story, and blessed me with an escapulario for protection on the campaign trail.

name: Cory Booker
text: When I was coming up, I remember how badly I wanted to give back to my community. Here's an option: my team is looking for (paid) fellows with a drive to build a better country. Today's the last day to apply - don't miss it!

name: Cory Booker
text: It's time to hold corporate polluters accountable for the damage they've done to our communities. That starts with ending Trump's rollback of anti-pollution enforcement and making these companies pay up.

name: Cory Booker
text:
Agent Orange in the Passaic River. 
Lead in Flint's water.
Manganese dust in Chicago.

This is what happens when polluters go unchecked. As president, I'll strengthen the Environmental Protection Agency's power and hold those poisoning our communities accountable.

name: Cory Booker
text: The people of New Orleans deserve an infrastructure that won’t fail at a moment’s notice. My friend @LaToyaForNOLA is doing an incredible job leading here.

name: Cory Booker
text: Thank you to everyone in the @iowahousedems who stayed up all night fighting for working families and their right to a secure retirement. Grateful for your leadership!

name: Cory Booker
text: My 50th birthday is in two days & I’m inviting you to celebrate with me by committing to 50 minutes of community service with your friends this Saturday. All you have to do is sign up here to host an event (or find one near you). Hope you can join us: https://www.mobilize.us/corybooker/event/create/ …

name: Cory Booker
text: Fact: Wages for the lowest-income workers in this country have barely risen in four decades but corporate profits are at an 80-plus year high. Something is wrong with that picture.

name: Cory Booker
text: If you live in a community like mine, climate change isn’t just some future threat—it’s an urgent problem right now. #SheThePeople2020

name: Cory Booker
text: This is a poll tax.

name: Cory Booker
text: We all owe a debt to women of color for their leadership. Today at @_shethepeople, I was honored to hear their questions. As your president, I will make sure that inclusion isn't just a box-checking exercise—it will mean having your voice heard at all times in this country.

name: Cory Booker
text: I can't stress how important and huge this win is, not just for Tampa, but for our country as we build a society reflective of all its peoples. Tampa, you did it. Congratulations again, @JaneCastor!

name: Cory Booker
text: Women of color have been on the front lines of movements & in front of the line at the voting booth. Honored to join @_shethepeople today to discuss the issues that matter most to them in this presidential election. Watch live:

name: Cory Booker
text: I support @Culinary226 and @CircusReno workers in their fight for a fair contract. It goes without saying that all workers deserve fair wages and it's shameful that this has to be repeated.

name: Cory Booker
text: Take a few minutes this morning to catch up on last week’s @NowThisNews town hall. We filmed live from a living room in Atlanta and talked about everything from the need for a new Voting Rights Act to a woman’s right to safe, legal abortion:

name: Cory Booker
text:
Having face-to-face conversations is often the best way to learn about the most important issues affecting communities...

Grateful to @blocbyblocMKE for bringing me along this morning to knock on doors and see firsthand the incredible work they do for communities of color.

name: Cory Booker
text: My heart breaks for Nigel and his family. We have to build a world where LGBTQ kids feel loved and affirmed in their identities. We honor Nigel by fighting for such a world every day.

name: Cory Booker
text: Milwaukee, thank you for having me today to discuss gun violence in our communities. I refuse to offer "thoughts & prayers" alone—as my mom would say, faith without works is dead. We need action on gun safety measures like universal background checks and an assault weapons ban.

name: Cory Booker
text: The face of gun violence in this country doesn't stop at mass shootings—it's an everyday reality for many people. I'm not going to ignore that constant trauma.

name: Cory Booker
text: I'm on a mission in this campaign to make people's lives better. And really, that's the number one priority.

name: Cory Booker
text: This is not up for debate: Fair wages and benefits should be extended to all working Americans in this country. Inspired by Stop & Shop employees, who demanded their voices be heard and their work valued.

name: Cory Booker
text: Views of our home from space never get old. Happy #EarthDay!

name: Cory Booker
text: Thank you for having me @EricGarcetti. It is truly inspiring to see what's possible for our country when leadership finds solutions that benefit both our environment and our economy. Plants like this one are the future.

name: Cory Booker
text: On #EarthDay, we can't forget communities that experience the biggest consequences of air pollution, water contamination, and more. The Environmental Justice Caucus will ensure that protecting our planet also means protecting our most vulnerable.

name: Cory Booker
text: .@KonfrstForHouse, I am honored to have you join team @CoryforIowa! It was great seeing you and your family last week. I look forward to being back in Iowa soon. Thank you for your hard work in the Iowa House!

name: Cory Booker
text: Students are the ones who will have to deal with the decisions lawmakers make for decades to come—protecting their right to vote is paramount. Thank you, @JeanneShaheen, for leading the fight in New Hampshire to protect student voters. I'm proud to support this fight.

name: Cory Booker
text: Five years after one of the worst man-made environmental disasters in our history, Flint still doesn't have clean water. And we're still fighting for clean water in places like Newark, Pittsburgh, & Detroit. Who are we if we can't guarantee this basic right to Americans?

name: Cory Booker
text: Taking time to reflect on the enduring power of grace this Easter morning. Happy Easter to everyone celebrating!

name: Cory Booker
text: The Apostle Paul wrote, "Rejoice with those who rejoice, weep with those who weep." On a day meant for celebration, so many families in Sri Lanka are devastated, and my heart breaks along with theirs. There's absolutely no justification for this.

name: Cory Booker
text: I hope the force is with us. Thanks for having me, Ben! Happy to help you and @Schneiderhuf carry on this tradition. Send me a picture of the model next year when it's complete!

name: Cory Booker
text: Blessed to meet with such an inspiring group of women today. The generous hospitality they showed to me and my team while sharing personal, harrowing stories of our immigration system is a lesson for us all about common decency, humanity and family.

name: Cory Booker
text: Columbine was 20 years ago, and yet we still haven’t taken meaningful action to stop gun violence. Enough is enough—we can't wait for progress. People are getting shot every day. It was time then, and it's time now.

name: Cory Booker
text: The New Colossus says, “Give me your tired, your poor, your huddled masses yearning to be free." Nowhere does it say kidnap families seeking a better life. These vigilantes are pointing to the administration as their license to do this.

name: Cory Booker
text: The Marijuana Justice Act wouldn’t just legalize marijuana—it would expunge the records of millions of people who have been hurt by the War on Drugs.

name: Cory Booker
text: As we work to legalize marijuana nationwide, we’ve got to also ensure equity in the marijuana industry. Communities that have been historically targeted by the failed War on Drugs can't be left out of opportunities to participate in the legal marijuana economy.

name: Cory Booker
text: Thanks so much for having me! We’ve got to make sure workers are included in company buyback profits—not just shareholders.

name: Cory Booker
text: The Passover story—one of redemption and freedom—is among the most powerful we have. Chag Pesach Sameach to everyone celebrating!

name: Cory Booker
text: Fired up to be back in Nevada—a second home for me since my mom lives here! Excited to meet new people in Reno, Carson City and rural communities throughout the state today.

name: Cory Booker
text: In the wealthiest country in the world, we've got to do more to ensure hard-working Americans can provide for themselves and their families. This plan will lift 15 million Americans out of poverty and help nearly half of all Americans pay for the rising cost of living.

name: Cory Booker
text: A cost-of-living refund matters to a low-income student who under the current code is excluded from benefits. The Rise Credit will help—30 percent of college students in this country struggle just to buy food.

name: Cory Booker
text: That matters to people caring for kids or elderly or sick family members, whose annual out-of-pocket costs to support their loved ones can reach the thousands. Combined with their own cost of living, the expenses can be crippling.

name: Cory Booker
text: The Rise Credit would expand eligibility of the Earned Income Tax Credit to include those typically left out—students, caregivers, & most people without kids—giving households a cost-of-living refund of up to $8,000.

name: Cory Booker
text: The cost of living is rising and families and individuals are struggling under current tax codes. The solution is simple—give them a refund. That's what the Rise Credit will do.

name: Cory Booker
text: We have a leader in the White House who chooses who to protect & support based on racism & bigotry. That's not leadership at all. That's playground politics. We need a president who will represent all of our country's people. And we won't accept anything less.

name: Cory Booker
text: Believe climate change is real and women should make their own reproductive health decisions? Then apply for a paid internship (or to receive college credit) with #Cory2020

name: Cory Booker
text:
The Trump administration posted an unsearchable pdf of the Mueller report so it would be harder for you to read.

We made it easier. Here’s a searchable version:

name: Cory Booker
text:
The American people deserve the truth.

name: Cory Booker

name: Cory Booker
text: A marijuana conviction is often a life sentence—people can’t get jobs or many business licenses, and they can’t get food assistance like SNAP or public housing if it's a felony. The @abaesq found over 45,000 collateral consequences facing formerly incarcerated people.

name: Cory Booker
text: And it’s not enough to just legalize marijuana, we should help those with records for use and possession convictions, and allow people currently in prison for marijuana-related crimes to petition for resentencing, which is why my legislation includes expungement provisions.

name: Cory Booker
text: Black people are 3.7 times more likely to be arrested for marijuana possession than their white peers even though they use marijuana at similar rates. If we truly want to be a fair and just nation we need to correct for this disparate treatment of enforcement practices.

name: Cory Booker
text: The Marijuana Justice Act doesn’t just end the federal prohibition on marijuana—it also incentivizes states to change their marijuana laws if those laws are being enforced in a way that disproportionately impacts people of color and the poor.

name: Cory Booker
text: The failed War on Drugs has really been a war on people—disproportionately criminalizing poor people, people of color & people with mental illness. text: My mother took care of my father when he was ill with Parkinson’s onset dementia. We have to do a better job of tackling the problems associated with neurological diseases—better research, better health care, better support for caregivers.

name: Cory Booker
text: Hope is the active conviction that despair will never have the last word, and this weekend, that’s what I felt—hope.

name: Cory Booker
text: We have to call for a revival of ideals of grace and decency in this country. We have to manifest a greater sense of kindness toward one another.

name: Cory Booker
text: With some awesome folks in Exeter this morning kicking off an exciting weekend around New Hampshire—my first trip to the state since I announced my run for president. Grateful for the warm welcome (and hot coffee!)

name: Cory Booker
text:
My heart is with the loved ones of the victims of the horrific shooting in Aurora, Illinois that has left 5 people dead and more injured. 

But we know our thoughts and prayers are not enough. Congress must take action to prevent gun violence.

name: Cory Booker
text: Across this country people are surrendering to despair and cynicism about our ability to solve our problems. I’m running for president because I know when we unite around a common purpose we can change that.

name: Cory Booker
text: In South Carolina last weekend I was reminded that even in our darkest moments of despair, we can never give up hope. We can never give up faith.

name: Cory Booker
text: For over a century, Congress has failed 200 times to pass legislation recognizing lynching for what it is—a bias-motivated act of terror. Our bill, just unanimously passed in the Senate, would finally make lynching a federal crime. The House must now act.

name: Cory Booker
text: New Hampshire! Looking forward to spending a long weekend in your beautiful state—my first trip to the Granite State as a presidential candidate. Hope to see you there.

name: Cory Booker
text: In an atmosphere of cynicism often found in Washington, we’ve found ways to find common ground and get things done that make our country more fair and just—including signing into law our bipartisan criminal justice reform bill that’s already changing lives across this country.

name: Cory Booker
text:
Trump’s inability to follow through on a campaign promise is not a national emergency. 

Let’s not forget those still struggling to rebuild their lives after this administration failed to respond effectively to real emergencies in places like Puerto Rico.

name: Cory Booker
text: The Senate just unanimously passed our bill to make lynching a federal crime. This bill acknowledges the wrongs in our history and honors the memories of those brutally killed. Making this law is the right thing to do—I hope the House will move quickly to pass.

name: Cory Booker
text: One year ago, the #Parkland community lost 17 lives in a heinous act of gun violence. #SinceParkland 1,200 kids in America have been killed by guns. It’s long past time we unite in common purpose and pass common sense gun safety legislation to prevent more tragedy.

name: Cory Booker
text: We have a system of mass incarceration that feeds upon the poor, the mentally ill, the addicted, and disproportionately on communities of color. Mr. Barr has shown an unwillingness to call out this broken system. For this reason and more I cannot support his nomination.

name: Cory Booker
text: Edward was one of the first people released after our First Step Act became law. Please listen to his story, and see his humanity and dignity. He’s now free but there are too many still incarcerated. The war on drugs is a war on people and it must end.

name: Cory Booker
text: Looking forward to joining @Maddow at 9pm ET tonight to discuss my presidential run and more. Hope you’ll tune in.

name: Cory Booker
text: In the richest country in the world, the lack of #paidleave is a moral affront. We must pass legislation to guarantee paid family and medical leave for Americans. #FAMILYAct

name: Cory Booker
text: It’s not just about who’s our president—it’s about who we are. It’s time for us to pull together. It’s time for us to work together. And if we do these things, America will rise together. Join us: http://corybooker.com

name: Cory Booker
text: Thank you to Bishop Bailey and First Lady Bailey for welcoming another New Jersey boy into your South Carolina flock.

name: Cory Booker
text: I always say before you speak of your religion you should show it by how you treat other people. Had the privilege of worshipping this morning at Right Direction Ministries, a congregation that’s dedicated to serving the Columbia, SC community.

name: Cory Booker
text: They say imitation is the sincerest form of flattery, my friend.

name: Cory Booker
text: Today, nearly 1 in 3 American families have zero to negative wealth, and the wealth gap is growing. My bill would create a savings account for every American child to invest in themselves through things like buying a home or paying for higher education.

name: Cory Booker
text: South Carolina — hope to see you at an event today or tomorrow during my first trip to your great state as a presidential candidate!

name: Cory Booker
text: As I leave Iowa tonight, my spirit is lifted. Thank you to the thousands of people—from Mason City to Des Moines—who took the time over the past several days to meet up and3 allow me to share why our campaign, our message, is different. Be back again soon!

name: Cory Booker
text: After a long day yesterday traveling around Iowa from Mason City to Waterloo to Cedar Rapids it was great to wind down the day in Iowa City at Micky’s!

name: Cory Booker
text: Had a powerful conversation this afternoon with inspirational local leaders in Waterloo about the concerns facing their community. I believe that in this country we can restore our sense of common purpose by focusing on our common pain—that’s at the core of my campaign ahead.

name: Cory Booker
text: Incredible day in Iowa (and still going!) I told my staff to buckle up—I’m going to be a candidate that goes to everybody I possibly can, to every community and every neighborhood. Honored to start this journey in Mason City.

name: Cory Booker
text: The multiple detailed allegations against the Lt. Gov. of Virginia are deeply troubling. They are serious, credible, and corroborated by others. It is no longer appropriate for him to serve. He should resign.

name: Cory Booker
text: Today marks 51 years since one of the most violent moments in the civil rights movement in Orangeburg, SC where 3 students were killed and 28 people were injured protesting segregation. We honor the victims by continuing their fight for justice & equality.

name: Cory Booker
text: The first question I was asked in Iowa was about #GreenNewDeal. The hard truth is climate change has imperiled our planet—it’s going to take bold action now to save it including dramatic investment in green energy that will create the jobs of the future. We can do this.

name: Cory Booker
text: Grateful to kick off my first Iowa trip as a presidential candidate surrounded by 5 generations of family at my Aunt Alma's home. All that I am is because of the work, sacrifice and love of my ancestors. As I said last night, I'm going to run a campaign my family can be proud of.

name: Cory Booker
text: John Dingell will be remembered as a legendary public servant who served his constituents honorably for six decades. My heart is with the Dingell family during this difficult time.

name: Cory Booker
text: Mr. Barr's record on mass incarceration and admitted lack of knowledge on the role of implicit racial bias in our criminal justice system were key factors in my no vote today. 2/

name: Cory Booker
text: Our next Attorney General must defend civil rights and our shared principles of equal protection. I am not persuaded Mr. Barr will meet this challenge. I pray I am wrong. 1/

name: Cory Booker
text: Excited to join @AOC & @SenMarkey on a historic #GreenNewDeal resolution to address the peril of climate change and worsening inequality. Our history is a testimony to the achievement of what some think is impossible — we must take bold action now.

name: Cory Booker
text:

name: Cory Booker

name: Cory Booker
text: The $15 minimum wage bill signed by @GovMurphy this week is big step forward for economic justice in our state. Glad NJ is leading by example—our #FightFor15 continues to ensure every working American has a job that pays a living wage.

name: Cory Booker
text: It takes more than a nod to unity at the top of a speech to bring our country together. Our president has spent the last 2 years trying to drive us apart. Actions speak louder than words. #SOTU

name: Cory Booker
text: Excited to hear my good friend @StaceyAbrams deliver her history-making #SOTU response tonight — one that will share an inspiring and hopeful vision for our country, for all Americans.

name: Cory Booker

name: Cory Booker
text: Our campaign is funded by grassroots donations from people like you. No corporate PACs. No federal lobbyists. Please pitch in now and be a part of this team from the beginning.

name: Cory Booker

name: Cory Booker

name: Cory Booker

name: Cory Booker
text: The lines that divide us are nowhere near as strong as the ties that bind us. When we put aside our differences there’s nothing we can’t accomplish—that’s going to be a central theme of my campaign & I hope you’ll sign up to be a part of it:

name: Cory Booker
text:
I was honored to have my mom with me yesterday from the very moment I announced my run for president. This is a campaign that will live up to my mom’s words and make her proud. I hope you’ll join us on this journey: http://corybooker.com

name: Cory Booker

name: Cory Booker
text:
Deeply grateful for you and this tweet my brother. 

Your integrity, strong sense of justice, and righteous and relentless activism is light in our nation.

name: Cory Booker
text: I’m not in this race to tear people down. I’m in it to build people up and bring people together to make progressive change and build a country that's more fair and more just.

name: Cory Booker
text:
I know that together, we can… we will, rise.

I hope you’ll join me.

name: Cory Booker
text: Despite our divisions, the hatred of some, and the economic hardship of many, together we will ensure that our generation and generations to come will achieve things others say can’t be done.

name: Cory Booker
text: When I went down to Washington, people told me it was a place where you couldn’t make change happen, but I’ve been able to pass laws that start to turn the tide against mass incarceration and spark historic investment in vulnerable communities.

name: Cory Booker
text: When I moved to Newark to protect tenants from slumlords, people told us we couldn't win. Well, we beat them. When I was mayor, we showed the doubters that impossible things could still happen in our city.

name: Cory Booker
text: I've spent my entire career running toward big challenges others had given up on, bringing people together to do things that we were told were impossible. That's what our country needs right now.

name: Cory Booker
text:
People feel left out. They worry that the lines that divide us right now are stronger than the ties that bind us. I’m running to change that.

In America, we have a common pain, common challenges. But what we're lacking is a sense of common purpose.

name: Cory Booker
text: The promise of our country, that this is a country that works for everyone, is hanging in the balance. When we should be coming together to take on our biggest challenges, there are forces at work trying to split us apart.

name: Cory Booker

text:

He had wise words that kept me grounded. When I graduated Law School: "Boy u got more degrees than the month of July but you ain't hot, life's about the service you give not the degrees you get."

Our last stop on this NH trip was another great one. Thank you for the very warm welcome and for taking the time to hear about my #PeopleFirst vision for America.

#OneNationOneDestiny #fitn #NHpolitics @KeeneState_

name: Julián Castro
text: Thanks for coming out, and for all your good work to end food insecurity for low income kids — I’m with you!

name: Julián Castro
text:
Access to healthcare (not just health insurance) is a primary concern all over the country. In Lebanon, NH we agreed that we need to strengthen Medicare and make it available to everyone, and that all women should have the right to choose.

#nhpolitics #fitn @NHUVDems

name: Julián Castro
text: At HUD during the Obama administration, we made serious progress on ending homelessness in this country. It’s time we recommit ourselves to that cause. Thank you @helpsonv and @NHAvoice for this eye opening tour.

name: Julián Castro
text:
Second event of the day at Lucky Dog Tavern with @plyareadems. Thank you all for coming out! 

More of today's events here  http://mobilize.us/julianforthefuture … 
Join us!

#nhpolitics #julián2020

name: Julián Castro
text: We must do more to end homelessness in this country. On my campaign, housing won’t be a back burner issue. #PeopleFirst #OneNationOneDestiny /2

name: Julián Castro
text: Many don’t know this, but beneath the massive casinos Las Vegas is known for, hundreds of homeless residents find shelter in a network of storm drain tunnels. Yesterday I toured these tunnels with local organizations working to find them permanent housing and support. /1

name: Julián Castro
text: My deepest condolences are with the community of Chabad of Poway as they mourn this despicable attack on their community. On this last day of Passover, we know without a doubt that hate and anti-semitism are on the rise and our tears today are bitter.

name: Julián Castro
text: The next leg of our weekend will be in New Hampshire! We have a handful of events tomorrow, beginning with a 9am breakfast. Join us! #nhpolitics

name: Julián Castro
text: We need an active government response with a 21st century safety net, including healthcare, fair pay, higher education and housing. We need to take action to protect our environment, and empower our workers to organize & hold lawmakers accountable. #WorkersForum @SEIU @CAPAction

name: Julián Castro
text: There are so many people right now that don't get a fair shot because they have to breathe dirty air or drink dirty water. We have people who aren't being paid a livable wage, with no access to healthcare or affordable housing options. #WorkersForum

name: Julián Castro
text: We don't have to choose between protecting our planet and creating jobs. That's why I like the #GreenNewDeal. My first executive order as President will be to recommit the US to the #ParisClimateAccord then make mass investments in renewable energy. #WorkersForum @SEIU @CAPAction

name: Julián Castro
text: It's important that we strengthen the Violence Against Women Act, and make sure our immigrant communities are comfortable reporting sexual assault and violence in the workplace (and elsewhere). #WorkersForum @SEIU @CAPAction

name: Julián Castro
text: Housing is a human right. We know the steps to take to provide affordable housing options for all, we just need the will to do it. I will be unrolling a comprehensive housing plan soon. Stay tuned. #WorkersForum @SEIU @CAPAction #housingisahumanright

name: Julián Castro
text: We need to incentivize states to empower their residents to organize and unionize. And I'm walking the walk: I've given my campaign staff the option to unionize and paying interns $15/hr. #WorkersForum @SEIU @CAPAction

name: Julián Castro
text: We need to get back to a place where everyone counts. We need to make sure our policies are meeting the needs of communities of color, and make sure we're not leaving Native American communities behind. #WorkersForum @SEIU @CAPAction

name: Julián Castro
text: About to hit the stage at the @SEIU / @CAPAction #WorkersForum. Watch live NOW  http://workersforum.org

name: Julián Castro
text: On my 7th trip through Nevada and we've talked conservation, climate and housing, toured homeless camps in the tunnels of Las Vegas, attended some great house parties, and now we're kicking off the @SEIU / @CAPAction #WorkersForum. #NV

name: Julián Castro
text: Share your questions for our @SEIU / @CAPAction forum starting at 1pm ET! Livestream will be at http://workersforum.org .

name: Julián Castro
text: Hey y’all  I’ve got a quick message for you. http://bit.ly/JCheyyall

name: Julián Castro
text: Today I toured the tunnels beneath Las Vegas that provide shelter to hundreds of homeless individuals escaping the desert heat. We must do more as a nation to support orgs like @helpsonv & @NHAvoice that provide housing support for these communities. #housingisahumanright

name: Julián Castro
text: Today's affordable housing roundtable with @NHAvoice, @helpsonv and Clark County Social Services, discussing how Nevada's housing issues are inflating homelessness.

name: Julián Castro
text:
Meet us this evening in Las Vegas!  http://bit.ly/JCLV042619 

#OneNationOneDestiny

name: Julián Castro
text: Today in Las Vegas! #TeamJulián has events all day, including a meet and greet this evening — join us  http://bit.ly/JCLV042619

name: Julián Castro
text: I wanted to go straight to what this President has considered his bread-and-butter issue. This is how he stokes division. This is how he stokes fear and paranoia. So I released a People First immigration plan that represents a completely different vision.

name: Julián Castro
text: The people of Flint have been without clean water for 5 years. This shameful failure has left thousands of families—disproportionately families of color—without water to drink or bathe in. Support activists like @LittleMissFlint and contribute today http://gofundme.com/LMFwater

name: Julián Castro
text: Hey, @jessicalbyrd, it happens all the time! Thank you all for creating #ShethePeople2020, the first-ever Presidential candidate forum focused on women of color who are too often overlooked in this country and I know firsthand are powerful agents of change.

name: Julián Castro
text: To be the fairest nation, we have to reform and reimagine our justice system.  We're going to keep saying the names of people of color who were victims of state violence. We're going to keep saying that #BlackLivesMatter, while working toward a justice system where it's true.

name: Julián Castro
text: My story wouldn't be possible without the strong women who came before me and passed me the baton. My mother @castrocountry would tell me, "As a citizen, you need to participate in the democratic process. If something is wrong, you can change it."

name: Julián Castro
text: I have zero confidence in anything this administration tells us when it comes to immigration policy. They’ve chosen cruelty as their guiding principle, and it has failed. It’s time we choose compassion. #PeopleFirst

name: Julián Castro
text:
This is Fiesta. 

Last night at #NIOSA (Night in Old San Antonio) I got to see old friends, meet new ones, and hand out some of my new Fiesta medals! 

We still have some available  http://bit.ly/JCfiesta2019  #vivafiesta #satx

name: Julián Castro
text: What I believe in is that everyone in this country should have health care, not just health insurance - I also believe in a woman’s right to choose. #SheThePeople2020

name: Julián Castro
text: We’re on our way to Houston for #SheThePeople2020, the nation’s 1st presidential forum focused on women of color. We will tweet the livestream of my remarks at 1:30pm CT/2:30pm ET. Tune in!

name: Julián Castro
text: We’re LIVE in downtown San Antonio for #Fiesta. Come say hello!

name: Julián Castro
text: We can walk and chew gum at the same time. Democrats can make the case for impeachment while laying out a positive vision for the future of our country. @LissandraVilla

name: Julián Castro
text:
Happy Fiesta, San Antonio! #JuliánForTheFuture Fiesta medals are in. We have a limited supply available for pickup in SA, and you might just spot me at some Fiesta festivities this week with medals to give away!

Contribute for yours here: http://bit.ly/JCfiesta2019 

#VivaFiesta

name: Julián Castro
text: "That small punctuation mark in Castro’s name serves as a powerful example of nonwhite visibility, particularly for Latinx people." - @XorjeO

name: Julián Castro
text: I'm proposing a 21st century Marshall Plan for Central and South America so people can find safety, security and opportunity in their home  countries. We need to invest more, not less as Trump suggests, in order to lower the amount of families needing asylum. #PeopleFirst

name: Julián Castro
text: The Trump administration’s politicization of the 2020 census would have serious consequences—including the possible undercounting of 6.5 million people from immigrant communities. We need a fair and accurate count, we can’t let this power grab stand.

name: Julián Castro
text: The Democratic Party is a big tent. The candidates running for president are representative of the incredible diversity of this country—including the number of badass female candidates breaking barriers. #AM2DM

name: Julián Castro
text: It’s clear the President tried to violate the law in a number of different ways. We must stand up for the rule of law.

name: Julián Castro
text: It was great to meet you! Thank you for your support.

name: Julián Castro
text: It’s flat out undemocratic to tell students who live, work, and learn in local communities that they can’t participate in the democratic process. I join @JeanneShaheen in condemning this blanket voter suppression scam.

name: Julián Castro
text: We're just an hour away -- hope to see you there!

name: Julián Castro
text: I will demilitarize police departments & decrease overreliance on policing to keep communities safe. I will create an office within the DOJ to address racially discriminatory policing, hold offending officers & departments accountable, and increase unconscious bias training.

name: Julián Castro
text: This isn't an isolated incident. It's part of a pattern that has allowed the dehumanization of young black folks across the country. It is a structural problem that needs a structural solution. As president, I will use my executive power to meaningfully address police violence.

name: Julián Castro
text: The @browardsheriff officers who brutalized a 15-year-old child must be held accountable, but how many more times does this need to happen before we hold accountable the system that lets it continue? We need #JusticeForLucca, but we also need #PoliceReform now.

name: Julián Castro
text: Tune in!

name: Julián Castro
text: I’m in! Climate change is a global crisis that knows no borders. My first executive action as President would be to recommit the U.S. to the Paris Climate Accord, and to reestablish America as a leader in the fight against climate change. #EarthDay

name: Julián Castro
text: I'm looking forward to joining @CapehartJ for a thoughtful conversation about the future of America, post-Donald Trump. Join us at the @92Y in #NYC tomorrow, April 22 → http://bit.ly/Julian92y

name: Julián Castro
text:
Today, we're at risk of dropping the baton. And that's why I'm running for President. Because we're going to make sure that the promise of America is there for everyone. #OneNationOneDestiny 

/3

name: Julián Castro
text: But right now, the relay isn't working. Today we're falling backwards instead of moving forward. And the opportunities that made America, America are reaching fewer and fewer people. /2

name: Julián Castro
text: My family's story wouldn't be possible without a country that challenged itself to live up to the promise of America. That was the point of the #AmericanDream: It wasn't supposed to be just a dream. America was the place where dreams could become real. /1

name: Julián Castro
text: On a day of redemption and hope, the evil of these attacks on Easter worshippers and tourists in Sri Lanka is deeply saddening. My prayers today are with the dead and injured, and their families. May we find grace.

name: Julián Castro
text: It’s not enough just to say we want to #LegalizeIt. We will also regulate it, taking best practices of states that have successfully legalized marijuana. And while we’re at it, we’ll expunge the records of folks who’ve been incarcerated for using it.

name: Julián Castro
text:
Americans want a president they can trust, not one who lies and puts his own interests first. When I’m elected, I will work to restore integrity and accountability to the White House. 

@AliVelshi

name: Julián Castro
text: Chag Pesach sameach, to all those celebrating #Passover across the United States and the world!

name: Julián Castro
text: Earlier today, I told @AC360 that I think it would be perfectly reasonable for Congress to open up impeachment hearings against President Trump. Robert Mueller clearly left that option in the hands of Congress.

name: Julián Castro
text:
Whether it’s handing out massive tax cuts to his billionaire donors, or asking our adversaries to influence our elections, Donald Trump always puts his own interests above our nation’s interests. 

As President, I will always work toward the best interest of the American people.

name: Julián Castro
text: As I’ve said many times, Congress should be subject to the Freedom of Information Act. Now.

name: Julián Castro
text: Failure to properly equip our schools and pay our teachers has almost doubled our shortage of educators since 2015. This morning, @rweingarten laid out the crisis at hand and how we can solve it. #FreedomToTeach #FundOurFuture

name: Julián Castro
text: The American people deserve to hear the full truth. Robert Mueller should testify in front of Congress and the American people. Add your name if you agree.  http://bit.ly/JCdemandtruth

name: Julián Castro
text: This report makes clear: Donald Trump is looking out for himself, not for America. We must restore integrity and accountability to the White House.

name: Julián Castro
text: Far from exonerating anyone, the Special Counsel report exposes disgraceful behavior by Donald Trump and his inner circle—both in seeking assistance from Russia & attempting to cover it up. Mueller should testify and Congress should investigate charges of obstruction of justice.

name: Julián Castro
text: Donald Trump is once again attempting to use a political appointee to pre-spin a report about an investigation into his own campaign. The full report should be released unimpeded by media stunts.

name: Julián Castro
text: Our immigration enforcement system is built around the lie that immigrants present a threat to national security. This lie has allowed Trump & others to demonize and attack immigrants for political gain. My #PeopleFirst immigration plan would overhaul enforcement in this country.

name: Julián Castro
text: Hey y'all. I wanted to make sure our friends in the Reno, NV area knew we'd be in town today at 3:30pm! Join #TeamJulián and the @WashoeDEMS for a meet and greet  http://bit.ly/JCinReno

name: Julián Castro
text: As we reflect on the 20th anniversary of the Columbine shooting, half a million Colorado students are missing school today due to the threat of a copycat attack. We’re forced to close our schools because of inaction on the part of lawmakers. Let that sink in.

name: Julián Castro
text:
Thank you @UChiPolitics and @davidaxelrod for hosting me tonight and allowing me to share my vision for our country’s future. It’s inspiring to see so many talented and driven young minds interested in public service.

#PeopleFirst #OneNationOneDestiny

name: Julián Castro
text: From separating families to attacking asylum seekers, this administration’s bottomless cruelty has failed time and time again. We need compassion, not cruelty, in our immigration system. #PeopleFirst

name: Julián Castro
text: Watch our conversation live now with @davidaxelrod and @UChiPolitics

name: Julián Castro
text: As a native Texan, I know what it’s like to be overlooked by Democratic presidential hopefuls. I’m going to travel everywhere and work hard for every vote, because on this campaign, everyone counts.

name: Julián Castro
text: Last week @CNN asked what sets me apart from the other candidates. My answer? I'm one of the only candidates with executive experience as Mayor of the 7th largest city in the country and as a former cabinet Secretary under President Obama.

name: Julián Castro
text: Friends in the #NYC area, I hope you'll head over to the 92nd Street Y on Monday, April 22 for a conversation Jonathan Capehart and I will be having about the future of America.  http://bit.ly/Julian92y

name: Julián Castro
text: Climate change will increasingly drive migration and instability in the years to come. My #PeopleFirst immigration plan would restore our refugee program and adapt it to accommodate those displaced by a changing climate.

name: Julián Castro
text: I told the Asian & Latino Coalition in Des Moines: I’m not much for making this country anything ‘again’, I’m not looking to the past. But there is one thing I look to the past for: I want to restore integrity to the White House. #IACaucus

name: Julián Castro
text:
Visiting with the House and Senate Democratic Caucuses, as well as the interns and pages, at the Iowa State Capitol today in Des Moines.

#IACaucus

name: Julián Castro
text: We’ve got a full day in Des Moines today, including a visit with the House and Senate Democrats at the state Capitol! For those in the area, come join us in Machinists Hall at 7pm for the Asian and Latino Caucus Reception: http://mobilize.us/julianforthefuture/event/89903/ …

name: Julián Castro
text: Heartbreaking images out of Paris as the beloved #NotreDame burns. An iconic symbol of the City of Love, the whole world mourns this loss of history and beauty.

name: Julián Castro
text:
It was great to tour @CentralCampusDM’s Skilled Trades Alliance in Des Moines this morning to learn about the 39 hands-on apprentice and trades programs they have on campus—from masonry to marine biology. 

Thanks for the chess photo, @DMschools!

name: Julián Castro
text: Thank you @pchtf for hosting me at your annual #AffordableHousingWeek. We can't overstate the importance of the work you're doing, and the importance of connecting the dots between policy issues like #housing, #education, and #transportation. #HousingForAll

name: Julián Castro
text: The issue folks wanted to hear about most at @PPLiveIowa? Climate change. I support the vision of the #GreenNewDeal because I know how urgent it is to be bold on climate change. We can’t afford to be timid. #IAcaucus

name: Julián Castro
text: Hey, y’all! Our flight was cancelled, so we drove to Iowa! We made it and are doing @ppLiveIowa at 7 PM in Iowa City tonight. Big day in Des Moines tomorrow. Stay tuned!

name: Julián Castro
text:
From Art Cullen at Iowa’s Storm Lake Times : “All the Democrats should take up Castro’s cause. It is the optimistic antidote to Trump that recognizes the basic American sense of fairness.” #IACaucus

http://www.stormlake.com/articles/2019/04/12/castro%E2%80%99s-positive-vision …

name: Julián Castro
text:
I am sorry to announce that we must cancel events in Davenport and Muscatine, IA today due to inclement weather.

You can still attend our @PPLiveIowa podcast recording in Iowa City, and we'll be in Des Moines tomorrow with the Asian & Latino Coalition:

name: Julián Castro
text: I was honored to share the stage with @GovEvers, and share a selfie with Lt. Gov @TheOtherMandela at the @WisDems #Founders2019 annual gala.

name: Julián Castro
text: Thank you @nadxely2 and @voces_milwaukee for inviting me to take part in your day of action, and for your persistent work for immigrant families' rights. #PeopleFirst #MayDay

name: Julián Castro
text:
Where I come from. #OneNationOneDestiny #PeopleFirst

http://bit.ly/julian4thefuture …

name: Julián Castro
text: I am grateful for @IlhanMN's courage and leadership and I stand with her - and with others targeted by the President's anti-Muslim rhetoric.

name: Julián Castro
text:
This is not rocket science. Closing the border AND cutting aid to Central America is downright stupid. 

I have a comprehensive immigration plan, and with your help, I can hash it out on the debate stage in June  http://bit.ly/JCfortheFuture

name: Julián Castro
text: Last night at my #CNNTownHall, someone asked me for one piece of advice I’d give to Donald Trump. I kept it simple: “Follow the law.”

name: Julián Castro
text:
To the transgender troops who proudly serve our country every day: this fight isn't over and we will continue to stand with you to oppose this discriminatory ban. 

#TransMilitaryBan #FightTheBan #OneNationOneDestiny

name: Julián Castro
text: New England was built by working families, and to ensure the community continues to thrive, we must protect wages and benefits, including healthcare. I urge Stop & Shop to negotiate in good faith with UFCW's New England members.

name: Julián Castro
text: We need to improve K-12 education by investing in  public schools and paying teachers what they deserve. And we need to  make higher education universal — at least tuition-free, so that  everyone gets the knowledge an skills that they need to compete.  #CastroTownHall

name: Julián Castro
text: As mayor of San Antonio, I created @PreK4SA which expanded high quality Pre-K for 4 year olds throughout the city. I want to do that for our country. And it doesn't stop there. http://bit.ly/JCfortheFuture

name: Julián Castro
text:
Just wrapped up my @cnn town hall and I’m so glad I got to share my vision for our country’s future with you. If you like what you heard, please make a contribution to help us make the debates: http://bit.ly/JCfortheFuture 
#CastroTownHall

name: Julián Castro
text: My hope is that, not only am I going to be offering a new vision for the future — one that is inclusive and based in integrity — but that some Latino boys and girls will see me and think, "hey, I can do that too." Help bring this vision to life: http://bit.ly/JCfortheFuture

name: Julián Castro
text: I'm very proud of my background...it is meaningful to run right now when the Latino community feels that this president has put a target on our backs. My vision is inclusive. #CastroTownHall

name: Julián Castro
text: I like the concept of a #GreenNewDeal. Invest in renewable energy, cut carbon emissions and convince other countries to do the same. But today we can’t do this, because this POTUS has decided to bury his head in the sand and pretend this isn’t a problem. But we know the truth.

name: Julián Castro
text: Legalize it. Then expunge the records of folks who are in prison for marijuana use. #CastroTownHall

name: Julián Castro
text: The American people need to see the #MuellerReport. Most importantly going forward, we need a standard for cybersecurity in our elections. #CastroTownHall

name: Julián Castro
text: Under my #PeopleFirst immigration plan we would put folks on a pathway to citizenship. That includes Dreamers and TPS recipients who have a target in their backs thanks to Donald Trump. #CastroTownHall

name: Julián Castro
text:
I would tell this president that he is not above the law, he needs to follow the law. Our constitution created three equal branches. President Trump needs to respect Congress and respect the courts. 
#CastroTownHall

name: Julián Castro
text: Advice to President Trump for the rest of your term: Follow the law. #CastroTownHall

name: Julián Castro
text: We’ve inherited many moral assets from our founders. But we’ve also inherited moral debts. One of those debts that we’ve never paid is the debt for the original sin of slavery. #CastroTownHall

name: Julián Castro
text: If we find ourselves in another housing crisis like we did 10 years ago, we need to put #PeopleFirst. We need to ensure folks can stay in their homes. Plain and simple. We should center policy around people. #CastroTownHall

name: Julián Castro
text: I don't believe that profit motive should ever prevent someone from getting the health care—not health insurance, but health care—that they need. #CastroTownHall

name: Julián Castro
text: A new low in the bottomless pit of cruelty towards immigrants. I look forward to discussing my #PeopleFirst immigration policy on tonight’s #CNNTownHall at 10pm ET/9pm CT.

name: Julián Castro
text: I want to make one thing clear: I’m not afraid of @realDonaldTrump’s lies, fear-mongering, or paranoia. Tune in to my #CNNTownhall tonight at 10pm ET (9pm CT) to hear how I plan to restore the American people’s faith in their government.

name: Julián Castro
text: Just touched down in Washington, D.C. for my @CNN town hall tonight at 10pm ET/9pm CT. Make sure to tune in! #CastroTownhall

name: Julián Castro
text:
Watch the full live stream of our #PeopleFirstRally rally here: https://www.facebook.com/julianforthefuture/videos/344837462809040/ …

Thank you. /5

name: Julián Castro
text: Thank you Zenén Jaimes Pérez of @TXCivilRights for sharing the story of Mario, a man from Guatemala, who had to wait 3 weeks for a DNA test to be reunited with his 2-year-old daughter and prove he was telling the truth all along. #PeopleFirst /4

name: Julián Castro
text: Thank you Maria Victoria de la Cruz of @organizetexas who gave a passionate speech about Trump's dangerous rhetoric and how it affects immigrant families like hers. Watch in Spanish here. #SiSePuede #PeopleFirst /3

name: Julián Castro
text: Thank you, Jennifer Falcon, local activist, who reminded us that San Antonio is a city that opens her doors in the middle of the night to welcome hundreds of migrant families who have been dropped at our Greyhound station. #PeopleFirst /2

name: Julián Castro
text: Thank you to everyone who came out to our #PeopleFirst rally to stand up for immigrants and migrant families. Special thanks to our community leaders who shared their voice and their stories. /1

name: Julián Castro
text: We're here today to stand up for immigrants. We're here today to put #PeopleFirst. We're not going to treat migrants like criminals, we're going to treat them like human beings. I'm going to need your support to help make sure this is possible. Join us: http://bit.ly/JC4peoplefirst

name: Julián Castro
text:
We don't just believe in putting people first when it comes to immigration. We believe in putting people first when it comes to healthcare, jobs, education, and all aspects of our lives.
#PeopleFirst

name: Julián Castro
text:
It's time for the truth in this country. The truth is that migrant families coming here are people, not animals. The truth is that our country needs them. 

#PeopleFirst

name: Julián Castro
text: This president wants us to believe that we have to choose between a border that's secure and compassion. We need to start telling the truth about border cities -- they're some of the safest cities in our country. #PeopleFirst

name: Julián Castro
text: We're here today because we believe in #PeopleFirst. Because we believe in compassion over cruelty.

name: Julián Castro
text:
"Trump and his rhetoric are not welcome here." - Jennifer Falcon, #westside #satx activist

#PeopleFirstRally #PeopleFirst

name: Julián Castro
text: Thomas Jefferson High School's Mariachis -- thank you for your support! #ProudAlumni #PeopleFirst

name: Julián Castro
text:
Trump wants you to choose cruelty. I want you to choose compassion. My #PeopleFirst immigration plan offers a much needed shift toward humanity in our immigration system.

Hear more about it at our rally tonight, and at my @CNN town hall tomorrow night.

name: Julián Castro
text:
Join me tomorrow night for a @CNN Presidential Town Hall at 9pm CT / 10pm ET — tune in live or join one of #TeamJulián's watch parties throughout the country: http://bit.ly/MobilizeJC2020 

#OneNationOneDestiny #PeopleFirst

name: Julián Castro
text: San Antonio, like America, is made up of people who value what immigrants bring to our communities. Let's put an end to this era of cruelty that Trump has created—join me at 6pm tonight to stand for compassion: http://bit.ly/JCrallySA410

name: Julián Castro
text: My story is just like that of so many families in this country—a story of hope, hard work, and opportunity. As president, I will work to ensure the opportunities I had are available to every American, and that everyone has a chance to achieve their dreams. #OneNationOneDestiny

name: Julián Castro
text:

name: Julián Castro
text: Tune into @TheLastWord with @Lawrence tonight at 10pm ET / 9pm CT—I'll be discussing the Mueller report, the chaos in the Trump cabinet, and my #PeopleFirst immigration plan.

name: Julián Castro
text: My #PeopleFirst immigration policy explicitly called for an end to ‘remain in Mexico’ practices because they’re cruel, short-sighted, and counter to our values. Today’s ruling highlights something else we already knew: they’re illegal.

name: Julián Castro
text: In abandoning our position as a good faith partner in the Middle East peace process, the Trump admin has enabled reckless actions like this from Netanyahu. US support for a two-state solution is on the line in November 2020.

name: Julián Castro
text: This is serious. President Trump wants to install a DHS Secretary that will reinstate family separation and illegally end the asylum system. The Senate cannot confirm a replacement without assurances that they will not carry out these immoral and illegal policies.

name: Julián Castro
text:
Sec. Nielsen operationalized one of the cruelest immigration policies this nation has ever seen. 

When a nominee is named, I call on senators to vote against anyone who doesn’t commit to treating asylum seekers humanely—including refusing to separate children from their parents.

name: Julián Castro
text:
Join me for a #PeopleFirst rally this Wednesday at 6pm at Hemisfair Park, #SA. Trump is going to  be in town for a fundraiser, and we want to send a loud and clear message -- that we believe in compassion, not cruelty when it comes to immigrants. 

RSVP  http://bit.ly/saRally4PeopleFirst …

name: Julián Castro
text:
Sec. Nielsen has been a willing partner in the most cruel and short-sighted immigration agenda in decades. We must defeat Donald Trump and create a more compassionate and sensible immigration system that puts #PeopleFirst. 

Read about mine here:

name: Julián Castro

name: Julián Castro
text: They returned a few weeks later and, protected by a court order and the U.S. Army, made it to Montgomery. Because of their bravery, and that of countless others, the Voting Rights Act of 1965 was signed that same spring. #SelmaJubilee

name: Julián Castro
text: Nearly 54 years ago, 600 civil rights warriors attempted their first march from Selma to Montgomery for voting rights. They were not just turned back at the Edmund Pettus Bridge, they were viciously attacked by state and local police. But they were not beaten. #SelmaJubilee

name: Julián Castro
text: During my time in public service, I had the chance to visit over 40 states, which helped me understand the issues most important to the people I served. I want to do that again. Over the course of my campaign, I will visit every state in our nation to hear directly from you.

name: Julián Castro
text: As someone from a state that’s largely been ignored by presidential campaigns for most of the past four decades, I know how much it means for the people in every state to have a chance to be heard by the men and women seeking to become their President.

name: Julián Castro
text: I just left Chicago, 45 miles from Aurora, IL. I am praying for the victims and families. But we know, we do, that this doesn’t have to happen over and over. Don’t let the gun lobby write firearm policies that generate profit and accept mass murder. We must unite against it.
