name: Julián Castro
text: "The lesson I learned from my mother so many years ago in this community is that when we want to see change in our community, we don’t wait for it. We work for it."

name: Julián Castro
text: "My story wouldn’t be possible without the strong women who came before me and passed me the baton. Because of their hard work, I have the opportunity to stand here today."

name: Julián Castro
text: "Hoy en día, esta comunidad representa el futuro de Estados Unidos: diverso, de rápido crecimiento, optimista, un lugar donde personas de diferentes orígenes se han unido para crear algo verdaderamente especial."

name: Julián Castro
text: I am proud to call myself a son of San Antonio. Home is always San Antonio.

name: Julián Castro
text: "Today, this community represents America’s future—diverse, fast-growing, optimistic, a place where people of different backgrounds have come together to create something truly special."

name: Julián Castro
text: "This is a community built by Native Americans. Families who worked to serve our future."

name: Julián Castro
text: "Esta es una comunidad construida por inmigrantes, familias de México. Pero también de Alemania y otros países. Y también de Nativos Americanos"

name: Julián Castro
text: "This is a community built by immigrants—families from Mexico.  But also from Germany and other countries."

name: Julián Castro
text: "Esta es una comunidad como muchas otras comunidades en nuestro país.Una comunidad de buenas personas. Gente humilde Las personas que se presentan temprano al trabajo y se quedan tarde (muchas veces en más de un trabajo) para que puedan mantener a su familia."

name: Julián Castro
text: "This is a community of good people.  Humble people.  People who show up for work early and stay late—oftentimes at more than one job—so they can provide for their family."

name: Julián Castro
text: "Miren a su alrededor, no hay ni un candidato delantero a la presidencia que haya nacido aquí, pero siempre he creído que con grandes sueños y trabajo duro todo es posible."

name: Julián Castro
text: "Look around, there are no frontrunners born here but I've always believed that with big dreams and hard work anything is possible."

name: Julián Castro
text: "Esta mañana, tomé el autobús número 68 con mi hermano por la calle Guadalupe, como lo hacíamos tantas veces como niños. Y esta vez traje a mi hija Carina."

name: Julián Castro
text: "This morning, I rode the number 68 bus with my brother down Guadalupe Street as we did so many times as kids. Only this time I brought my daughter Carina with me."

name: Julián Castro
text: "Es donde ella creció, donde trabajó durante años como sirvienta, cocinera y niñera mientras criaba a mi madre como madre soltera."

name: John Delaney
text: 8/8 But across time, if we would have invested the Social Security Trust fund assets better, we could now be in a position of increasing social security benefits.  It's another example of the average American getting a bad deal.

name: John Delaney
text: 7/8 Just to be clear, I'm not for privatizing social security. Your social security benefits should not go down because the stock marekt went down.

name: John Delaney
text: 6/8 Making matters worse, when after the recession we cut interest rates. This made the stock market go up and the rate on the social security trust fund go down.

name: John Delaney
text: 5/8 Thing about it this way. Rich people invest their savings in retirement accounts in the stock market. Most Americans, who don't have excess savings, only have social security, which is invested in Treasuries The stock market goes up faster than returns on Treasuries.

name: John Delaney
text: 4/8 In many ways the largest asset each average American owns is their right to social security, which they create by paying into with their wages. It's a great program but doesn't it seem unfair that we don't invest these contributions for a higher rate of return?

name: John Delaney
text: 3/8 But we don't do that. We invest them at Treasury Bond rates. The data is overwhelmingly clear, if you invest in the market you earn much higher rates across the long term then if you invest in Treasury Bonds

name: John Delaney
text: 2/8 The returns on these assets effect the overall solvency of social security. The lower the returns, the more pressure on the program. If this were a pension fund, the managers of the fund would invest these assets in the market to ensure higher long term returns.

name: John Delaney
text: 1/8 To elaborate on my prior post. Social Security should not be privatized but we should do the right thing for the beneficiaries. Currently the Social Security Trust Fund has $2.8 Billion of assets all invested at treasury bond yields.

name: John Delaney
text: This is a scandal. I am NOT for privatizing social security but the notion that we don't invest the trust fund assets in the market - and instead invest at treasury bond rates - fundamentally hurts average Americans.

text: I will end the approximately $5 billion in fossil fuel subsidies annually and use that funding to promote NET through a reverse auction program in which companies that can capture and store atmospheric carbon for the lowest cost get first access to government subsidies.

name: John Delaney
text: While we have 24 x 7 political coverage that doesn't mean all of life is politics (and it shouldnt be!). There is community, friends, relationships, hobbies, activities, health, fellowship, charity, nature, work, creative endeavors, and - most importantly - family, faith and love

name: John Delaney
text: Loneliness among young people is reaching epidemic level and many attribute this to social media, which also drives isolation, anxiety and anger in addictive ways. My (voluntary) national service program for young people will help in this area.

name: John Delaney
text: Dr. King had a dream & vision for this country that was unparalleled. The movement he & many other brave pioneers started was for decency, equality, and justice—things we need much more of today. Please join me in remembering the great legacy of Dr. Martin Luther King Jr. #MLK51

name: John Delaney
text: "I promise to work every day to give whatever gifts God’s given me, and whatever power I have as President, to ensure that every single American, regardless of the circumstances of their birth, or the color of their skin, has the same opportunities I had." #NANCONV19 @TheRevAl

name: John Delaney
text: “The 1st thing I promise is to listen, learn, and engage with your community. The 2nd thing I promise to do as your President is to never let a decision about domestic economic policy in the USA be made without your voices being in the room.” #NANCONV19 @NationalAction @TheRevAl

name: John Delaney
text: "I swear to never lie to you. I can never understand or fully comprehend what it means to be black in the United States of America. And I certainly don’t pretend to understand what it means to be black in the era of Trump.” #NANCONV19 @NationalAction @TheRevAl

#NANCONV2019

name: John Delaney
text: We need to close the racial wealth gap, the education gap, the health care gap. My Commitment to Black America is to fight every day for a more just America.

name: John Delaney
text: We need to make sure that the American Dream is available to everyone. Millions of African Americans haven’t received a fair shot and have had to face an economic and criminal justice system that is unjust, unfair and often racist.

name: John Delaney

name: John Delaney
text: How do you deal with Trump? Simple... You stand strong in the face of his aggression, and you call him out on his lies.

name: John Delaney
text: People invested in me to get me where I am today and then I made it my life's work to invest in others as an entrepreneur, as a Congressman, and now hopefully, as the next President. A big part of that means investing in those communities that have been left behind.

name: John Delaney
text: Closing our southern border is a political stunt that will have a devastating impact on our own economy.

name: John Delaney
text: 51 years ago today, #MLK gave this speech at Mason Temple in Memphis, Tennessee. Today, we honor his legacy by continuing the fight for #socialjustice and #equality on both a personal and political level.

name: John Delaney
text: I promise the American people the truth, for a change. If we aren't honest about our problems, there's no way we can arrive at the solutions. #BelieveinSomethingBetter #FocusontheFuture #TheTruthForaChange

name: John Delaney
text: If Trump wanted to help rural America now he would reenter the TPP.

name: John Delaney
text: We have to start thinking about politics differently and until we do that nothing will change. We have to start valuing what gets done, not what gets said. The point of government is to do thing to help people, not use it as a platform for talking points or entertainment.

name: John Delaney
text: #EqualPayDay is the day that represents how far women must work into the year to catch up to what their male counterparts earned the previous year. We need equal pay for equal work now. [source: https://www.axios.com/equal-pay-day-chart-fdcc9242-0de6-479 ……]

name: John Delaney
text: It's shameful the Republican-controlled Congress allowed the Act to expire on 12/21/18. Congress must pass a reauthorization that maintains current protections for survivors. #SAAPM #VAWA

name: John Delaney
text: It's Sexual Assault Awareness & Prevention Month & way past time for Congress to reauthorize the Violence Against Women Act. #SAAPM #VAWA

name: John Delaney

name: John Delaney
text: Thank a veteran, a member of our military, a teacher, a member of law enforcement, a first responder, or anyone else engaged in a job oriented towards serving the common good.

name: John Delaney
text: Men and women deserve equal pay for equal work, period. The pay gap continues to cost women $840 billion per year. We need a leader committed to ensuring fairness and equal pay. #EqualPayDay

name: John Delaney
text: As I've traveled around this country, and listened to voters, they want elected leaders to focus on their job, their pay, their healthcare, their kid's education, opportunities for their kids and national security. They want solutions to the issues that matter to them!

name: John Delaney
text: We look for villains in our politics when we should be looking for solutions. I believe in the politics of progress, which involves working together to get things done.

name: John Delaney
text: The 2020 election should be as much about decency, honesty and functioning politics as it is about policy.  Our next president needs to have big new ideas but they also have to be honest, moral and have a plan to get things done.

name: John Delaney
text: This is sad & a problem for our democracy. Local papers are central to a community and focus residents on things that really matter to them. Absent local papers people are left with social media (not journalism) and national media, which focuses on DC.

name: John Delaney
text: Nothing happens unless someone invests. We need real policies that encourage people to invest in other people, in communities and in businesses.

name: John Delaney
text: Sexual assault is all too common and for too long we swept it under the rug. We need to stand with survivors and do more to prevent sexual assault and violence.

name: John Delaney
text: The Trump administration’s failure to properly vet staff security clearances is just another example of the incompetence of the White House.

name: John Delaney
text: I'm not afraid to go on Fox News. I went on @TeamCavuto this weekend to talk about what we need to do to secure our southern border. Our #immigration system is broken and to fix it, we need to get at the root causes.

name: John Delaney
text: If a drug costs $100 in the US but only an average of $40 in similarly developed nations, the pharmaceutical co. would owe a tax equal to the difference of $60. The point of this tax is to lower costs in the US and raise them in other parts of the world.

name: John Delaney
text: My plan is designed to specifically address the huge discrepancies in drug prices and the much higher prices paid by American patients. Humira, for example, costs an average of $822 in Switzerland and $2,669 in the United States.

name: John Delaney
text: The American people are paying too much for #prescriptiondrugs, period. This is a major #healthcare and #economic issue and we have an obligation to act. #Drug companies allow citizens of other wealthy nations to free ride on the backs of US citizens.

name: John Delaney
text: "That's why I'm running for president. I want to be the person that brings this terribly divided nation back together."

name: John Delaney
text: "Give justice to the weak and the fatherless; maintain the right of the afflicted and the destitute. Rescue the weak and the needy" Something to think about from Psalm 82

name: John Delaney
text: I am very sorry to have missed the event today, but I want to take this opportunity to reaffirm my commitment to ensuring equal rights for everyone, across the country. You can read more about my LGBTQ policy initiatives here: https://www.johndelaney.com/issues/lgbtq/

name: John Delaney
text: The @iowasafeschools Governor's Conference does incredibly important work in preventing bullying and harassment of LGBTQ students, as well as creating leadership opportunities for them to explore. #iagovlgbtq #iowasafeschools

name: John Delaney
text: The US went from a collection of small farms & villages 200+ years ago to a $20+ Trillion economy full of innovation and prosperity. Our economic engine saved the world in WW2 & created the largest middle class. Our model works - we should not throw it out - we should improve it

name: John Delaney
text: Trump-style nationalism is the wrong answer to any question we could ask ourselves and it is not reflective of our ideals, counterproductive to our economic and security interests, and ultimately not patriotic.

name: John Delaney
text: A great event yesterday

name: John Delaney
text: Capitalism is one of the things that made this country great and it will continue to make it great but we need to make it benefit more people. The job of the next President is to make capitalism more just and inclusive.

name: John Delaney
text: Packed house today at Merge a terrific incubator in Iowa City. As a former entrepreneur and self described "compassionate capitalist" it was a great location to have a meet and greet.

name: John Delaney
text: Talking issues and eating a delicious pork tenderloin sandwich at the world famous Hamburg Inn in Iowa City!

name: John Delaney

name: John Delaney
text: Great office opening in Dubuque Iowa. Packed house and great discussion about healthcare, national service, social justice, and serving for the right reason! Anytime I get to talk about my amazing wife April, my family, and my roots in working class Jersey is also a bonus.

name: John Delaney
text:
Many brave Trans Americans live openly & authentically but many more remain in the shadows. We need a leader who supports & empowers the trans community; not ignores & disenfranchises them.
Please join me in celebrating International Transgender Day of Visibility. #TDOV

name: John Delaney
text: To be honest, changing the Electoral College requires a constitutional amendment and will likely never happen and it DEFINITELY will never happen by 2020.   Talking about it sends a message to rural America that we don't value their vote.  I say we try to win rural America!

name: John Delaney
text: Rural America sends young people off into our military at a rate twice as high as other parts of the country. Rural Americans are deeply patriotic.

name: John Delaney
text: If we (Dems) make this election about throwing out the entire economic model of the country we will lose. If we make this election about solving real problems facing hardworking Americans, building a better future for their kids & restoring honesty to our politics, we will win.

name: John Delaney
text: Finishing up my 26th trip to Iowa today with our 7th and 8th office opening. This trip focused on rural Iowa/rural America, an area that the Democratic Party has forgotten about. I'm committed to changing that.  My agenda is centered on hard working families.

name: John Delaney
text: It's important for the Democratic Party to remember that we have to put the needs of the hard working middle class families front and center in our agenda. If we are not fighting for them, we are not doing our job.

name: John Delaney
text: A few days ago someone called me a "Compassionate Capitalist" - I like the ring of that.

name: John Delaney
text: Listening to Dylan's Knockin' On Heaven's Door and remembering how great a song it is.

name: John Delaney
text: Starting the day in Cedar Falls Iowa in dad's pickup. This songs starts most basketball games - makes us feel like we should be running out on the court!

name: John Delaney
text: "For I was hungry and you gave me something to eat, I was thirsty and you gave me something to drink, I was a stranger and you invited me in, I needed clothes and you clothed me, I was sick and you looked after me...." A good reminder from the Gospel of Mathew.

text: Read about my new plan here:

name: John Delaney
text: Everyone deserves an equal shot at a good job and steady income no matter where they live. Today I'm announcing my Heartland Fair Deal plan to revitalize rural America by stimulating economic growth, improving infrastructure, prioritizing rural health, and supporting agriculture.

name: John Delaney

name: John Delaney
text: Great team dinner @hopandgrind in NH. I just cast the deciding vote on "No" pineapple on pizza. Not even a close call.

name: John Delaney
text: Our #taxsystem is fundamentally #unfair. Right now people who are making massive amounts of money off investments are being taxed at a much lower rate than people who earn their money working. We have to change this.

name: John Delaney
text: We should be proud and excited to live in a country where disagreement is not only allowed but encouraged. The battle of ideas is what makes this country free but we have to remember we are all striving toward a common goal.

name: John Delaney
text: It's 2019. Americans shouldn't have to choose between the #medicine they need and putting food on the table. We must elect leaders who will stop talking about fixing the problem and actually do something.

name: John Delaney
text: We need to stem the flow of #opioids into communities and make sure patients have access to alternative pain management, and my campaign is focused on addressing this crisis. Thank you for having me.

name: John Delaney
text: I appreciated the opportunity to hear from community leaders & experts today at HOPE for New Hampshire Recovery about the opioid epidemic, which has ravaged this country.

name: John Delaney
text: Because of the #AffordableCareAct, millions of people have #healthcare coverage.  Trump's plan to repeal it would be a disaster for the country and that's why it's so important we fight back. #ACA

name: John Delaney
text: I had a great convo with @NHPRExchange this morning about universal #healthcare, making our #tax system fairer, and the Mueller report. Check it out here:

name: John Delaney
text: We need to end the stigma around mental health and make sure that those who are suffering know that they are not alone.

name: John Delaney
text: As a country, we have to do so much more to treat #mentalhealth. Last year, I introduced #bipartisan legislation, the Suicide Prevention Analytics Act, to give medical professionals access to more real-time data so that they can help those at risk of self-harm.

name: John Delaney
text: This chart says all you need to know about Trump's ability to follow through on his promises. [source: https://nyti.ms/2V4Zkeh ]

name: John Delaney
text: The roadmap for the White House 2020 was written by the Democratic House members that flipped Republican seats. By and large they were moderates, they focused on solutions, they did not embrace unworkable (or unpaid for) polices and they didn't talk about Trump.

name: John Delaney
text: For too long, opportunity in this country has been concentrated in just a few areas. Join me on Saturday at ~2 PM CT to hear about my vision for the future.

name: John Delaney
text: Everyone should have #healthcare as a right. It's good policy and also smart economics. @AmericaNewsroom @BillHemmer #nine2noon

name: John Delaney
text: Public service is about serving the interests of Americans, not big interest groups and corporations. #NoPACs #NoSpecialInterests #NoCorporations https://secure.actblue.com/donate/nopacsnocorporations …

name: John Delaney
text: #Healthcare has become a heavily partisan and politicized issue, but let’s not forget to take a step back and consider all of the positive things that the #ACA has done for this country, and all of the people it has helped.

name: John Delaney
text: Trump's insistence on taking #healthcare away from Americans challenges not only our morals & ethical convictions but our entire system. The administration can't pick & choose which laws it wants to defend. Share if you believe health care is a right.

name: John Delaney
text: If women & men do the same job, they should get the same pay. That’s why I support the #PaycheckFairness Act. RETWEET if you do too! @rosadelauro

name: John Delaney
text: I was a very good entrepreneur because I always lived by the motto that "strategy is easy and execution is really hard."  The same is true with governing. It is easy to say you want to do big things (don't we all!) but what is really hard is showing how you can get them done.

name: John Delaney
text: Our Presidential campaign is funded entirely by individual donors and investments my wife and I make in our effort to serve the public. No corporate PAC money is funding the Delaney for President Campaign.

name: John Delaney
text: Good advice from President Obama. We need big ideas, but we also have to tell the American people how we are going to pay for them. Or they can never become reality.

name: John Delaney
text: "If you take a few minutes to listen to him, you will instantly get that he has given the issues facing our nation a great deal of thought, and he'll challenge you to consider approaches to these issues that we aren’t hearing." Thanks, @DeanObeidallah

name: John Delaney
text: The outrageous prices of pharmaceutical drugs in this country prevent people from getting the medical treatment they need, or leave them massively in debt. This issue needs to be resolved now. That’s why I have a plan to fix it. Read my proposal here: https://www.johndelaney.com/2019/03/26/delaney-announces-plan-to-lower-prescription-drug-prices/ …

name: John Delaney
text: I support the idea that the #pharmaceutical industry needs a strong profit incentive to continue to invest in the R&D of innovative new treatments. But US patients should not continue to subsidize those costs for the benefit of citizens in other developed, wealthy countries.

name: John Delaney
text: Americans are paying too much for #prescriptiondrugs, period. This is a major #healthcare and economic issue, and we have an obligation to act. The drug companies allow the citizens of other wealthy nations to free ride on the backs of US citizens.

name: John Delaney
text: The results of the Mueller Investigation + a reasonably good economy means we need a centrist who can go toe-to toe with Trump on jobs.  As a blue collar kid who went on to found two NYSE companies and then serve in Congress, I've got that resume.

name: John Delaney
text: Instead of continuing to attack the ACA, the American people deserve a White House that is actually committed to improving the ACA and establishing coverage for all. This White House has never laid out a plan to improve people’s health care.

name: John Delaney
text: This Administration has consistently acted to undermine the basic health care security of the American people and this latest legal maneuvering is another example of their cruel policies. Real people will suffer if this legal fantasy became a reality.

name: John Delaney
text: This is the reason I've got a plan for negative emissions technology (or direct air capture). We will not be able to stop global warming unless we advance the technologies and machines that take carbon out of the atmosphere.

name: John Delaney
text: I believe in capitalism. We need free markets combined with strong social programs and appropriate regulations. According to this breakdown from Yahoo Finance, I'm the strongest capitalist in the field.

name: John Delaney
text: What the country needs in its next leader and what the Democratic Party needs in its nominee are the same thing: a person that can unite us, find common ground, restore decency to politics & get things done. Time to turn the page on partisanship and get on with problem solving.

name: John Delaney
text: The Mueller investigation is over and the report should be made public. Period. Time to focus on what the Democratic Party can do for the American people. Now more than ever, our nominee must be a problem solver that can bring the country together around some new ideas.

name: John Delaney
text: We need a new national service program to bring the country together.

name: John Delaney
text: If you or someone you know may be at risk of suicide, call the @afspnational National Suicide Prevention Lifeline 1-800-273-8255 or send a text to 741741

name: John Delaney
text: These are tragedies that no Americans should have to face, yet every year we hear similar stories. We need stronger gun laws that make our schools safe and a more robust mental health system to offer the help and support survivors need.

name: John Delaney
text: My family and I are keeping the Marjory Stoneman Douglas survivors and Parkland families in our thoughts and prayers as more precious lives have been claimed following last year's horrific school shooting.

name: John Delaney
text: Will miss being at AIPAC today; always attended when I was in Congress & look forward to speaking next year as a 2020 candidate. Israel is under unfair attack with the BDS movement & other efforts to undermine its legitimacy. Dems should stand w/ Israel & against antisemitism

name: John Delaney
text:
Obstruction was obviously a 
"close call" - another reasons we need to see the report.

name: John Delaney
text: Not releasing the report sends a message to Russia that there will not be full transparency with the American people as it relates to their efforts to interfere with our election.

name: John Delaney
text: The fact that the AG Barr - the highest ranking law enforcement official in the country - stated that after a full investigation the President could not be exonerated from obstructing justice is chilling and demands that the full details of the Report be released.

name: John Delaney
text: The voice and will of the American people were influenced by a foreign adversary - the American people deserve to see the full report. Period.

name: John Delaney
text: Here is your challenge @JasonFish58 - 10 deadlifts with 225lbs.

name: John Delaney
text: My friend Jason challenged me to do 10 proper pull ups. Here you go. Easy! Good start to the morning.

name: John Delaney
text: Right now your tax dollars are subsidizing fossil fuels, making climate change worse. Read my plan to end those subsidies and invest instead in negative emissions technologies that can actually take carbon out of the atmosphere.

name: John Delaney
text: The Mueller investigation is over, we need to see the report, but we also have to start tackling the issues that really matter to the day-to-day lives of the American people.  Our job is to be problem solvers not pundits.

name: John Delaney
text: Mueller did all the hard work. Barr simply has to send a message to: "The American People" distribution list and attach "The Mueller Report" as a PDF attachment.

name: John Delaney
text: I want people to start a business, volunteer in their community, create a job, help someone, support a cause, or give back anyway they can. We all need to step up and serve in a REAL and tangible way at this moment in time.

name: John Delaney
text: Quick interview with local press before I speak to about 100 good folks Twin Falls, Idaho.  Dems have to campaign everywhere. We are going to all 50 states.

name: John Delaney
text: The Mueller Report should be made public, the American people should know what Mr. Mueller found, they should pass judgment on its findings, and our elected officials should listen to the American people.

name: John Delaney
text: We need a White House that follows the facts on climate change and wants to solve the problem instead of ignoring it. We need to 1) implement a carbon tax and 2) invest in negative emissions technology.

name: John Delaney
text:

name: John Delaney
text: This week I went on Bloomberg to discuss the economy, taxes and my plan for universal health care. Check out the full clip here:

name: John Delaney
text: In Congress, I was proud to vote dozens of times to defend the ACA. Happy Birthday Obamacare!

name: John Delaney
text: In 2010, President Obama signed the Affordable Care Act into law. The ACA is one of the most consequential pieces of legislation in our history, leading to millions of Americans having health care coverage, including people with preexisting conditions.

name: John Delaney
text: My national service program works by having HS grads sign up for military or community service or infrastructure (rebuilding parks etc) service. They get assigned a location and are provided housing and a stipend. They get either a skills certificate or grants for college at end.

name: John Delaney
text: A year of national service - doing military or community service or rebuilding our parks - is exactly what we need. It would unify our nation, help young people get skills, create pathways for more affordable education, and provide mixing by ideology and geography for nextgen.

name: John Delaney
text: We all should agree that a year of national service for our high school graduates would be good for our country. That's why I'm the person running for President on this issue. It won't be mandatory but it will be so exciting that everyone will want to do it.

name: John Delaney
text: While our attention shifts to the full release of the Mueller Report, we should thank Mr. Mueller, for his work as special counsel and his service to our country. He is a decorated former Marine, dedicated public servant and has conducted his work with dignity and without leaks.

name: John Delaney
text: You, the American people, paid for the Mueller Report and you, the American people, deserve to see it. Make your voices heard!

name: John Delaney
text: The patriotic action for the Attorney General is to release the entire Mueller Report to the American people. We paid for it and this moment requires transparency.

name: John Delaney
text: I am continually inspired by this new generation who stand up and fight for what they believe in. At 12, Greta Thunberg has already become a global leader in the fight against climate change. We should all be inspired by her eloquence and determination in the face of this crisis.

name: John Delaney
text: If you've heard about the exciting new Negative Emissions Technology that pulls CO2 from the atmosphere, you’re probably wondering why nobody's discussing it. But that changes today. I’m not only talking about it, I’m ready to invest. Read my plan here:

name: John Delaney
text: Elected officials shouldn't be choosing their constituents. Constituents should be choosing their elected officials. It's really pretty simple. That's why I authored legislation to end congressional gerrymandering.

name: John Delaney
text: Memo to President Trump: There are at least two things Wite-Out doesn't work on: computer screens and the Constitution.

name: John Delaney
text: 2020 will be an old fashioned persuasion election. The winner of the center will win the Presidency.  Trump will turn out his supporters and Dems will turn out in big numbers because we will be organized and motivated to beat Trump. Win the center, win the White House.

name: John Delaney
text: Rather than focus on changing Electoral College (VERY hard to change and 100% likely to be the way the 2020 winner is picked), let's focus on a candidate and a platform that can win independents (FASTEST growing party) and thereby win in 2020. Common sense

Congresswoman Tulsi Gabbard ─ Build, Don't Bomb: A New American Foreign Policy

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: All people deserve clean air, clean water, & the promise of a bright future. My OFF Act will end our addiction to fossil fuels & transition the country to a 100% clean energy economy—laying a just and economic pathway toward a cleaner, more secure future for all. Happy #EarthDay

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: Corrupt powerful politicians need to be held accountable for their lies and complicity when they poisoned the drinking water of the American people. Without clean water and air, there is no life. #WaterIsLife

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: Congratulations!!! What an incredible game. We are so proud.  #HawaiiMVB #GoBows

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: My heart is with Sri Lanka on this #EasterSunday, w/hundreds killed & wounded in a horrific attack as they gathered in prayer. On a day devoted to love & peace, may we remember Jesus Christ’s message of love - for God & for each other - as we commit to defeating hate with love.

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: We're live in Exeter for a Town Hall! Come join the live stream:

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: Neocons and Trump Admin distort intelligence in effort to lay groundwork for new regime change war. We must never forget the lies that led to our disastrous invasion of Iraq. Stop history from repeating itself.

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: Saudi Arabia is the world’s #1 exporter of violent jihadi extremism that persecutes & oppresses women, all other religions including all other forms of Islam, atheists & the LGBT community. We must end our alliance with this theocratic dictatorship.

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: Legalizing marijuana is a basic question of fairness & freedom for the American people. We must legalize marijuana, expunge the records of those w/ marijuana possession charges/convictions & hold Big Pharma accountable for the opioid epidemic that has killed thousands #420

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: If our leaders & media want to protect our elections, not just score political pts, first & most important thing we must do is institute b/up paper ballots by passing my Securing America’s Elections Act so no one can manipulate our votes & hack our elections #MuellerReport

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: As president, I will end federal subsidies for oil companies that are destroying our air, land & water & invest that money in supporting renewable energy to ensure our energy & food security and build a brighter future for all.

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: #BarrCoverUp. The most dangerous coverup is that US voting machines are vulnerable to hackers. If we lose faith in election results, democracy crumbles. The Justice Dept should be focused on instituting paper ballot backups, per my Securing America's Elections Act. #MuellerReport

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: There are bad people in the world, but we can't be the world’s policeman. Regime change wars cost millions of lives, strengthen terrorist orgs, undermine our national security & waste precious money that should be used to improve the lives of the American people. #Tulsi2020

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: By vetoing War Powers Act, Trump again proves he’s the servant of Saudi Arabia—the theocratic dictatorship spending billions spreading the most extreme & intolerant form of Islam around the world, supporting al-Qaeda & other jihadists, & waging genocidal war in Yemen w/ US help

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: Trump is surrounded by neocon war hawks who supported regime change wars in Libya, Iraq, Syria...now they’re calling for overthrow the govts of Venezuela and Iran, and the result will be the same: thousands of lives lost, trillions wasted, more suffering. http://tulsi.to/warhawks

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: Notre Dame was constructed to remind us of the beauty and greatness of God, and to have a place to gather in that remembrance. Today, we mourn with France, and Catholics around the world. Tomorrow, we rebuild.

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: Another #TaxDay, another year corporations like Amazon pay $0 taxes. The rich & powerful pay to play & write laws so they don't pay taxes. Trump has made this corruption even worse, turning the swamp into a cesspool.  As President, I will change this and put #PeopleBeforeProfits.

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: This is so heartbreaking and such an incredible loss.

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: I started practicing martial arts as a kid and trained Capoeira for many years - an art that originated with slaves in Brazil as a form of resistance. This weekend, I stopped in at @capoeirabatuque in LA and got in some training and play time! #capoeira #TULSI2020

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: My flight delayed from LAX for hours because Chicago is covered in snow. Winter is coming. In April. Are you ready? #GameofThrones

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: Trump’s criticism of Rep #IlhanOmar is complete hypocrisy. Trump says “WE WILL NEVER FORGET (9/11)!” Yet it is Trump who’s been acting as al-Qaeda’s big brother and protector in Syria, and turned America into the prostitute of AQ's biggest supporter—the Saudis #WeWillNeverForget

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: What a historic comeback! Congratulations, Tiger.  #TheMasters

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: Trump is shamelessly trying to foment religious bigotry against ⁦#IlhanOmar & all Muslims, based on the horrendous actions of a few individuals claiming to be Muslim. This is the very definition of religious bigotry & Trump is fomenting it for political gain. Dangerous & sad

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: I met a mom whose son was born with a heart defect. The fear of being unable to afford sudden, major heart surgery has shaped this family’s life in many tragic ways. I promised this mom that I’ll fight for her son and all Americans to make Medicare for All who want it a reality.

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: Insulin is overpriced and it’s killing Americans. Between 1997 and 2017, Big Pharma increased the price of insulin over 1,000%. People are dying because they can’t afford insulin. #PeopleBeforeProfits

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: The foreign policy establishment and military industrial complex wage one regime change war after another under the guise of humanitarianism—wars that INCREASE the people’s suffering and devastation in those countries, and strengthen jihadists like al-Qaeda.

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: Assange Arrest: The message is clear. To journalists and all Americans, if you try to take away our power, you will pay a high price.

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: The purpose of arresting #JulianAssange is to send a message to the people, especially journalists, to be quiet and don’t get out of line. If we, the people, allow the government to control us through fear, we are no longer free, we are no longer America.

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: The arrest of #JulianAssange is meant to send a message to all Americans and journalists: be quiet, behave, toe the line. Or you will pay the price.

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: Hemp played a vital role in the American economy through the early 1900’s until it was replaced w/ fossil fuel products. Versatile & environmentally friendly, it represents great opportunity for small farmers. It’s time to bring it back!

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: Congress passed legislation to end US support of Saudi genocidal war in Yemen that has killed thousands, caused famine, & cholera epidemic. The bill is on Trump’s desk awaiting signature or veto. Join our petition urging Trump to sign this bill to law — http://tulsi.to/yemen

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: Thank you! I’m extremely grateful that over 65,000 of you have now donated to our campaign, ensuring our voice will be heard in the upcoming debates. For a small campaign that doesn’t accept PAC money, I knew we had to rely fully on the power of the people. Aloha & Mahalo!

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: Protecting #NetNeutrality is about protecting freedom of speech online. We passed our bill today to reinstate net neutrality — to stop corporations from controlling what we can read, watch or listen to. RT if you agree and tell the Senate to pass the #SavetheInternetAct now.

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: On #NationalSiblingsDay I pay tribute to this one ... my best friend and partner in all things for as long as I can remember (even when she was a little kid punk). Can’t imagine life without her! Love you, sister. @vrin_davan

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: Happy anniversary, my love.  This seems like just yesterday. I love you so much and am so grateful for you! #love @abewilliamsdp

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: Unfortunately, we don’t have healthcare in this country—we have sick care. We’ve created a massive for-profit entity incentivized to keep people sick and on drugs. As president, I will work to build a healthcare system incentivized to increase health and prevent & heal disease

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: Netanyahu and Saudi Arabia want to drag the United States into war with Iran, and Trump is submitting to their wishes. The cost in money and lives will be catastrophic.

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: Drivers license renewed! And it’s not even noon yet. Thanks to the hard working people at the Kapolei DMV who take care of huge lines of people every day. Back to DC tonight!

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: I've always supported Israel's right to exist—especially after visiting Auschwitz in 2005. That's why I'm so concerned with Netanyahu's aggressive annexation policies which will simply stoke the flames of resentment and conflict. Bad for Israel, US, Palestinians, and region.

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: Trump’s effort to rollback regulations means that Big Ag now gets to inspect its own pork - & they decided to stop testing for E. coli. This endangers everyone, even if you don’t eat pork, because bacteria can easily spread on shared surfaces. This is swamp politics at its worst.

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: At last, we have passed historic legislation in the House of Representatives to end the US’ unconstitutional support of Saudi-led genocidal war in Yemen, which is killing tens of thousands & starving millions. This legislation is now w/ @realDonaldTrump for signature or veto.

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: While Tulsi is in Guard duty this weekend, we’re posting stories of people putting #ServiceAboveSelf in their daily lives, like these two friends who teamed up to overcome their disabilities and plant 10,000 trees around their village -TULSI2020

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text:
While Tulsi is in Guard duty this weekend, we’re posting stories of people putting #ServiceAboveSelf in their daily lives, like Dr. Semmler who has chosen to live modestly so that he can give back to his community as much as possible -TULSI2020
https://www.nvcc.edu/news/press-releases/2018/semmler-donation.html …

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: While Tulsi is in Guard duty this weekend, we’re posting stories of people putting #ServiceAboveSelf in their daily lives, like MMA fighter Dustin Poirie raising money to build a playground for disabled kids in his old neighborhood -TULSI2020

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: While Tulsi is in Guard duty this weekend, we’re posting stories of people putting #ServiceAboveSelf in their daily lives, like this powerful story of Gettysburg

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text:
63,434! We’re so close! Tulsi is in National Guard duty this weekend - let’s surprise her by reaching 65,000 by the time she gets out. - TULSI2020 
Link to donate: http://tulsi.to/chip-in

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: LA Memorial Coliseum honors those who fought & died in WWI. The proposal to rename it after United Airlines dishonors those who put their lives on the line for our country. I support the veterans mobilizing to fight the name change #VeteransBeforeProfits https://www.tulsi2020.com/press/2019-04-05-tulsi-gabbard-calls-veterans-oppose-renaming-iconic-world-war-i-monument-united …

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: Neocons Bolton, Pence & Abrams miscalculated at every step in attempting regime change in Venezuela. The Venezuelan people have seen the devastating impacts of US intervention in Latin America for decades - they need real solutions, not political theater.

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: Trump is for socialism when it comes to taxpayers underwriting military contractors and arms manufacturers. The same money would create more jobs used for rebuilding our country’s infrastructure and green economy, and it would be better for humanity.

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: Coral reefs are a vital ecosystem on the front lines of climate change's devastating impacts. We can’t afford to sit back & watch them die. My OFF Act will ensure a 100% transition from fossil fuels to clean and renewable energy to achieve #ClimateJustice

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: If we treat people like animals in prison & force them to do dehumanizing things to survive that environment, we perpetuate violent behavior & increase recidivism. Goal of our prisons should be to help ppl become more caring, develop respect & compassion

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: 1 in 3 women in this country are subjected to domestic violence. I was proud to cast my vote today to pass the Violence Against Women Reauthorization Act to close gaps in the law and provide resources to help survivors heal and rebuild their lives. #VAWA19 #NOMORE

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: Finally. Today we passed legislation to end US support for Saudi Arabia’s genocidal war in Yemen that has killed tens of thousands and caused the worst humanitarian crisis in the world.

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: Our infrastructure is crumbling. We need leadership that puts #PeopleBeforeProfits, to end regime change wars, the new Cold War and arms race, and keep the money in people’s pockets and/or rebuild our country’s bridges, airports, roads, sewer lines, etc.

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: Oil lobbyists have “unprecedented access” to Trump’s administration—meanwhile Pence/Bolton continue their crusade for regime change in Venezuela, the world’s richest oil reserves. The height of swamp politics. #PeopleBeforeProfits #ServiceBeforeSelf

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: We must stand united against neocons/neolibs who drag us from one regime change war to the next, exacerbating the New Cold War, bringing us closer to nuclear war. We must redirect our precious resources to rebuilding our infrastructure, Medicare for All, a green economy, & more.

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: 61,029! Our success isn't driven by mainstream media coverage, celebrity influencers or establishment networks. It's driven by you. Thank you. #Tulsi2020 http://tulsi.to/chip-in

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text:
We must fight for #EqualPayForEqualWork
#Tulsi2020 #ServiceBeforeSelf

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: Central America asylum seekers pose serious challenge—our response must enforce border security, be compassionate, & work to solve root problem which has been exacerbated by decades of US exploitation & regime change wars. Closing border not the solution

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: TV talking heads love trying to goad Trump into going to war w/ Russia. Here’s just one example: @FareedZakaria is trying to get Trump to prove he's not guilty of appeasement by going to war with Russia over Venezuela.

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: [4/4] …that means sacrificing the wellbeing of our country, then that’s the price he’s willing to pay. A true leader is willing to make personal sacrifice for the wellbeing of our country. Trump is willing to sacrifice the wellbeing of our country for his own selfish interests.

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: [3/4] Trump’s closing the border isn’t because he cares more about security than trade, as he falsely claims, but rather it’s because he wants to prove to his base of supporters that he is tough on immigration. But all he cares about is his political interests, and if…

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: [2/4] …and advanced nuclear tech to Saudi Arabia, the world’s biggest spreader and propagator of terrorist/radical jihadist ideology; selling F-35 fighter jets to Turkey, etc. These examples expose the lie.

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: [1/4] President Trump just said he might close the border even though it will be damaging to our economy, claiming that "safety & security is more important to me than trade.” Really? Selling hundreds of billions in arms sales…

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: Another 2,000 new donors have joined our campaign in the last 48 hours! We're so close... With your help, we can cross the threshold by the end of the week. http://tulsi.to/chip-in

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: Aloha to Hawai’i Army National Guard soldiers deploying to Afghanistan

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: A whale that washed up in Italy last week with 49 lbs of plastic in her stomach is the latest reminder that we must lead an international effort to ban single-use plastic items and clean up the estimated 150M metric tons of plastic garbage in our oceans.

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: We need a #PeaceDividend to take the trillions of dollars spent on regime change wars and the nuclear arms race and invest them to meet the needs of the American people. Otherwise, we can't even ensure our most vulnerable communities have clean water following a disaster. https://twitter.com/nowthisnews/status/1111717915328499713 …

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: Many of my sisters and brothers in the military who have been sexually assaulted keep it to themselves out of fear. As commander-in-chief, I will make sure that any servicemember who makes a sexual assault complaint will be taken seriously and protected. #Tulsi2020

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: We need to stop using immigrants as tokens in a political game & start talking solutions—funding to process asylum requests & targeted aid to address the decades of US intervention that contributed to the collapse of the countries they are fleeing.

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: I will be a president who puts the interests of our country—our whole country—before the interests of my political party. If something is good for our country, but not good for my party, I will choose our country. Every time. #PeopleBeforeProfits #CountryBeforeParty

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: President Trump’s recent decision to allow U.S. companies to sell Saudi Arabia nuclear technology is both mind-blowing and inexplicable. How does it serve our interests to help Saudi Arabia develop nuclear weapons?

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: 5,500 new donors joined our campaign in the last 48 hours! We are almost there. Will you help us reach the 65,000 we need to get on the debate stage? http://tulsi.to/chip-in

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text:
We have a big FEC fundraising deadline at midnight tonight - there is no better time to donate to our campaign than now. Will you help? 
Let’s show the power of our voices and the positive change we will make together. Contribute here by midnight: http://tulsi2020.com/donate

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: On #TransVisibilityDay let’s stand for equality for all Americans by ending the discrimination faced by LGBTQ individuals every day — take action and call on Congress to pass the Equality Act!

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: Purdue Pharma knowingly & aggressively pushed highly addictive drugs, hiding the truth about them & describing those caught in addiction as criminals who brought it on themselves. We must reject their lies for profit & this damaging view of addiction

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: My heart is with the people of Puna and all of our Hawaii Island ohana for continued strength and resilience as they continue to rebuild following Kilauea’s eruption.

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: As president, I will end federal subsidies for oil companies and invest that money in supporting renewable energy & renewable agriculture—industries that are vital to our future, address climate change, and are necessary for energy & food security.

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: More than 2,000 new donors since yesterday! We are finishing this quarter strong and I’m so grateful to all of you for being with me on this journey! http://tulsi2020.com/donate

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: We keep having problems with Twitter Live/Pscp.tv feed on Twitter, you can watch live at the Youtube link above or on Facebook! https://www.facebook.com/tulsigabbard  Thank you -Livestream team

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: Watch Tulsi LIVE on the road in L.A.: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=BBQoUWly1Eg … #TULSI2020 #TulsiGabbard #TulsiTV

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: Mind-blowing & inexplicable is Trump’s recent approval for US companies to sell nuclear technology to Saudi Arabia. Why it’s in our interest to help the world’s primary exporter of jihadist ideology and terrorism get nuclear weapons is a question we should demand Trump answer.

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: The people of Georgia deserve to know that Georgian elections can’t be hacked. My Securing America’s Elections Act will give every Georgian voter the confidence that their votes will count and not be tampered with.

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: UPDATE: due to high demand, we had to move to a bigger venue for our event tomorrow. See details below. If you’re in LA, come out and join us tomorrow at 11:00am! I’d love to see you there.  #TULSI2020

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: We are fighting for our future—by leading with strength and a message of love for humanity and our world. I'm asking you to donate for a future without one regime change war after another and an end to the new Cold War and nuclear arms race.

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: Sending my deepest aloha, respect, love and gratitude to our Vietnam Veterans who unfortunately bore the brunt of anger that so many had for political leaders who were responsible for the war. We honor you. Welcome home.   #VietnamWarVeteransDay

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: Tulsi is LIVE right now with Niko House on YouTube, tune in at 3pm PST for Jimmy Dore and 5:30pm with The Young Turks!

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: Turkey has proven time and again that they are a NATO ally in name only. Let’s be honest - Turkey continues to take actions that counter US interests and undermine our national security. Congress must act now & pass our bill to stop the sale of our F-35s to Turkey.

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: We must stand up against for-profit, private prisons and a criminal justice system that favors the rich and powerful and punishes the poor, locking up people who smoke marijuana and ignoring corps like Purdue Pharma responsible for thousands of opioid-related deaths. #Tulsi2020

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: .@KimIversenShow Happy birthday! Thank you so much! This is so kind of you. Look forward to seeing you tomorrow for your show! https://twitter.com/KimIversenShow/status/1111280667910791168 …

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: Mueller reported Trump did not collude with Russia to influence our elections. Now we must put aside partisan interests, move forward, and work to unite our country to deal with the serious challenges we face.

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: 49,624! Thank you to everyone reaching out to your friends and family, being a voice for peace in your community. It takes all of us, together.

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: Last year an 11 yo girl at DEFCON hacked a replica of FL’s voting system in 10 mins - threats to election security are real. My Securing America’s Elections Act will empower every state to use voter-verified paper ballots to ensure no one can alter our election results.

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: When we stand up and speak the truth, it exposes those whose motives aren't in the interests of the people. They'll try to silence us, but we can't cower in a corner because they want us to shut up. I don’t know about you, but when someone tells me to be quiet, I speak up louder

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: Trump’s budget would cut Medicaid by $1.5 trillion, Medicare by $845 billion and now he wants to strike down the entire ACA, leaving 20m people uninsured. The American people deserve a president who puts their health and safety first. #ServiceBeforeSelf

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: Pulling funding for military readiness in order to construct small portions of a wall that will not increase border security is unserious and unstrategic leadership. The American people need genuine national security & effective, humane border security.

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: Saudi/US alliance bombing more hospitals in Yemen. The US has been aiding Saudi Arabia in their genocide of the Yemeni people for four years. This must end now.  https://tulsi.click/2v5cp7  #Tulsi2020

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: When we are informed, involved, and working together toward a common goal, we are more powerful than any special interest group. We need to get corporate money and lobbyists out of politics and elevate the voices of the people of our country. #ServiceBeforeSelf @Tulsi2020

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text:
Another 1,000 people joined our movement just yesterday. We will carry all of your voices with us to the debate stage in June! Thank you 
https://tulsi2020.com/donate

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: My husband and I both have roots in New Zealand and it’s inspiring to see how the community is rallying to heal together. An attack on one of us is an attack on all of us - because when one of us hurts, we all hurt.

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: “The time is always right to do what is right.” - Dr. Martin Luther King Jr. #TuesdayThoughts

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: Happy 40th birthday @cspan! Thank you for providing transparency for the American people through your unfiltered coverage of what is happening in our nation’s capital.

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: Once you catch the service bug, it’s hard to shake! Charles Carroll is a 105 year old WWII vet still serving. He does it because he loves the people and seeing their smiles "is worth a lot." #ServiceBeforeSelf

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: By 2025, wind and solar will be cheaper than coal across the board. Anyone who’s still against renewable energy is fighting a losing battle. #ClimateJustice

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: "We still don't know how rampant sexual assault in the military is, because there is still a fear of retaliation, there is a stigma, and people who don't want to be known as 'that one' who went against the team, who turned their back." #Tulsi2020

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: (6/6) We have a lot of work to do — rebuilding our country's crumbling infrastructure, ending wasteful regime change wars, forging a clean energy future, ensuring healthcare for all, achieving immigration reform and so much more.

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: (5/6) ... Americans all over the country are asking when our leaders, from every party, are going to put aside partisan politics and work to address the challenges that are threatening American lives and livelihoods...

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: (4/6) … the 2020 elections - and all elections - by passing my Securing America's Elections Act, which empowers every state to use voter-verified paper ballots making it impossible for Russia or anyone else to change our election results…

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: (3/6) …it would have precipitated a terribly divisive crisis that could have even led to civil war. Now we must stand together and move beyond this divisive issue that has taken up enough of the national conversation. I'm calling on Congress to protect the integrity of...

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: (2/6) …of conspiring with a foreign power to interfere with our elections is a good thing for America. If the president of the United States had been indicted for conspiring with Russia to interfere with and affect the outcome of our elections…

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: (1/6) I strongly supported Mueller being allowed to complete his investigation and submit his findings. Now that Mueller has found no collusion took place, we need to set aside our partisan interests and recognize that finding the president of the United States not guilty…

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: New reports show legal marijuana to be the fastest-growing industry in the country: 65,000 full-time jobs added to the US job market in 2018 and 60% of voters supporting legalization. This underscores the fact that it’s time to decriminalize marijuana nationwide.

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: In 2017, 72,000 people died of drug overdoses - more than the number of US soldiers killed during the Vietnam War. Purdue Pharma and other drug cartels masquerading as legitimate pharmaceutical corporations must be prosecuted. #PeopleBeforeProfits

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: While we were in New Hampshire yesterday, 1,600 people joined us from all across the country. Your support is the reason our message of peace will be heard. https://www.tulsi2020.com/donate

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: Thank you @EspeSpalding for your support and for urging others to do the same! And thank you for sharing your music with the world ... I remain a fan.

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: So sorry! Technical issues with Twitter again... Head to Facebook and YouTube to watch Tulsi LIVE at Plaistow Public Library. -V.

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: Executing even one prisoner in error is too great a risk. We must end the death penalty now. As President I will work for comprehensive criminal justice reform including abolishing the federal death penalty. #TULSI2020

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: It is unacceptable that it takes a lawsuit against Monsanto, maker of Roundup, to determine whether exposure to glyphosate can cause cancer. We must protect the ability of independent scientists to research & publish findings free of corporate influence

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: 1,600 more donors today. Thank you! This is what democracy looks like. Our campaign is powered by the people - not PACs.

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: LIVE on the road - Dover Town Hall - Dover, NH #TulsiTV #TULSI2020 https://tulsi.to/tv

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: Unless we protect our water, there is no economy, there are no jobs, there is no life - it's as simple as that. #WorldWaterDay is Every Day. #LoveWater #WaterIsLife #StandingRock #TULSI2020 https://tulsi.to/

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: This little girl warmed my heart. Strong fathers teach their daughters to be strong women. Thank you for being an example to all fathers out there, Adam Powell @SelmaTimes!

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: Make the full Mueller report public and available to the American people. #ReleaseTheReport

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: Thank you! So far we have 44,255 unique donors of the 65,000 needed to get on the debate stage! Almost 4,000 people contributed in the last 2 days. I’m humbled by your support. Stay tuned for updates!

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: LIVE on the road - NEC Town Hall - Concord, NH #TulsiTV #TULSI2020 https://tulsi.to/tv

text: LIVE on the road - World Water Day - Concord, NH #TulsiTV #TULSI2020 https://tulsi.to/tv

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: Aloha Henniker! Tune in to Tulsi’s New England College town hall! -V.

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: We must stand united against antisemitism and all forms of religious bigotry—symbols of hatred are a poison. We cannot be complacent. We must fight back with the power of love and inclusivity.

name: Tulsi Gabbard

name: Tulsi Gabbard

text: Our voice is needed in the debates! The DNC req's candidates have 65,000 unique donors to qualify for the debate stage. With your help, we can get there. Just $1 today will help bring us to a debate on the issues of life and death that face our nation.

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: Rev. James Davis has a mission—to advocate for the kids that he buses to school every day. Let’s build a country where we value our work as service to our community, & where every worker is valued as a member of that community. #AlohaInAction #AlohaInSC

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: Pulling out of the INF Treaty will escalate the new cold war, set in motion a new nuclear arms race, & undermine our national security. Walking away from this agreement brings us closer to nuclear war & wastes our precious taxpayer dollars #SayNoToNewColdWar #SayNoToNuclearWar

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: I introduced the INF Treaty Compliance Act (HR1249) to stop Trump from escalating the new cold war and sparking an expensive & dangerous new nuclear arms race. Our precious taxpayer dollars are for improving the lives of the American people, not bring us closer to nuclear war.

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: Trump’s volatile & ill-conceived trade wars are causing farmers to declare bankruptcy in record numbers. The median income for U.S. farm households was -$1,548 in 2018. This is crazy. We need leadership in the WH that provides the stability & support small farmers need to thrive.

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: I will bring a soldier's values & principles to the White House, restoring dignity, honor & respect to the presidency. Above all, a soldier lives by the principle of putting service before self. As your president, I will bring this spirit to the Oval Office. #ServiceBeforeSelf

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: Our veterans deserve the best care we can provide as a nation, and no one - especially those who fought for our country - should be in danger of prosecution for seeking safe and effective treatment.

text: Congratulations to Denver teachers on their successful strike! When we stand united in the face of a broken system, we have the power to enact change. Teachers should be valued as much as doctors - their work lays the foundation for our children's future.

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: I’m running for President to end our regime change wars, work to end new Cold War, & walk us back from the abyss of nuclear war. We face greater risk of nuclear catastrophe now more than ever. I’m introducing a bill to stop Trump from scrapping INF treaty & sparking new arms race

No escaping climate change. HI is a frontline cmmty for the impacts of climate change. We don't debate whether it is real here, we talk about how to adapt to rising ocean levels flooding storm drains, & increasingly severe weather patterns. #ClimateAction

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: America’s broken prison system is the center of our mental health crisis. In LA where 70% of inmates are medically or mentally ill they’re tearing down a “dungeon-like” county jail to make room for a mental health treatment center.  #CriminalJusticeReform

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: Every time a president declares a "national emergency" in order to get  his way on a particular issue, the closer we are to a dictatorship. Who needs Congress or the people if the president can make the decision on issues by himself? Very dangerous precedent.

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: NeoCon Elliott Abrams career is built on promoting regime-change wars. The Trump Admin’s appointment of Abrams as special envoy to Venezuela is further evidence of the president’s lack of understanding of our dark history in Latin America and the NeoCons’ control over him.

When everybody's gotta pick a side

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: I’ve read the letter from Dr. Vanessa Tyson. Her description of her experience is sober, credible and heart wrenching. Her story should be taken seriously and there should be a thorough investigation that respects Dr. Tyson’s privacy and courage in coming forward.

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: We must always remember the true cost of war, for our troops as well as their families, from wounds visible and invisible, and keep those who make the ultimate sacrifice always in our hearts as we work for peace.

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: This, too, is the cost of war and it should weigh on the conscience of those who find the money and political will to send our servicemen and women into battle, but not to care for them when they return.

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: We cannot and must not be complacent in the face of a system that abandons our veterans who put their lives on the line for our country.

name: Tulsi Gabbard

text: If we profess to truly care about the Syrian people, if we truly care about ending their suffering, we've got to be willing to meet with whoever we need to if there is a possibility and a chance that can help us take steps forward towards peace.

name: Tulsi Gabbard

text: .@morningjoe Syria/Assad did not attack us on 9/11, killing thousands of Americans — al-Qaeda did. No Authorization to Use Military Force has ever passed Congress to go to war against Syria. If US topples Assad, Al-Qaeda/ISIS will take over. Why do you prefer them to Assad?

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: We heard attacks from warmongers in politics/media before. Those opposed to Iraq/Libya/Syria regime change wars are called “dicatator-lovers” or “cozy” with evil regimes. Rather than defend their position, they resort to name-calling & smears. American people wont fall for this.

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: Prison for sewage violation?? This is appalling, unfair and unjust.

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: Trump says he is going to focus on counter-terrorism while simultaneously supporting/helping al-Qaeda and partnering with the Saudis, the actual leading state sponsors of terror, who spread the extremist ideology that fuels the likes of ISIS and al-Qaeda.

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: Trumps actions to withdraw from the Iran nuclear deal makes it MORE likely they will restart their nuclear weapons program, and makes it less likely North Korea will ever give up theirs. This makes our people, our country and the world less safe. #SOTU

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: I visited the Auschwitz concentration camp and it is an experience I will never, ever forget. The world must never forget the genocide that the Jewish people suffered. Only then can we appreciate how necessarily it is to never allow such a thing to ever happen again. #SOTU

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: I applaud the president for standing up against anti-Semitism. Now we should all stand up against religious and racial bigotry of all kinds. #SOTU

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: Trump promised North Korea that we will not wage regime-change war against them while we simultaneously threaten regime-change war in Venezuela and Iran. North Korea will look at Trump’s actions, not his empty promises. #SOTU

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: Trillions of dollars to pay for your endless regime-change wars, your new cold war, including your new nuclear arms race caused by your trashing the INF treaty. #SOTU

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: Trump’s unpredictable impulsive trade policies make it impossible for businesses, small and large, to plan ahead regarding investment, expansion, etc. His unpredictability is bad for business/economy/workers. #SOTU

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: Trump’s trade-war against China has damaged, not helped, our economy, has undermined our efforts to denuclearize North Korea, and has strengthened the hand of Chinese anti-American militarists. #SOTU

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: Our immigration system is a mess, and our politicians refuse to get serious about it. This is the state of the union. We need comprehensive immigration reform now. #SOTU

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: The root cause of mass immigration on our southern border is our history of US military intervention in Latin America that left countries destroyed. Before we talk about a wall, we need to end our ongoing threats of intervention - this time in Venezuela. #SOTU

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: This president is incapable of unifying our country. He is a great divider. He was elected by and governs by fomenting division amongst us. His calls for unity are hollow. This is the state of the union. #sotu

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: A police officer who murdered a black man in cold blood, shooting him 16 times, was only give a 7-year sentence. Those who tried to cover up his crime were let off scot-free. Racists are emboldened. This is the state of the union. #BlackHistoryMonth #sotu

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: Yes - passage of #firststepact was a major bipartisan milestone for prison reform. There is much more to be done to reform our broken criminal justice system. #sotu

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: Trump’s tax cuts have been a failure - tax giveaways to corporations, adding $1.5 trillion to the national debt and not translating to relief for working Americans or benefiting small business. #SOTU

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: Too many people in our country are forced to work 2-3 jobs just to pay the rent and put food on the table. #SOTU

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: Beautiful. There is no greater happiness than when we do things to serve others. Let’s lift up stories of young leaders like Jahkil doing the good work of building and healing our communities. #BHM

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: Later tonight I'll welcome Syrian Kurdish leader, Ilham Ahmed, Co-President of the Syrian Democratic Council, as my guest to the State of the Union address. She has been a leader in the fight against ISIS in Syria, and a strong advocate for peace.

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: Trump continues to turn the swamp into a cesspool - this time nominating David Bernhardt, a former oil and gas lobbyist and “walking conflict of interest,” as Secretary of the Interior, responsible for conservation of our federal land and natural resources.

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: NBC/Neocons’ fraud exposed. Revealing interview with Glenn Greenwald. It’s a must see for anyone who cares about the future of our country.

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: After apologizing for the picture, Governor Northam now says it wasn't him in the picture. He's lost all credibility. And I hope that for the good of Virginia and the country, he will resign.

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: We need to get serious about fighting cancer by resolving to take on the powerful forces in our society that profit from it. We need a green economy that rewards clean energy industries & ensures access to fresh, affordable, pesticide-free foods for all. #worldcancerday2019

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: Say no to nuclear war. Say no to regime change wars.

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: Rosa Parks understood the power of a simple action to assert dignity & humanity in the face of a culture caught in the grip of individual & systemic racism. Today we remember her in all that she was - not only a symbol, but a leader who worked tirelessly for racial justice. #BHM

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: As commander-in-chief, I will work to end the new cold war, nuclear arms race and slide into nuclear war. That is why the neocon/neolib warmongers will do anything to stop me.

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: I will bring a soldier's perspective, values and heart to the White House -- restoring the values of dignity, honor and respect to the presidency. And above all, love for our people and love of country. #tulsi2020

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: @ggreenwald exposes that @NBC used journalistic fraud to discredit our campaign. But more important is their motive: “to smear any adversary of the establishment wing of the Democratic Party – whether on the left or the right – as a stooge or asset of the Kremlin.”

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: Happy Spring Festival! To those celebrating early this weekend, please accept my best wishes and hopes for a peaceful and prosperous new year. #YearOfThePig

text: Each of us and all of us must rise again now and come together for each other, our country, and the world. #Tulsi2020 #AlohaRally

text:
Deep inside the heart of every American is the love, honor,
courage, and ideals that formed the foundation of this country … ideals that still shine in each and every one of us.

text: What our country needs now more than ever is the spirit of aloha. #Tulsi2020 #AlohaRally

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: Love should not be mistaken for weakness. There is no force more powerful than love. #Tulsi2020 #AlohaRally

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: These powerful politicians dishonor the sacrifices made by every one of our service members, and their families - they are the ones who pay the price for these wars. #Tulsi2020 #AlohaRally

text: Trump campaigned against regime change wars when he ran for President but now bows to the wishes of the neocons around him, clamoring for the regime change wars he claimed to oppose, this time in Venezuela and Iran.

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: We must stand against powerful politicians from both parties who sit in ivory towers thinking up new wars to wage & new places for people to die. Wasting trillions of dollars, hundreds of thousands of lives, undermining our economy and security, and destroying our middle class.

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: Tune in to watch Tulsi speak now and announce her vision for our country.

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: TULSI 2020: Tulsi Gabbard Presidential Campaign, The ALOHA Launch - Live from Hawaii, USA

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: Join me in building a movement for peace at home and abroad that will fulfill the promise of America for freedom, justice, equality, and opportunity for all. Today we kick off our campaign. Tune in here at 3 PM HST/ 8 PM EST. #Tulsi2020 https://tulsi2020.com

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text:
The government is funded for 21 days. 

Let’s stay focused on what’s most important:

Reopen the government, pay Federal employees, and deliver solutions that serve the needs of our people and our country. People before politics.
