name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: Veterans who survived combat are now suffering from rare cancers, lung diseases, neurological disorders, & more. Today we intro'd Burn Pits Accountability Act to help make sure veterans can get the care they've earned. Thanks @IAVA for your leadership!

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: Toxic burn pits are the Agent Orange of our post-9/11 generation of veterans. When I was deployed to Iraq, the cloud of toxic smoke and fumes from the massive burn pit on our camp was an every day reality. I know the damage they can cause. #BURNPITS

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: Politicians must represent and listen to the people who elected them to serve—not whatever lobbyist writes them the biggest check. It’s long past due for campaign finance reform in our country. PAC $$ has no place in politics and has no place in my people-powered campaign.

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: I regret the role I played in causing such pain, and I remain committed to fighting for LGBTQ+ equality. You can learn more about my legislative record here:

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: I’m so grateful to my friends and loved ones, both gay and straight, who patiently helped me see how my past positions on these issues were at odds with my values, my aloha, and that they were causing people harm.

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: When we divide people based on who they are or who they love, all we are doing is adding fuel to the flames that perpetuate bigotry and hatred.

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: When we deny LGBTQ+ people the basic rights that exist for every American, we are denying their humanity - denying that they are equal. We are also creating a dangerous environment that breeds discrimination and violence.

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: I look forward to being able to share more of my story and experiences growing up – not as an excuse, but in the hopes that it may inspire others to truly live aloha; to love and care for others.

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: But over the years, I formed my own opinions based on my life experience that changed my views – at a personal level in having aloha, love, for all people, and ensuring that every American, regardless of sexual orientation or gender identity, is treated equally under the law.

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: While many Americans may relate to growing up in a conservative home, my story is a little different because my father was very outspoken. He was an activist who was fighting against gay rights and marriage equality in Hawaii – and at that time, I forcefully defended him.

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: But I also grew up in a socially conservative household, where I was raised to believe that marriage should only be between a man and a woman. For a period of my life I didn’t see the contradiction in those beliefs.

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: I grew up knowing that every person is a child of God, and equally loved by God. I have always believed in the fundamental rights and equality of all people.

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: That cannot happen, because every single American deserves to be treated equally – by their fellow Americans and under the law. I will continue to fight for LGBTQ+ people, whether they’re in school or serving in uniform, trying to get healthcare, or taking care of their family.

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: I know that LGBTQ+ people still struggle, are still facing discrimination, are still facing abuse and still fear that their hard-won rights are going to be taken away by people who hold views like I used to.

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: My views have changed significantly since then, and my record in Congress over the last 6 years reflects what is in my heart: A strong and ongoing commitment to fighting for LGBTQ+ rights.

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: Many years ago, I apologized for my words and, more importantly, for the negative impact that they had. I sincerely repeat my apology today.

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: Aloha. In my past, I said and believed things that were wrong, and worse, hurtful to people in the LGBTQ+ community and their loved ones. I’m deeply sorry for having said and believed them.

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: Purdue Pharma knew about the addictive nature of their drugs and instructed executives to try to push blame on those who had become addicted, instead of taking accountability for fueling the #opioidcrisis. We must hold them accountable for their crimes.

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: Thank you, Sean. I'm grateful for you & your friendship. Many years ago I said & believed things that were wrong & hurtful to the LGBT community. For that, I remain deeply sorry. My views have changed, & I'm committed to continuing to fight for LGBT equality.

name: Tulsi Gabbard

text: By recognizing our interdependence and committing to a spirit of collaboration and mutual respect, we can bring about a brighter future for all.

name: Tulsi Gabbard

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: Steve King’s comments and views are outrageous, offensive and must be condemned. Congress must take action immediately and pass a resolution to censure him.

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: We need leadership in Washington that will protect our air, our water, and our health. Continuing down this path is unimaginable. More details here in this @nytimes feature:

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: A coal plant outside Houston, TX is spewing sulphur dioxide into the air without restrictions, spreading a toxic haze across state lines. Pollutants from coal mines in West Virginia are killing aquatic life in the area’s waterways.

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: Millions of pounds of a pesticide Obama tried to ban have been applied to crops in southern California, sickening farm workers. A daycare in the migrant center is located near these pesticide spraying areas, leaving infants and toddlers at risk of exposure.

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: In just two years, the Trump Administration has rolled back 78 environmental regulations, directly putting the health and safety of Americans at risk.

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: Today an estimated 800,000 federal employees will miss their first  paychecks of the year. Families are suffering. Our country is less safe. The impact of this shutdown is real.

name: Tulsi Gabbard
text: It’s appalling how our health and safety are being put in jeopardy as a result of this government shutdown. This shows the administration puts political priorities over the American people.

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: From Kavanaugh to state abortion bans—including the one signed today in Georgia—Republicans are waging a coordinated assault to overturn Roe v. Wade. We need a president who understands the real stakes of this fight, and who's willing to draw a line.

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: Teachers deserve our endless thanks on #TeacherAppreciationDay and every day. And you know what else they deserve? To be paid as though they hold our kids' futures in their hands—because they do.

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: Women deserve a president who will fiercely defend their rights, without hesitation. If you agree, sign on and support my pledge to only nominate judges who will uphold Roe v. Wade and protect reproductive rights:

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: I believe that reproductive rights are human rights, and they are nonnegotiable. So in the face of relentless attacks, I pledge that I will only nominate judges — including Supreme Court justices — who will commit to upholding Roe v. Wade. Here's why:

text: We have a president who can't imagine what it's like to be denied basic rights—but he'd deny them to LGBTQ people and so many others. We deserve better. We deserve equality. And it's going to take all of us raising our voices to win this fight.

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: I had a blast with Lillian and Kendall on @podblesstexas. My episode goes live today, check it out!

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: Nurses deserve more than just our appreciation for the love, expertise, and long hours they put into their work—they deserve pay that reflects it. Happy #NationalNursesDay to the amazing nurses across the country. Thank you for taking care of all of us.

text: Great to be with @HinojosaTX and @texasdemocrats to discuss how we'll turn Texas blue!

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: If you want to know what my presidency would look like, just take a look at this campaign. It's powered by the voices of people, of all ages and backgrounds, who prove every day that #BraveWins. We’re growing fast, and I'd love for you to join our team: http://kirstengillibrand.com/donate

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: I'm so moved by your words, @MartiGCummings, and you're right: LGBTQ people deserve to have a president fighting for them in Washington. And we will win this fight.

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: As Ramadan begins, may this holy month bring reflection and renewal to all our Muslim brothers and sisters. Ramadan Mubarak!

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: The way our elections are funded now excludes so many voices from the political process. But our government works best when *more* people participate, not just the wealthy. That's why I have a Clean Elections Plan to democratize our democracy.

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: Enough is enough. There's no room for excuses. Congress must past the Military Justice Improvement Act. We need to step up and fix a system that is failing the brave men and women that serve to keep our nation safe.

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: In 2018, I flipped 18 Trump counties in NY. My 2012 vote share is the highest a statewide candidate has won in NY—ever. So yes, I'm “electable.” But I’m also the right candidate to take on Trump because I have the experience, vision and record to win.

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: We've seen the corrupting force money plays in politics. My Clean Elections Plan will give power back to everyday Americans and ensure our elected officials are actually fighting for the people they represent.

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: I’ve voted against President Trump’s cabinet and administration picks (including John Kelly in 2017) more than any other Senator. Why? Because they weren’t fit for the job—just like the president who appointed them. https://www.nytimes.com/interactive/2017/01/31/us/politics/trump-cabinet-confirmation-votes.html?fbclid=IwAR0BFxcj7wBoN-MXFQ_eqN8dPSRSI8F3pzilqB3woUS-RYvw2BjM55qACSM …

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: Today in Texas, a disability rights activist asked me what I would do to meet standards of inclusion. I've committed to having someone with disabilities in my Cabinet, because I want to get this right. Accessibility and inclusion are issues I'll take on with urgency and care.

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: Right now, most of the money in our politics comes from a small group of mostly white, mostly older men. My Clean Elections Plan would amplify more voices, like a similar program did in Seattle. When we bring more people to the table, our government works better for all of us.

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: I was honored to have @MonicaSibri at our campaign kickoff. She's a DREAMer, an advocate for immigrants and women, and now she's headed to graduate school. We need more brave leaders like her—if you can, please chip in to support her dreams:

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: Representing Iowans means ALL Iowans. Signing this bill and widening health care disparities doesn’t make @IAGovernor a leader, it makes her a bully.

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: Congratulations, @samiheiney! #BraveWins

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: If we want working families to thrive, we must take every opportunity to support workers and their right to collectively bargain for better wages and benefits. I'm proud to be an original cosponsor of the Protecting the Right to Organize Act, and I urge Congress to pass it.

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: Can we have a good time *and* talk about the issues people care about? Absolutely. Thanks for a great event @MartiGCummings!

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: This is immoral, un-American, and will hurt millions of women and transgender people. Religious freedom doesn't give anyone the right to deny health care.

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: If we want to change the way Washington works—or make it work at all—we have to get big money out of politics. My Clean Elections Plan is designed to do just that by making every American's voice just as powerful as the Koch brothers': https://medium.com/@SenGillibrand/ba02ec1aaf19 …

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: What she said.

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: The gratitude is mutual, @MartiGCummings!

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: On this #NationalDayOfPrayer, we must face the reality that not everyone is safe in their house of worship. America is supposed to welcome all people, regardless of faith. My prayer is that we can restore our moral fabric, reject hate, and live up to who we're supposed to be.

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text:
We need a president who's brave enough to take on corruption in Washington. Americans have lost faith in our democracy because elected officials are more beholden to big donors and special interests than they are to the people.

My Clean Elections Plan would change that.

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: My Clean Elections Plan would flip our current political system on its head—empowering more women, young people, and people of color to have a say in our government and set our course for a more equal and just future.

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text:

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: I'll go anywhere, any time, to make the case for progressive policies that will make life better for American families. Looking forward to my town hall in Iowa with Chris Wallace.

text: I've been concerned about AG Barr since his nomination, which is why I voted against it. After yesterday's hearing, there's no question that he's more focused on representing the president than the American people. It's an embarrassment to his office and he should resign.

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: By eliminating a current taxpayer subsidy for excessive CEO compensation—25 times the median salary of their employees, or more than $1 million—we'd fully fund my Clean Elections Plan and then some. That's leveling the playing field in more ways than one.

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: It's clear the Trump Administration will stop at nothing to take health care away from tens of millions of Americans and end coverage for pre-existing conditions. We have to vote like our lives depend on it—because for many families, they do.

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: Labor movements all over the world have given us the hard-fought rights workers have today—and with those rights under attack more than ever, we have to hold that line. This #InternationalWorkersDay, let's keep up the fight for strong unions and a strong middle class.

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: We will never accomplish our boldest, most progressive policy ideas if we don't get big money out of politics first. My Clean Elections Plan is a way to get there. Read more about it here:

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: Plans like mine will put our elections back in the hands of the people instead of special interests—and in a functioning democracy, shouldn't that be the standard?

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: Not only do clean elections make candidates less beholden to big money, but they amplify more voices in the process. Historically political donors have been disproportionately white, male, older and very wealthy. Democracy Dollars will bring more people to the table.

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: How can we know if my Clean Elections Plan will work? The answer is, it already has. My plan is modeled in part off of a program in Seattle, which has led to candidates relying less on big money, making them more accountable to their constituents.

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: In commemoration of #YomHaShoah, we honor the millions of lives taken in the Holocaust—and we must recommit to fighting the rising threats of anti-Semitism, bigotry and white supremacy around the globe and here at home. Our silence is not an option.

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: Attorney General Barr needs to resign. Today, he's proven once again that he's more interested in protecting the president than working for the American people. We can't trust him to tell the truth, and these embarrassing displays of propaganda have to stop.

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: Show me a supposedly “unfixable” problem in Washington, and I’ll show you the political corruption standing in the way. That’s why I rolled out my Clean Elections plan—bold reform to attack the corrupting influence of money at its core.

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: Big money in politics has bred a culture where special interests and wealthy megadonors—who are overwhelmingly white, male and older—have all the influence in our elections. My Clean Elections plan amplifies voices that haven’t been heard for too long. https://medium.com/@SenGillibrand/my-clean-elections-plan-to-get-money-out-of-politics-ba02ec1aaf19 …

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: We can change the way Washington works by leveling the playing field of whose voices are heard in our democracy. It starts with getting big money out of our elections, and I have a plan to do just that.

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: Big money has corrupted our politics, allowing wealthy donors' voices to drown out everyone else's. If we want a government that works for all of us, we have to ensure that elected officials in Washington actually represent the people who sent them there.

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: If we want to fix what's broken in Washington, we have to start at the root of the problem: money in politics. Today, I'm announcing a bold new Clean Elections plan to combat political corruption and bring more people to the table in our government.

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: Again and again and again. We can't accept this as our reality. For #UNCC, for Parkland, for Santa Fe, and for too many communities who've lived through a day at school turning into a nightmare—we have to fix this.

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: The photos coming out of Davenport are heartbreaking. I'm thinking of all the families, first responders and all those impacted along the Mississippi River and across the Heartland who have faced historic flooding this year. Please stay safe and follow officials' instructions.

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: New Hampshire takes their responsibility seriously as the #FITN primary. I always love talking with voters there—and future voters like Scout!—because they’re not afraid to get to the heart of the issues that matter most to working families. Good news: neither am I.

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: Women make up a majority of Democratic voters, but they have almost never had an equal or majority stake in powering presidential campaigns. We're changing that.

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: We need 65,000 individual donors to secure a spot on the debate stage. If you chip in $1, you can help get us there. https://secure.actblue.com/donate/kg-social?refcode=tw-043019 …

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: When I meet girls like Scout on the trail, I always take time to tell them they can be leaders too. It turns out Scout runs a lemonade stand to help children at the border. She didn't wait for someone to tell her she could lead—she just did it!

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text:
When women work together, nothing can stand in our way.

Join @supermajority’s women-powered movement here: http://bit.ly/2ZKMbd5

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: At the end of the day, this fight is about fixing what’s been broken and restoring decency to our government. I proudly signed the #WeAreIndivisible pledge to have a substantive debate in this primary, and work to defeat President Trump together. Let’s do this!

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: I pledged not to use hacked material in my campaign because restoring American faith in the Oval Office is critical to unifying our nation. I hope the other presidential candidates will join me.

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: The reviews are in: Henry gives Avengers: Endgame a 10/10. (No spoilers!)

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: The road ahead of us is long, but it is lined with brave and powerful women fighting for the soul of our country—women like @KirstenisKit. #BraveWins

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: Yesterday's house party in Milford, NH was amazing! Even as voters sat silently listening to each other's questions, you could feel the buzzing energy in the room. These voters are fighting tirelessly to protect their families—and you can bet I'm fighting right alongside them.

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: The president is a coward, a bully, and someone with over a dozen sexual assault allegations against him. My campaign is rooted in bravery, standing up for the vulnerable, and valuing women. That contrast is what this fight is about—right over wrong. And right will win.

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: Something is fundamentally broken in our society when any house of worship is made unsafe by gun violence and hate—again and again and again. I’m keeping Poway and the entire Jewish community in my prayers. More than that, I don’t accept this. We must end this epidemic.

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: How will I reunite this country as president? The same way I’ve always approached public service—with bravery and compassion.

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text:
At our @KeeneState_ town hall, a voter asked how I plan to close the wealth gap. Some of the ideas I shared were:
• Establishing postal banking
• Raising the minimum wage
• Passing national paid leave
• Full employment through skills training

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: Is there anything more American than talking about the issues that matter most over a good local brew? Thank you for having us, @GreaterNashuaYD!

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: Women belong where decisions are made. Agree? Then I’ve got a sticker for you:

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text:
It cannot be said enough: Your body, your choice.

This is a win for reproductive rights advocates across the country, and an important reminder that we must continue the fight to protect safe, legal abortion.

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text:
Excited to be heading back to Nashua, NH today! The people were so warm and welcoming the last time we were in town. 

Here's a look at what the last trip looked like:

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: No parent should have to depend on the compassion and generosity of coworkers to care for a seriously ill child. We need national paid family leave now.

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: I proudly endorsed @Marie4Congress in her primary for Illinois's 3rd congressional district. We need her in Congress, fighting for good jobs, health care, and equal rights for all—including women and LGBT Americans. If you can, chip in to support her:

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: It's been five years since the Flint water crisis began, and still, not every family has the guarantee of clean water. @LittleMissFlint has been tirelessly keeping up the ongoing fight for justice—you can support her community here: http://gofundme.com/LMFwater  #DontForgetFlint

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: It’s always been harder for women to run for office and win—but we can break that cycle by getting off the sidelines and speaking up in this election. Chip in $1 and we'll send you this sticker: https://secure.actblue.com/donate/women-belong-2020-sticker?refcode=tw042519 …

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: I've always been an underdog. I'm used to it. I've also won every race I've run. So when I say I'm not worried about being discounted now, you can believe it.

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: The Mueller report is incredibly damning, and presents significant bases for obstruction of justice. President Trump has to respond to congressional subpoenas so we can get the facts—and if he's going to try to fight Nancy Pelosi on it, I'll put my money on Pelosi every time.

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: I joined the women of @TheView this morning and talked about bravery.

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: This race is a marathon, not a sprint, and I'm going to keep sharing why I'm the best candidate to take on Trump.

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: The moment we're in isn't just about speaking up against sexual assault and harassment—it's about deciding whether we as a society value women.

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: President Trump and his aides are not only failing to hold Russia accountable for attacking our democracy, they're condoning it. Democrats need to be better—that's why I want us all to defend the integrity of our elections and pledge that we won't use stolen or hacked materials.

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text:
I pledge not to accept stolen or hacked materials from foreign actors, and I urge all other presidential candidates to do the same.

Join me in calling on the rest of the 2020 field to help defend our elections from foreign interference:

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text:
If we don't learn from Russia's cyber attacks on our election in 2016, they'll do it again. And we can't depend on President Trump to stop them.

So I created a pledge to defend our democracy, and I'm asking all of my fellow 2020 candidates to join me. http://kirstengillibrand.com/cybersecurity

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text:
Defending our elections from foreign interference is critical to protecting our democracy. Today, I created a pledge not to use any stolen or hacked information in my campaign, and I'm asking all 2020 candidates to sign it.

Sign on to support our pledge:

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: #EarthDay isn't just a day to recommit to the fight for our planet. Founded after the 1969 Santa Barbara oil spill, it reminds us that we can't win that fight if we don't take on oil industry greed. That's why I signed the #NoFossilFuelMoney pledge. Planet over profits.

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text:
Russia is a foreign adversary of the US, and the Trump administration is refusing to stop them from attacking our elections again.

I pledge that my campaign won't use stolen or hacked information from foreign actors, and I urge 2020 candidates to join me.

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: Sounds like a man with nothing to hide.

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: Bravo to the 31,000 #StopAndShopWorkers and @UFCW members who stood up for their right to health care and fair wages, and now have reached a tentative contract agreement. I'm proud to stand with them, and for all workers' right to collectively bargain.

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: I'm proud to stand with my colleague @JeanneShaheen opposing efforts to suppress the vote of tens of thousands of students. As a country we should encourage all voters to participate, not put up barriers for those seeking to perform their civic duty.

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: One of the highlights of my week in Iowa was spending time with @KirstenisKit. Her endorsement means the world to me. She embodies the bravery that this campaign is about.

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: Our democracy is strongest when voters have the freedom to head to the ballot box to make their voice heard. The efforts of @GovChrisSununu to restrict this right for tens of thousands of students is unconscionable. I strongly support efforts to amend and repeal this bill.

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text:
Glenwood
Pacific Junction

We visited 12 towns in Iowa this week, and kept a journal of the whole trip. My reflections along the way:

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: Happy Easter to all celebrating, from the Gillibrands!

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: My heart is with the families of those killed in the horrific attack in Sri Lanka. No one should fear violence when they come together in worship, anywhere in the world.

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: Okay, “brilliant kryptonite” might be my new favorite review. Thank you for coming to our events in New Hampshire, Susan!

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text:
65% of Americans agree: We have to legalize marijuana. 

It's critical to dismantling mass incarceration and institutional racism, and to achieving fundamental justice.

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: Vana and the amazing queens at the Blazing Saddle in Des Moines invited me for a visit tonight before their show. I felt underdressed, so I brought a dress I picked up yesterday—turns out it fit me, but it fit Vana even better! Thank you for having me, ladies!

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text:
.@oliviahabinck challenged me to an arm-wrestling match for a donation to support @CYDiowa and @iowastatedems. I said game on.

(Spoiler alert: I’m donating either way!)

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: Our rural Iowa listening tour wrapped today in Harlan, Denison, and Carroll, IA. Someone said they believe I can represent these communities well because I’m “from the Iowa part of New York State”—might have to steal that!

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: I take this notebook with me to every listening session, and I’ve been filling it on this listening tour through rural Iowa! I don’t assume I have all the answers—I’m here to learn from people, and the rural policy ideas I put out will come in part from these notes and stories.

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: These heroes deserve our respect and our support. If Congress fails to permanently renew the 9/11 Victim Compensation Fund, we will have denied them both.

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: Wishing a happy Passover to all those celebrating. Chag Sameach!

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: Thanks for coming out, Council Bluffs!

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text:
Behind the scenes of our rural Iowa listening tour.
https://medium.com/@SenGillibrand/notes-from-the-road-my-listening-tour-through-rural-iowa-7eb5702cee26 …

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: Today we kicked off our rural Iowa listening tour! These small towns don’t get a lot of visits from candidates, but I’m here to learn about locally crucial issues like mental health and rural economic development, hear from Iowans, and take notes. https://medium.com/@SenGillibrand/notes-from-the-road-my-listening-tour-through-rural-iowa-7eb5702cee26?source=linkShare-7d655378f079-1555624692 …

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text:
We can’t trust Trump’s handpicked AG to be transparent about the Mueller report. Congress needs to see it in full—and the public needs to know whether Trump obstructed justice.

Sign our petition calling on Barr to release the full report:

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: Really?

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: AG Barr’s press conference was a farce and an embarrassing display of propaganda on behalf of President Trump. Barr works for the people, not the president. They deserve to know Mueller’s full findings because nobody—especially not the president—is immune from accountability.

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: Congress should get the full, unredacted Mueller report. The American people have the right to know the facts—without the spin.

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: Even if you're not able to join us for my rural Iowa listening tour, you can follow along with our conversations and highlights on our live blog for the trip. I'll be sharing some of my favorite moments from the road:

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: So honored to have @KirstenisKit’s endorsement for my campaign. We’re going to be brave together.

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: Happy birthday, @ProgressIowa!

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: Tune in for our endorsement event with @KirstenisKit in Des Moines! I'm so inspired by her story of speaking out about sexual harassment, and keeping up the fight as an advocate for all survivors and women. So proud to have her support in this campaign! https://www.c-span.org/video/?459876-1/senator-kirsten-gillibrand-campaigns-des-moines-iowa&live …

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: So much fun hanging out with @DrakeDemocrats and community members, both human and canine.

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: Bravery is getting back up when you’ve been knocked down. Thank you to Fran and the Iowans who welcomed me today to see the flooding and hear how we can help.

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: I'm so moved by the Iowans I met who are focused on lifting others up in the wake of flooding—doing their part to help their whole community, even while recovering from losing their own homes. My reflections on this afternoon’s visit:

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: Fran and Jason Parr showed me around their home to see the unbelievable flood damage in Pacific Junction, IA. It’s heartbreaking, but they and their community aren’t broken down. They’re rallying to lift each other up and rebuild. And I told Fran I’d be back this summer to help.

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: Our first campaign stop in Iowa was to visit the flood relief center in Glenwood. This community is showing incredible bravery and resilience—they and every community affected by recent disasters need their leaders to set politics aside and provide the aid they need.

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: I'm excited about this! We're putting together a live blog so you can keep up with my listening tour through rural Iowa this week. Be sure to follow along for a behind-the-scenes look at the stories and ideas we're talking about:

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: Can’t wait to celebrate and support @iowademocrats in June!

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: I'm so thankful to receive @Marie4Congress's endorsement here in Chicago tonight, and I'm proud to endorse her to be the next congresswoman for IL-03. Illinoisans deserve leaders who will truly fight for all of them, including women seeking reproductive healthcare. #BraveWins!

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: You're on! If you win, my campaign will make a donation to @CYDiowa. If I win, be my tour guide on an Iowa trip this summer? See you Friday

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: Recently a reporter asked me why I think I'm the candidate who's best able to take on Trump and get things done. Here's my answer.

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: When @KirstenisKit spoke up about rampant sexual harassment in the Iowa Senate, she was fired. So she filed a lawsuit, and won—leading the Senate to change their policies and create accountability. That's bravery. And I'm so honored to have her support.

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: Institutional racism throughout our society has created a racial wealth gap that holds families back for generations. We need solutions both broad and targeted, from full employment and raising wages to postal banking and studying reparations.

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text:
Donald Trump is the first president in recent history to not release his tax returns. He's hiding something.

We deserve transparency and accountability from presidents and presidential candidates. Sign our petition calling on Trump to release his taxes:

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: Notre Dame has inspired millions around the world as a symbol of not only history and beauty, but of resilience and human ingenuity. Just as she has been for centuries, she'll be rebuilt again. I'm keeping the people of Paris and its heroic firefighters in my thoughts tonight.

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: I was proud to be the first presidential candidate to release my 2018 tax return, and for the 12 years I've been in office. Anyone who seeks the presidency should meet that standard—including Trump. Sign our petition calling on him to release his taxes:

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: Black moms are 3-4x more likely to die from pregnancy-related complications—it’s outrageous and it’s preventable. The MOMs Act, my bill to help hospitals standardize maternal care, is one way we can close the gap. This has to be a priority for all of us. #BlackMaternalHealthWeek

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: Thank you, @KirstenisKit. I'm so inspired by your bravery and your advocacy for women and survivors in Iowa and everywhere. Excited to keep up this fight with you.

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: We can't combat the corrupting influence of money in politics without transparency from our leaders. In honor of #TaxDay, add your name to say you won’t support a president who doesn’t release their tax returns—and call on President Trump to release his:

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text:
Donald Trump is hiding something. Otherwise, he would have released his tax returns by now.

Let's mark Tax Day tomorrow by demanding he release his tax returns, and pledging to only support a presidential candidate who releases theirs:

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: I’m really proud of what our team and this community have built so far—and we're just getting started.

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: Why not train the next generation in the STEM jobs we need to strengthen our economy and combat climate change? Why not invent our way into the future?

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: As a Senator who represents 9/11 victims, I can't accept any minimizing of that pain. But Trump's dangerous rhetoric against @IlhanMN is disgusting. It’s a false choice to suggest we can’t fight terrorism and reject Islamophobic hate at once—a president should do both.

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: Happy 103rd birthday, Beverly Cleary! Thank you for creating iconic characters who were adventurous and brave, unruly and unstoppable all at once—and expanding our idea of what a girl can be.

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text:
I believe that we can:
‣ Stop greed and corruption
‣ Restore our values
‣ Build an economy for all
‣ Keep America safe
‣ Fight for women and families

Text ISSUES to 60980 to learn more about what I'm fighting for.

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: Our troops deserve a Commander in Chief who fights for them as fiercely as they fight for this country. President Trump's transgender military ban, taking effect today, proves he fails that standard. As president I will end this.

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text:
The Public Service Loan Forgiveness program is a bureaucratic nightmare that has shortchanged millions of teachers, social workers, nurses and other public servants of the loan forgiveness they've earned.

@timkaine and I just introduced a bill to fix it.

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text:
As I travel around the country, the number-one fear on people’s minds is often this: If they or someone in their family get seriously sick or injured, how are they going to pay for it?
 
Let’s get this done for Americans and end that fear. We need Medicare For All.

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: It's unacceptable for CEOs to stack up profits while working families struggle. I stand with the #StopandShop workers striking in New England to fight back against cuts to their wages and health care.

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text:
This administration has replaced a corrupt oil lobbyist as Interior Secretary with...a corrupt oil lobbyist as Interior Secretary.

This is exactly why I signed the #NoFossilFuelMoney pledge. Our public lands are not for sale to the highest bidder.

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: This is what leadership looks like.

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: Happy #NationalPetDay from Maple!

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: The reason I've fought for so many years to end sexual assault in our military, on our college campuses, and in Congress comes down to one question: Do we value women? Unfortunately, there's a lot of evidence that we don't. I believe women and survivors deserve better.

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: I talked with CNN after our town hall about issues like climate change and health care, bringing people together, and why I love Wonder Woman.

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: Last night, a student named Alexis asked why I held my campaign kickoff rally outside of Trump International. Here's why.

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text:
A six-week abortion ban without exceptions for rape or incest. Unconstitutional and unconscionable. 

Ohio women are being endangered with this bill. Gov. DeWine: Veto this.

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: Medicare For All is an ambitious goal. But we also need a plan for how to get there, and I have one: Under my transition plan, we'd create a public option and force insurance companies to compete. That's how we can lower costs and get to universal health care.

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: There isn't just one political party for people of faith. My faith is an important part of who I am, why I'm a Democrat, and why I'm running for president.

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text:
Everyone knows the truth on this: Health care in this country is just too expensive.

Today I joined my Senate colleagues in co-sponsoring a new Medicare For All bill. We need everyone who supports it to speak out—sign our petition to join our fight:

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: Health care should be a fundamental right, and the American people deserve leaders who won't rest until we meet that goal. I'm proud to co-sponsor Medicare For All as we re-introduce it in the Senate today.

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: Bringing people together isn't just how we'll beat Trump in 2020—it's what this country needs from our next president. I'll do it because it's what I've always done.

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: Ending gun violence in this country is an issue of changing hearts and speaking to people's humanity. We can't give up that fight. Our kids' lives have to come before gun lobby greed.

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: Americans deserve a president who leads with bravery and compassion—not cowardice and hate. If you're ready to take on this fight with us, chip in $5 to help power this campaign: https://secure.actblue.com/donate/kg-social?refcode=tw-040919 … #GillibrandTownHall

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: We should confront the existential threat of climate change like JFK's moonshot: Let's pass a #GreenNewDeal and get to net-zero carbon emissions not because it's easy, but because it's hard. The whole point is that it's an ambitious set of goals—why not try? #GillibrandTownHall

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: When kids are being killed in their schools and in their communities in an epidemic of gun violence, every public official's humanity should kick in. NRA money is in the way. This can't wait—we have to put lives over greed. #GillibrandTownHall

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: If you've served your sentence and are reentering society, you should have the right to participate in our democracy and have a say in who represents you. We should restore returning citizens' right to vote. #GillibrandTownHall

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: We need Medicare For All, and I wrote a plan to get there by creating a public option that you can buy into. That's how we can create competition with insurance companies, get costs down, and make sure everyone has access to the health care they need. #GillibrandTownHall

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text:
President Trump is weak. He is a coward. 

Americans deserve a president who's brave. It's time to put a leader back in the White House. #GillibrandTownHall

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: If you're unwilling to stand up to the special interests that control everything in Washington, you're never going to make the changes we need. We need a president who's brave enough to stand up to the powerful and fight for what's right. #GillibrandTownHall

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: We have to end sexual assault and harassment in this country because it comes down to one important question: Do we value women? There's only one acceptable answer. #GillibrandTownHall

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: I'm the right candidate to take on President Trump because I can bring people together. I have and I can win red, purple, and blue districts. We need a president who will fix what's broken in this country—that's why I'm running. #GillibrandTownHall

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: What President Trump is doing to immigrant families at the border is inhumane and has nothing to do with national security. We need a complete transformation of our immigration policy and a real pathway to citizenship. #GillibrandTownHall

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: Team Gillibrand here! Kirsten's about to take the stage for her first @CNN town hall—tune in NOW on TV or http://go.cnn.com , and follow along here for highlights! #GillibrandTownHall

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: No.

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: Want to know where I stand on important issues ahead of our @CNN town hall tonight? Text ISSUES to 60980 to learn about my record and plans for everything from jobs to health care to national security. Tune in at 10 pm ET to hear more!

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: This election is the fight of our lives, and we can't win if we aren't willing to be brave for what we believe in.

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: We don't need Attorney General Barr, appointed by Donald Trump, to do any more editorializing. Make the full Mueller report public.

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: Tonight I'll take the stage for our first @CNN town hall! It's an exciting chance to answer voters' questions and share why I'm running and who I'm fighting for. Tune in at 10 pm ET! #bravewins

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: Getting ready for tonight’s CNN town hall!

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: Millions of Americans feel left behind right now because they see Washington as only working for the powerful. And they're absolutely right.

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: The Electoral College is undermining the most basic principle of a direct democracy: one person, one vote. I think it's time to end its control over our presidential elections—sign our petition if you agree:

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: Protecting kids from harm and discrimination shouldn't require brave leadership—it should just be what we do. Thank you, @CharlieBakerMA, and the advocates who've been leading this moral fight.

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: .@cmclymer is so right: If someone is brave enough to serve their country, they deserve our respect. Patriotism doesn't have a gender.

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: When it comes to this election, there’s one question we need to ask ourselves:

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: Years from now, we will all be asked, "What did you do when hate reigned? What battle did you take on? Who were you willing to stand up to?" If we want to be proud of our answer to that question, we have to fight now.

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: I voted against Kirstjen Nielsen’s nomination, and called for her resignation over the administration’s inhumane treatment of immigrant families six months ago. What this country truly needs is a moral reset on immigration policies—we won’t get that in this administration.

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: We celebrated 18 years today at our favorite brunch place, rode some scooters, and played ping pong with friends. Happy anniversary, Jonathan. Love you.

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text:
While we were still reeling from the attacks on 9/11, these brave emergency responders rushed to serve our country. Now these patriots are dying from the toxic exposure they endured at Ground Zero.

Not renewing the Victim Compensation Fund—permanently—would be a moral failure.

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: Any system that is built on disenfranchising voters is a system that needs to be torn down. We can't call this a true democracy as long as the Electoral College determines our elections—if you agree, sign our petition to end it:

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: I think public service is about listening—that’s why I’ve done more than 60 public events (and counting!) since announcing my run for president. Tune in to our town hall with voters in Concord, NH:

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: Thank you for having me! It’s time to make national paid family leave the priority it deserves to be.

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: If we want to break down the systematic barriers holding back too many unemployed and underemployed Americans—particularly in low-income communities—we have to make accessible the job training people need to work their way into the middle class.

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text:
Racist language like this has led to violence throughout the world’s history. No human being is an animal. We have to be better than this.
https://twitter.com/markmobility/status/1114287002348863488?s=21 …

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: Loved meeting voters (and future voters) in Dover, NH!

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: My national public service plan would make college accessible while advancing our goals in infrastructure, green energy and job training.

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: I think the American people want a president who is brave, who will lead with compassion rather than hate, and who will repair our moral fabric. That's why I'm running.

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text:
Survivors of campus sexual assault have shown extraordinary bravery by sharing their stories, demanding change, and leading a national movement to end this scourge at our colleges and universities. 

We should honor their bravery with action.

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: We should value women more than NRA greed, period. Let's pass the Violence Against Women Act in the Senate now.

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: 51 years ago today, Dr. Martin Luther King Jr. was assassinated. We can't forget his legacy of fiercely tackling injustice, nor the hate that cut his life short. His goals of equality and resistance to bigotry are as timely as ever—let's honor him by continuing to fight for them.

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: For far too long, colleges and universities have gotten away with turning a blind eye to the epidemic of campus sexual assault. We owe it to survivors to change the system and hold institutions accountable for protecting students.

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: One of my favorite days of the year: the first Congressional Women’s Softball team practice of the season. Press team doesn’t stand a chance!

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: Ten years ago today, Iowa legalized marriage equality: one of the first steps toward making it the law of the land in America. Our work isn't done until every LGBTQ person is safe and free from discrimination—but we're not done fighting. Cheers to victories, past and future.

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text:
When it comes to historic milestones for representation, progress, and equality, sometimes a picture is worth a thousand words. Congratulations to Chicago’s new mayor, @LightfootForChi. 

Photo: Kamil Krzaczyński

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: If we want to restore power to the people, we have to get to the root of our central problem: corruption and greed.

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: If the Georgia GOP actually cared about family values and saving lives, they'd be addressing maternal mortality instead of decimating access to safe reproductive health care.

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text:
President Trump is tearing apart the moral fabric of this country. He demonizes the vulnerable and punches down. He puts his name in bold on every building. He does this because he wants us to believe he's strong. He's not. Our President is a coward.

Americans deserve better .

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: President Trump has twisted the issue of immigration because he's a coward, and he's afraid of refugees. Let's untwist it: We need to secure our border, but we also need real immigration reform, a path to citizenship, and to treat asylum seekers with humanity instead of hate.

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: Leadership requires bravery. And if we don't have the courage to take on the most urgent threat we face, then what are we doing?

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: If you're elected president, you have to represent everyone. It makes no sense for the outcome of our elections to not actually reflect the number of votes received.

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: It's absurd that the leader of our country is chosen by a distorted system instead of the voices of all Americans. Proud to support @brianschatz's bill to abolish the Electoral College.

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: If women made up 51% of our elected offices, do you think we'd still be fighting for equal pay, affordable daycare, and paid leave? I think it's time to change who's at the decision-making table, and start prioritizing issues that have taken a back seat for too long. #EqualPayDay

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: President Trump is a bully and a coward, and his callousness towards Puerto Ricans who are still suffering is outrageous. He needs to stop lying and start helping our fellow citizens on the island—and I won't vote for a bill that cuts out the aid and rebuilding money they need.

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: The fact that we have a gender pay gap in 2019 means we're still struggling to value women in this country—and women of color even more. We need to make basic structural changes to ensure women can make what they earn. #EqualPayDay

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: Women on average may make 20% less than white men—and many women of color much less—but your glass will be 100% full with our new #EqualPayDay mug. Get yours and support our campaign to fight for equal pay for equal work: https://store.kirstengillibrand.com/products/mug?variant=14363074035747 …

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: When presidents are elected without the majority of Americans' votes, something is seriously broken in our democracy. Let's fix it.

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: Our democracy is built on the principle of one person, one vote. It can't function until we restore that principle. It's time to abolish the Electoral College.

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: About to take the stage at #WeThePeople19! Tune in here:

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: I'm so honored to address the 2019 graduates of New England College this May. Students are the future leaders of our country, and deserve our support in all ways—from expanding their opportunities to supporting their future careers and families. See you soon, @NewEngCollege!

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text:
President Trump is tearing apart the moral fabric of this country. He demonizes the vulnerable and punches down. He puts his name in bold on every building. He does this because he wants us to believe he's strong. He's not. Our President is a coward.

Americans deserve better .

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: We’re a few hours away from our biggest test of the campaign: the first FEC filing deadline. We have to show we have what it takes to pass a Green New Deal, Medicare For All, and national paid leave. If you're with me, donate $3 before midnight:

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text:
My grandmother taught me that there's nowhere women don't belong. But to prove that we belong in the White House, we have to prove we belong on the debate stage.

As #WomensHistoryMonth ends, I'm ready to make some new history. Join me—donate $1 now:

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: Our first end-of-quarter filing deadline is tonight, and we need to show we've got what it takes to win. If you agree we need a president who's brave enough to do what's right, chip in to help build this movement:

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text:
Being yourself takes bravery.
Serving your country takes bravery.

Demeaning and discriminating against trans Americans—including service members and students—is just cowardice. 

Trans rights are human rights. We will defend them as such. #TransDayOfVisibility

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: I'm running to get corruption and greed out of our politics, and make government accountable to you. That's why I released 12 years of tax returns and don't take money from corporate PACs or federal lobbyists. Will you help power this campaign? https://secure.actblue.com/donate/kg-social?refcode=tw-033019 …

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: I believe in an America where government works for people instead of special interests. Where we value women. Where we lead with bravery and compassion instead of fear and hate. Will you chip in $3 to make sure I can share that vision on the debate stage?

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: We need to call this what it is: An abortion ban, a violation of women's constitutional rights, and a direct assault on Roe v. Wade. I stand in solidarity with advocates in GA and nationwide who have been and will keep fighting for our rights. We're not going back.

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: Make the report public. Every page.

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: I’ve fought for Medicare for All since my first House race in 2006. It's not an abstract goal—I helped write the plan to get there from our current system. We will create competition, get costs down, and finally make health care a right for all. It's about time.

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text:
Let's prove that fear and hate are no match for all of us standing together and speaking out for what's right. 

Help us build this movement and win this fight: https://secure.actblue.com/donate/kg-social?refcode=tw-032919 …

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: We must secure our borders effectively and fight terrorism relentlessly. But let's be clear: Attacking immigrants and asylum seekers, throwing babies in cages, coddling white supremacists, building a pointless wall—these things aren't just immoral. They also make us LESS safe.

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: Women and men should make equal amounts of money for doing equal work. What a concept. https://www.vox.com/2019/3/27/18282775/paycheck-fairness-act-gender-pay-gap-pelosi … #PaycheckFairnessAct

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: It's mutual, @corybooker—and you're welcome for dinner any time. Great job last night!

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: Making national paid leave a reality for every worker in America has been my priority as a Senator, it's a priority in my campaign, and it would be a priority in my administration—exactly how it should be.

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: I will go toe-to-toe with anyone to do the right thing. Whether it’s powerful institutions, the President, or even my own party.

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: We can't fix what's broken in Washington unless we're brave enough to fundamentally change the way our government works, and detox our politics from the influence of unaccountable money. Join me in asking every 2020 candidate to release their tax returns: http://kirstengillibrand.com/taxes

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: 50 women are shot to death by their partners every month in America. We have to face the fact that there is a deadly connection between violence against women and guns in America. Leaders who put NRA blood money over women's lives shouldn't be anywhere near our laws.

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: I was the first member of Congress to make my official meetings, personal financial disclosures and taxes public. Now I'm the first presidential candidate to release my tax returns for 2018—and every year since 2007. Ask every candidate to do the same:

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: Corruption and greed are the root of almost all evil in our democracy. We need to protect voting rights and the integrity of our elections, get dark money out of politics and make government answerable to people again. Give the #ForThePeople Act a vote.

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: Democrats should proudly be the party of honesty, transparency and accountability. It's what voters deserve, and it's who we are. Add your name to join me in calling on every 2020 candidate to release their tax returns:

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: Kudos to my friend and fellow New Yorker @ReElectNydia for refusing to accept corporate PAC donations. Voters need to know we're working for them, not special interests—and we can't fix Washington until we walk the walk on transparency.

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: Transparency is essential to combating the corrupting influence of money in politics. The American people should know that their president is beholden to no one but them—that's why I’m urging all presidential candidates to join me and disclose at least ten years of their taxes.

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text:
My tax returns for every year I’ve been in office, including 2018, are now public.

We can't win our fight against Donald Trump without transparency and accountability. Sign my petition calling on every 2020 candidate to release their tax returns, too:

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text:
I just published my latest tax returns, like I do every year.

I've now released 12 years of my tax returns because voters deserve to know we're beholden only to them. If you agree, sign our petition calling on all presidential candidates to do the same: http://kirstengillibrand.com/taxes

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: Criminalizing women for exercising their constitutional rights is as dystopian as it gets. Doing so while ignoring the highest maternal mortality rate in the country is just hypocrisy. This bill is an outrage, and we all need to speak out against it.

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: We are living under an administration with no humanity.

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: Saving our planet should not be a partisan issue. Putting our kids' and grandkids' futures over today's fossil fuel profits should not be a hard choice to make. We need to treat global climate change like the urgent, existential threat that it is, and act accordingly.

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: Cutting people around the world off from reproductive health care hurts whole communities, degrades public health and results in more deaths. This policy is abominable, and I'll overturn it on day one of my presidency.

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: Here's a radical idea: Instead of a game of political piñata with our planet's future, let's have a real debate about the #GreenNewDeal. We're talking about infrastructure, job creation and clean air and water—and if Republicans don't support that, they should explain why.

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text:
Today's #GreenNewDeal vote is a partisan stunt to side-step needed debate on climate action, and give Republicans cover to put oil lobby checks over our kids. I've come to expect nothing less from @senatemajldr.

I'll be voting "present." I don't play ball with bad-faith farces.

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: Couldn't agree more.

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: The people of this country deserve a president worthy of your bravery. That's why I’m running for President of the United States.

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: If it’s a fight for healthcare this administration wants, it’s a fight they’ll get—and we will win.

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text:
Find me a so-called unsolvable problem, and I will point you to the dark, unaccountable money in its way—whether it's opioid makers getting a pass instead of indictments, or the NRA stopping gun reform. 

We need to crack open our government and let the light flood in.

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: What don’t you want the American people to see, @senatemajldr?

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: Americans across party lines agree that we need paid leave for every worker. New Hampshire voters chose leaders who campaigned on it, including @GovChrisSununu. He is wrong to renege on that promise. Granite Staters deserve paid leave.

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text:
Two survivors of the Parkland shooting and one parent of a child killed at Sandy Hook have died by suicide in the past week. Tragic doesn't begin to cover it.

The trauma of this violence doesn't end when the news cycle moves on. We have to fix this.

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text:
Yesterday, we joined together in New York City to reject hate and fear, and to show that when we speak out, lock arms and fight for our values, brave wins.

Read my full speech from our official campaign kickoff rally: https://medium.com/@SenGillibrand/brave-wins-3afdb61983ea?source=linkShare-7d655378f079-1553524614 …

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: What a day.

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: President Trump is a coward. That's not what America deserves. We deserve a president who is brave.

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: The Mueller report must be made public. Not just a letter from someone appointed by Trump to protect himself—all of it. The President works for the people, and he is not above the law.

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: Thank you, New York!

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text:
This fight is so much bigger than any one election—it’s about making a choice and deciding who we are. So will we defend this democracy? Will we reject hate and fear? Will we be brave?

If you’re with me, chip in and let's win this fight: https://secure.actblue.com/donate/kg-social?refcode=tw-032419 … #BraveWins

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text:
Years from now, we will look back on this moment in our history, and we’ll be able to say that we did something about it.

We stood up, locked arms and proved to America—and the world—that when people come together to drive out darkness, hope rises.

Fear loses.

And #BraveWins.

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text:
None of these big fights will be easy. But I’ve never backed down from a fight for what’s right, and I’m not about to start now.

That’s why I’m in this race. I'm running for president to fix what’s been broken, repair our moral fabric and rebuild our common bonds.

#BraveWins

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text:
We need to treat climate change like the existential threat it is and pass a #GreenNewDeal. Let’s make it our generation’s moonshot. Addressing a global challenge of this urgency will take massive effort and transformative vision—which is exactly why we should do it.

#BraveWins

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text:
We must hold accountable any threats to our democracy.

The Mueller report must be made public. Nobody is above the law. I don’t often agree with Richard Nixon, but he was right to say the American people have a right to know whether or not their president is a crook.

#BraveWins

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text:
We need to restore our moral leadership in the world. We must secure our borders effectively and fight terrorism relentlessly, but let’s be very clear: Racism and fear are not a national security strategy.

#BraveWins

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text:
We need to dismantle institutional racism.
 
We need solutions both targeted and broad—like higher standards for maternity care, a national commitment to full employment, postal banking, ending cash bail and legalizing marijuana.

#BraveWins

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text:
Hear me when I say this: Paid leave, equal pay and affordable daycare are not just “women’s issues.” These are economic issues—ones that will determine whether or not our country succeeds. 

#BraveWins

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text:
Our goals are ambitious, but they shouldn't be controversial:

Medicare for all.
Universal pre-K and high-quality public education.
Affordable college.
Full employment.
A $15 minimum wage.
National paid leave.

#BraveWins

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text:
As president, I will fight for publicly-funded federal elections. It would change the way Washington works overnight. Imagine your voice being just as loud as the Koch brothers—what a concept!

We have to level the political playing field so our democracy can thrive.

#BraveWins

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text:
Right now, special interests are displacing the voices of the people in our democracy. Find me a so-called unsolvable problem, and I'll point you to the greed and corruption in the way.

We need to crack open our government, flip the switch and let the light flood in.

#BraveWins

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text:
I’m fighting for an America where where compassion and integrity define our government, not self-interest and corruption. Where we don’t just care about the profits we make today, but the future we’re leaving to our grandchildren.

I know we can be that America.

#BraveWins

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text:
I stood up to greed and voted against the bank bailout.

I stood up to corruption in Congress.

I stood up to the Pentagon, Congress and colleges on behalf of survivors of sexual assault.
 
And I’m proud to have stood up to Trump more than anyone else in the Senate.

#BraveWins

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text:
My grandmother Polly taught me that being brave doesn’t just mean standing up for yourself—it means standing up for other people who need you. 

Bravery means standing up to the powerful, and summoning the courage to confront them head on. And that's what I've done.

#BraveWins

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text:
Day in and day out, Americans are making a choice to resist the backward pull of this administration, and pushing us toward a better future.

The people of this country deserve a president worthy of your bravery. That's why I’m running for president.

#BraveWins

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text:
We deserve a president who is brave. A president who inspires us to stand for something greater than ourselves.

We don’t build walls; we build bridges. Because our unity of purpose lifts us higher than any tower.

#BraveWins

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text:
President Trump is tearing apart the moral fabric of this country. He demonizes the vulnerable and he punches down. He puts his name in bold on every building.

He does all of this because he wants us to believe he is strong. He is not. Our President is a coward.

#BraveWins

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text:
Brave isn’t winning right now.

Brave doesn’t spread hate or bully the vulnerable. 
Brave doesn’t put greed and self-interest over millions of lives. 
Brave doesn’t cower behind lies and walls. 
Brave doesn’t pit people against one another. That’s what fear does.

#BraveWins

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: “Kirsten’s dedication isn’t just to my son, it’s to your sons and daughters, to you, and to all of us. She cannot be knocked down. And she listens. That is what we need to lead us out of the storm.” —@conniebritton, actor and activist #BraveWins

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: #BraveWins. Tune in live now for our campaign kickoff rally in NYC!

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: “We are all brave enough to fight. I am proud to be here to tell you that there is no other candidate that is more prepared to invest and empower all of the American people than your NY Senator, Kirsten Gillibrand.” —Andrea Pino-Silva, anti-sexual assault activist #BraveWins

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: “We owe it to our world, to our country, to our children, to the people who fought for this—to ensure that our fight never ends. To ensure that the bravery of New Yorkers helps lead the country once again.” —Gabriel Blau, LGBTQ rights activist #BraveWins

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: “I want to see someone elected as president who is unafraid to stand up and bring us closer to LGBT equity and equality.” —Tanya Asapansa-Johnson Walker, transgender rights activist #BraveWins

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: “Before Senator Gillibrand, we did not have any hope. Now we have hope. We are feeling brave. We know there’s somebody standing with us and being a voice for the voiceless.” —Jackie Rowe-Adams, gun safety advocate #BraveWins

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: “Bravery isn’t always loud. Sometimes bravery is quiet and isn’t in the headlines. Sometimes bravery listens.” —Annie Clark, anti-sexual assault activist #BraveWins

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: “Hate will be defeated. Brave will win. Families belong together.” —Monica Sibri, Dreamer and immigrant rights activist #BraveWins

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: “My fight is your fight. Your fight is my fight. And our fight is her fight.” —Lisdy Contreras-Giron, Dreamer and immigrant rights activist #BraveWins

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: Kirsten’s team here—follow along starting now for highlights from Kirsten’s official campaign kickoff rally in New York City! #BraveWins

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: Beautiful day for a campaign kickoff! #BraveWins

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: Setting the stage for a campaign rally that’s all about fighting for what’s right, no matter who we’re up against. #BraveWins

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: Whether you're coming to our kickoff rally in New York at noon or following along online, here's a sneak preview of the soundtrack! Listen to our official campaign playlist on @Spotify: https://open.spotify.com/user/xiqp723sgft3dosx8b0izgd2s/playlist/79xcUMTjOly2Ezfv456zWr?si=A0-XCuOVSX2mYFTfTy-54g … #BraveWins

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: Hello, New York!

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text:
Today’s the day we show America that #BraveWins, and fear loses.

If you’re in New York City, join us at noon in front of Trump International for our campaign kickoff rally: https://www.mobilize.us/kirstengillibrand/event/88230/?utm_source=social_0324 …

If you aren’t, follow along here as we share our vision for the future. Let's go!

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text:
On November 3, 2020, we will send a resounding rebuke to Donald Trump and vote him out of office. 

And tomorrow, we'll put him on notice by standing up for our values and sharing our vision, right in his front yard. Join us in NYC at noon ET: https://www.mobilize.us/kirstengillibrand/event/88230/?utm_source=social_0323 … #BraveWins

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: When I studied abroad in China, @conniebritton was right beside me. In our decades of friendship, she's continued to inspire me as an activist to combat poverty and advance equal rights for women on top of her career as an actor. I'm so glad she'll be with us tomorrow. #BraveWins

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: Monica Sibri believes that representation matters, and that’s why she’s fighting to elect young women and standing up for Dreamers like herself. Monica's being brave and showing her communities how to be brave too. #BraveWins

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: When Annie Clark saw firsthand that colleges weren’t doing enough to protect students from sexual assault, she filed a Title IX complaint to hold her school accountable—and won. Her bravery helped kickstart a national movement to end sexual assault on campuses. #BraveWins

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: Tanya Asapansa-Johnson Walker has embodied bravery in more ways than one—from serving in the US Army to serving marginalized transgender people to fighting for the rights of women, LGBTQ people and the undocumented. I'm honored to have her with me tomorrow. #BraveWins

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: It takes extraordinary bravery for a sexual assault survivor to tell their story. Andrea Pino-Silva did, and then she kept going. She helped lead a nationwide charge to combat sexual assault on college campuses by changing policies and empowering survivors. #BraveWins

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: Gabriel Blau has spent his career fighting so that all families are treated with respect and equality. Being brave means standing up for others in addition to yourself—Gabriel acts on those values. #BraveWins

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: Lisdy Contreras-Giron is a Dreamer in every sense of the word. She came to the US at 5, and now she's getting her law degree to help marginalized people. She uses her voice to advocate for equal opportunity for everyone, no matter where you came from. That’s bravery. #BraveWins

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: When Jackie Rowe-Adams lost two of her sons to gun violence, she turned her unimaginable pain into action. She formed a group of moms and other safety advocates dedicated to ending gun violence in Harlem. Jackie chose to be brave, and New York is better for it. #BraveWins

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text:
Exciting news: I'm honored that I'll be joined by some inspiring people on stage at our campaign kickoff rally tomorrow in New York City. Today we'll introduce those people, and their stories of everyday bravery.

RSVP to the rally here: https://www.mobilize.us/kirstengillibrand/event/88230/?utm_source=social_0323 … #BraveWins

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: If we're going to make our economy work for families, we have to transform the infrastructure of work to make it easier to be a parent AND make a living. We need equal pay for equal work, affordable daycare for all and national paid leave. It's 2019. Let's get this done.

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: Whatever Mueller's report contains, here's what we already know: Trump has spread hate, clouded truth, sown division and undermined our democracy. On Sunday, we'll send him a message that says: Your time is up. Join us at noon at Trump International:

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: Special counsel Mueller’s report should be made public without any delay. The American people have a right to know its findings.

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: Let's put aside the overreaching, fake national emergency for a minute. How does Trump intend to pay for his pointless wall and tax cuts for millionaires? By cutting $845 billion from Medicare, $26B from Social Security, and $200B from student loan programs. It's all wrong.

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: The best way to provide national paid leave is to make it an earned benefit, just like Social Security. Under my plan, you and your employer would each pay in $2/week, and you'd get 12 weeks of paid leave. It's that simple.

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text:
On Sunday, we get to share our vision for the future and show America what this campaign is fighting for—right in Donald Trump's front yard. 

Trump International, New York City, 12 pm. Join us:

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: Good to be back in Iowa. Do you like my new workout shirt?

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text:
One of the many problems with Trump is Betsy DeVos. She's unqualified and unfit for the job, and that's why I voted against her nomination.

The Department of Education needs to protect students, not predatory lenders and sexual abusers. Enforcing Title IX shouldn't be optional.

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
