name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: I'm hard-pressed to think of any policy more cruel—and more hypocritical for a party that claims to have family values—than cutting lifelines for low-income children. We are not going to let kids go hungry so Trump can pay for his tax cuts for billionaires.

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: Student debt is one of the biggest crises we have in this country today. The federal government should not be making money off the backs of our students.

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: Tens of thousands of Americans are killed with guns every year. Many are kids. There's no excuse for the NRA's chokehold on our laws; even gun owners want background checks. Someone has to protect the children of this country against the danger your greed puts them in. I will.

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text:
What's happening at our border is inhumane and intolerable, and it doesn't make us safer. These are refugees and asylum seekers. We need to secure our border in smart ways, end family separation and create a real path to citizenship.

There is no such thing as an illegal human.

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: White supremacy and hate crimes are on the rise around the world. Donald Trump didn't create them, but he has poured gasoline on that fire, and his hate has made us all less safe. I refuse to let it go unchecked. I will stand up to him and I will fight for the best of our values.

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: Tonight, I talked to Michiganders about why I'm the best candidate to take on President Trump and fight for our values. If you liked what you heard, chip in $3 to help make sure I can share that vision at the Democratic primary debates: http://kirstengillibrand.com/townhall  #GillibrandTownHall

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: Donald Trump's hatred makes us less safe. His Muslim ban makes us less safe. So I will protect this country. I will make sure that we are safe, but I will make sure that we remember that we are at our best when we love one another. #GillibrandTownHall

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: Donald Trump did not create hate and racism, bigotry and anti-Semitism. But what he has done is poured fuel on the fire that is raging more than I've seen in my lifetime. I will stand up against him and his hate. #GillibrandTownHall

name: Kirsten Gillibrand

text: Clean air and clean water is a human right. I’ve made clean water one of my priorities, including the PIPES Act. We should make polluters pay for the damage they inflict on communities, and stop rolling back EPA regulations. #GillibrandTownHall

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text:
There is no such thing as an illegal human.

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: Health care should be a right, not a privilege. We need a president who'll fight for universal, quality coverage that's affordable for everybody. I believe we need #MedicareForAll, and that we should create a public option as a transition to single-payer. #GillibrandTownHall

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: Student debt is an out-of-control crisis in this country, and it isn’t just a burden on individual graduates—it’s a drag on the whole economy. #GillibrandTownHall

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: America is the only industrialized country in the world without a national paid leave plan. It's 2019. Let's make this a priority at last. #GillibrandTownHall

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text:
Rewarding work means a few things to me:
We need to support unions and workers' rights.
We need to raise the minimum wage to $15.
We need to invest in job training.
We need national paid leave. 
And we need to punish companies who outsource American jobs. #GillibrandTownHall

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: America is facing an opioid crisis, and one of the ways we need to put a stop to it is by holding opioid makers accountable for their greed. They knowingly put their profits over people's lives, and they should be prosecuted. #GillibrandTownHall

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: We need to get money out of politics because the way Washington works is that the powerful have unlimited power, and money is the name of the game. If we want change, we need to stand up to the powerful special interests and restore the people's voices. #GillibrandTownHall

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: We all have a responsibility to end gun violence in this country. We all have to take on the corruption and greed that the NRA represents. It is unacceptable, and I will hold them accountable. #GillibrandTownHall

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: I’m the best candidate to take on Trump because I have the vision of what needs to be done in America. I’ve listened to voters about their lives, and I have the compassion to absorb that and offer a real plan. I have the experience and I’ve gotten things done. #GillibrandTownHall

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: We need a leader who makes big, bold, brave choices. That’s why I’m running for president. Join me and let's build this movement together: http://kirstengillibrand.com/join

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text:
Every generation of Americans has to make a choice: Will we accept an agenda of cowardice and division, or will brave win? 

Join me at Trump International in New York City on Sunday, March 24 and let’s show which side we’re on:

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text:
The decision-making in our government is going to the highest bidder. We need to get unaccountable money out of our politics and restore the principle of one person, one vote.

We’re fighting to restore power to people, so we’re powered by people. http://kirstengillibrand.com/donate

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: New campaign, new store! Get your shirts, stickers, tote bags and more to show you’re on our team: http://store.kirstengillibrand.com

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text:
We need to remember what it feels like to be brave. Brave doesn’t pit people against each other or put money over lives. It doesn’t spread hate, cloud truth or build a wall. That’s what fear does. 

I'm running because we're better than that. Let's be brave together.

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: I can't think of many other people who better define what "brave" means to me. Thank you, my friend and hero.

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: Whether you’re with me all the way or just want to learn more about what I’m fighting for, I want you to be part of this campaign. Text BRAVE to 60980 to get text updates and hear about how you can do something brave, too!

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: It’s time to answer cowardice with bravery. Fear with boldness. Greed with compassion. Let’s win this fight together: http://kirstengillibrand.com/join

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: We’re building a campaign that will change who’s at the decision-making table, take on powerful interests and restore moral integrity to the White House—and we won't take a cent from corporate PACs or federal lobbyists. Donate to help power this campaign:

name: Kirsten Gillibrand
text: I’m fighting for an America where we lead with bravery and compassion, not fear and greed—and I’m taking that fight straight to President Trump’s doorstep. Join me at Trump International in New York City on Sunday, March 24: https://www.mobilize.us/kirstengillibrand/event/88230/ …

name: Mike Gravel
text: And because the new elite ostensibly owes its position to merit, rather than inherited privilege, it feels no sense of noblesse oblige that older aristocracies felt; as Christopher Lasch pointed out, there is no valor or chivalry in the new system, just Darwinian triumph.

name: Mike Gravel
text: Professional Democrats and elite journalists are largely in thrall to the cult of meritocracy, which is the solidification and beautification of inequality. It is inequality based on socially-defined merit—but inequality nonetheless. It is “talent” made god.

text: It’s time we had a leader who speaks out against hate in all its forms.

text: Did you know our campaign does not accept money from corporate PACs and federal lobbyists? We’re building a truly grassroots-powered movement here and we rely on your support. Chip in to join us.

name: Kamala Harris
text:
Our party is not white or Black...Hispanic or Asian...immigrant or indigenous. It is all of us.

This is our Party. This is the America we believe in.

And it’s the America I’ll always fight for as President. #NAACPDetroit

name: Kamala Harris
text: When Black churches are burned to the ground in Louisiana - that is terrorism. 2018 was the deadliest year on record for domestic terrorism since the Oklahoma City Bombing more than 20 years ago. And as President, I won’t feed it. I won’t ignore it. And I won’t tolerate it.

name: Kamala Harris
text: When Black worshipers are gunned down during Bible study in Charleston - that is terrorism. When a bomb is set off at a mosque in Minnesota - that is terrorism. When a man shoots up a synagogue yelling anti-Semitic slurs - that is terrorism. #NAACPDetroit

name: Kamala Harris
text:
It’s time we had a leader who speaks out against hate in all its forms. 

It’s time we had a President who’s not scared to call neo-Nazi violence what it is: domestic terrorism.

I know we are better than this. #NAACPDetroit

name: Kamala Harris
text: Let’s speak truth here today - this President isn’t trying to make America great, he’s trying to make America hate. #NAACPDetroit

name: Kamala Harris
text: Right now we have a President who would rather give a teacher a gun than give a teacher a raise. That must end. #NAACPDetroit

name: Kamala Harris
text: And let's be clear -- there are two groups of people raising our children: parents, often with the assistance of grandparents & aunties and uncles, and our teachers. Teachers are helping to raise the next generation of leaders and we are not paying them their value. #NAACPDetroit

name: Kamala Harris
text: It's been 65 years since Emmett Till, 52 years since three young Black men were killed at the Algiers Motel and seven years since Trayvon Martin. Yet, this is still everyday life for young Black people in America. Let's speak that truth. #NAACPDetroit

name: Kamala Harris
text: We have a criminal justice system that is deeply flawed, infected with bias, and in need of reform. #NAACPDetroit

name: Kamala Harris
text: The truth is, we need a new Voting Rights Act in this country with automatic voter registration, Election Day as a national holiday, and we need to fight back against Republicans who suppress our constitutional right to vote. #NAACPDetroit

name: Kamala Harris
text: Let’s say this loud and clear - without voter suppression: @staceyabrams is Governor Stacey Abrams. @AndrewGillum is Governor Andrew Gillum. #NAACPDetroit

name: Kamala Harris
text: Our right to vote, the very foundation of our democracy, is under attack. #NAACPDetroit

name: Kamala Harris
text: When people ask me “How are you going to pay for middle-class tax cuts?” I'll tell you - I’m going to repeal that Trump trillion dollar tax cut that benefitted the top 1% and the biggest corporations in our country. #NAACPDetroit

name: Kamala Harris
text: As President, I’ll pass the largest tax cut for middle-class and working families in a generation. Families making less than $100,000 a year would receive $6,000 that they can access at up to $500 a month. #NAACPDetroit

name: Kamala Harris
text: That is what I have done from the first day I walked into the San Francisco DA’s office, from the first day I walked into the California AG's office, from the first day I walked into the U.S. Senate, and that is what I will do the first day I walk into the Oval Office.

name: Kamala Harris
text: The system is in need of reform—so let’s have people on the inside prepared to use their power to open doors and prepared to implement the agenda to make the system more fair and just. #NAACPDetroit

text: The Detroit NAACP has been at the forefront of the fight for justice - from taking on school desegregatation to housing discrimination to voter suppression. You are a national model. #NAACPDetroit

name: Kamala Harris
text: I’d like to wish a blessed Ramadan to Muslims observing around the world. It’s a time for reflection, compassion, and patience. Ramadan Kareem.

name: Kamala Harris
text: It’s past time our leaders recognize that our country faces a mental health crisis. I introduced legislation in the Senate to increase access to mental health care services and will continue to make it a priority when elected president.

name: Kamala Harris
text: I’m fed up with the inaction on gun violence. People are dying. Too many lives have been lost and too many communities are left to heal. We need leaders who will address this horrifying epidemic and have the courage to speak up.

name: Kamala Harris
text: We cannot wait for our broken health care system to fix itself. It’s on us to fight so that access to health care is never seen as a luxury again. Let’s make Medicare for All a reality.

name: Kamala Harris
text: Nia, Cheslie, and Kaliegh: you are trailblazers, creating your own path on your own terms. Congratulations.

text: America is one of the wealthiest countries in the world, but many of our students still go hungry and into debt as they try and pay for a quality education.

name: Kamala Harris

name: Kamala Harris
text: May is #MentalHealthMonth. We are facing a mental health crisis in our nation, yet too many Americans aren't receiving the treatment they need due to lack of access or stigma. Mental health is just as important as physical health. It’s on us to change the narrative.

name: Kamala Harris
text: Floods have ravaged Western and Eastern Iowa over the last few months. The @RedCross and @AmeriCorps are two great organizations lending a hand. The recovery will be long, please consider chipping in today. I know every dollar will help.

name: Kamala Harris
text: John Kelly was the architect of the Trump Administration's cruel child separation policy. Now he will profit off the separation of families. It's unethical. We are better than this.

name: Kamala Harris
text: Women, people of color, people with disabilities, and LGBTQ Americans are often underrepresented in STEM jobs. Fixing the problem starts with investing in our classrooms. That is why I’ve introduced a bill to build a pipeline of diverse talent for these good-paying jobs.

name: Kamala Harris
text:
As my mother always said, “You may be the first to do many things, but make sure you are not the last.” 

Thank you @LenaWaithe and @GPBmadeit for speaking out about why it’s so important to be a mentor and lift others up.

name: Kamala Harris
text: Today, on #WorldPressFreedomDay, we honor journalists for playing a critical role in defending our democracy both at home and abroad. There are consequences to Trump's hateful rhetoric against the press.

name: Kamala Harris
text: My mother was the biggest source of inspiration in my life. Born in India, she came to the U.S. to study at UC Berkeley, and became a breast cancer researcher. This #APAHM, I will highlight people like my mother who have made this world a better place.

name: Kamala Harris
text: This is exactly why we need Medicare for All. People can't afford their insurance, and too many are having to choose between paying the bills or putting food on the table. This is unacceptable. Let’s make health care a right in this country.

text: It should be deeply troubling to all Americans that Attorney General Barr made a decision about the sitting president and obstruction of justice without reviewing the evidence. This Attorney General lacks all credibility.

text: Dana, a CO teacher, would sometimes rent her apartment and sleep in her car just to make ends meet. It's infuriating what our teachers must sacrifice just to survive. When I'm president, teachers will get the raise they deserve.

text: Attorney General Barr has weakened our standing in the world. He's undermined our democracy. He must resign.

name: Kamala Harris
text: This isn’t sustainable. We can’t keep relocating our cities — we must fix the problem. Another reason why the United States must act now, rejoin the Paris Agreement, and pass the Green New Deal.

name: Kamala Harris
text: Yesterday in North and South Carolina, teachers stood up and demanded to be heard. It's time to pay them their value and show them the dignity and respect they deserve for helping raise our kids. I stand in solidarity with them in this fight.

name: Kamala Harris
text: I’m running for president to pursue justice for the American people. We need the full truth about Russian interference in the 2016 elections, not an abridged, watered-down version from this Administration. If you’re with me in this fight, pitch in now:

name: Kamala Harris
text: As I see it, there is a “conflict of interest” in the Mueller investigation: President Trump has an interest in obstructing justice, and Robert Mueller has an interest in pursuing justice. Attorney General Barr has chosen to side with the President. He needs to go.

name: Kamala Harris
text: This Holocaust Remembrance Day, we honor the memory of the six million Jews murdered in the Holocaust. We must renew our commitment to the promise of “never again” and fight against hate and anti-Semitism every time we see it.

name: Kamala Harris
text: Remember their names: Riley Howell and Ellis Parlier. We don't need another tragedy, we need action.

name: Kamala Harris
text: Our democracy is being tested. We have an Attorney General protecting the President instead of pursuing justice for the American people. That needs to change.

name: Kamala Harris
text: For someone who calls the Mueller report his "baby," the Attorney General didn't spend a lot of time looking at its underlying evidence. He failed to tell the American people the truth. It's time for Attorney General Barr to resign.

name: Kamala Harris
text: I’m running for president because the American people deserve truth and integrity from their elected leaders. That’s not what we’re getting right now. If you’re with me in this fight, I need you now:

name: Kamala Harris
text: What I just saw from the Attorney General is unacceptable. Barr must resign now.

name: Kamala Harris
text: On International Workers’ Day, we must fight to build a nation where the dignity of work is respected. Where everyone can keep a roof over their head and pay the bills. We must stand up and protect the rights of hard-working Americans.

name: Kamala Harris
text: Today, teachers in South Carolina are marching for fair wages and improved working conditions. I stand with them. As president, I will raise the average teacher pay in South Carolina by 19%, reduce teacher turnover, and ensure our teachers are paid their worth. #SCforEd

name: Kamala Harris
text: The rising cost of housing disproportionately impacts Black and Latinx communities. Having a safe place to live and raise your family is not just about shelter, it's about dignity. The Rent Relief Act would make that dignity possible for millions of families.

text: From day one, I made a commitment to you: Our campaign will reject all contributions from corporate PACs and federal lobbyists. We’re counting on real people to power our campaign. Chip in #ForThePeople now:

name: Kamala Harris
text: This is outrageous: Sixty of America’s largest corporations paid zero federal taxes. Zero. As president, I’ll lift up those who need it most — the middle class — and ensure corporations pay their fair share. Our economy shouldn’t be built on the backs of working people.

text: My thoughts are with everyone in the Davenport community tonight who is affected by the floods — praying for everyone's safety.

text: Read this powerful testimony from the courageous activist @AdyBarkan on why our nation needs #MedicareForAll. Ady, from the bottom of my heart, thank you for speaking out.

name: Kamala Harris
text: Health care is a human right. It shouldn’t matter where you live, how much money you make, or whether you have a pre-existing condition. It’s incumbent we make that right a reality with Medicare for All.

text: As president, I’ll work with Sens @Claire4Iowa, @ZachWahls, and Kinney, as well as other leaders, to make affordable housing a reality for Iowa families. I am committed to this cause.

name: Kamala Harris
text: It’s been almost 10 years and the federal minimum wage is still $7.25/hour. That’s $15,000 a year in this country—not nearly enough to keep a roof over your head. We have to speak truth: This system isn’t working for working people. That’s why I’m fighting for a $15 minimum wage.

name: Kamala Harris
text: Better pay for teachers, Medicare for All, and debt-free college. These are some of the issues we fight for at this election. If you can, help our campaign to ensure we build a better, brighter future for our country:

name: Kamala Harris
text: When Susan got sick, she had to delay critical annual screenings until she and her husband paid off their previous medical bills. Her story is all too common in America. We must pass Medicare for All.

name: Kamala Harris
text: My first-grade teacher, Mrs. Wilson, sparked my love for learning and became a lifelong mentor and friend. She even attended my law school graduation. There are Mrs. Wilson’s all across this country who deserve a raise. It’s time we give them one.

name: Kamala Harris
text: Our young people are dying every day because of senseless gun violence. Republicans don’t have the courage to stand up to the NRA. I do. We need to elect a president who is committed to keeping our children and communities safe from gun violence:

name: Kamala Harris
text: Our campaign isn’t funded by corporate PACs or federal lobbyists. We can’t change our broken campaign finance system unless we lead with our values. Every dollar you give can help us hire more staff and visit more states:

name: Kamala Harris
text: This is the world we live in. Our children should never have to be experts in what to do during a mass shooting. I'm a proud co-sponsor of S. 42. If Congress fails to pass it within my first 100 days as president, I'll take executive action myself.

name: Kamala Harris
text: From Merrimack, NH to Oscoda, MI, communities across the U.S. are suffering from water contamination. I'm troubled to hear reports that the EPA will weaken standards for chemicals polluting water supplies. Everyone needs access to clean drinking water.

name: Kamala Harris
text: More than a year and a half ago, Hurricane Maria devastated Puerto Rico. It’s appalling that thousands of children on the Island show signs of PTSD. Our government failed them and it’s on us to ensure something like this never happens again.

name: Kamala Harris
text: Labor has lifted up working Americans. Built the middle class. Brought us the five-day work week. When organized labor is attacked, working people suffer. : @CAPAction @SEIU

name: Kamala Harris
text: The maternal mortality rate in our nation is worse than it was 25 years ago. The risk of death from pregnancy-related causes is 3-4x higher for Black women than for white women. My Maternal CARE Act will help solve this epidemic.

name: Kamala Harris
text: Thank you @CuyahogaDems for having me tonight! Glad to be in Cleveland to discuss how we restore opportunity for all Americans and elect Democrats up and down the ticket.

name: Kamala Harris
text: Anti-Semitism has no place in our country.

text: Trump and his Administration are trying to push immigrant families back into the shadows. This is unacceptable.

name: Kamala Harris
text: Right now in this country, we have students excelling in science who want to become teachers — they want to teach but they can’t. My plan will close the teacher pay gap and finally ensure teachers are paid their worth.

text: Yet again a place of worship is the target of senseless gun violence and hate. Anti-Semitism is real in this country and we must not be silent - enough is enough. My heart aches for the Chabad of Poway synagogue and the Jewish community.

name: Kamala Harris
text: .@chefjoseandres’ humanitarian work nourishes the soul and the world. Congratulations on a well-earned key to the Las Vegas Strip. Let's swap recipes next time you're in town.

name: Kamala Harris
text:
No corporate PACs. 
No federal lobbyists. 

Our campaign is powered by people just like you. It would mean a lot if you chipped in a dollar or two:

text: We must stand up for labor’s right to collectively bargain. No one should have to fight their fight alone. When I am president, workers everywhere will have a fighter in the White House. #WorkersForum

name: Kamala Harris
text: The working people who are members of @SEIU live a life of service for other people. Service is some of the most noble work you can do. You are why I fight hard for workers rights, now and when I'm in the White House. #WorkersForum

text: Our economy isn’t working for working people. I'm proud throughout my career to have stood on the picket line with organized labor. I'm proud to have stood with teachers in Oakland. There is still so much work to be done, both through legislation and in the White House.

name: Kamala Harris
text: We must make paid family leave a reality for all Americans. No one should have to rely on the kindness of their colleagues when their kids need them the most.

text:

We can't let that happen. 

We must stop this President so that millions of Americans don't lose their insurance and protections for their pre-existing conditions.

name: Kamala Harris
text: How dangerous is President Trump on guns? He made it easier for fugitives to buy guns, and thousands of gun sales have been approved for individuals with outstanding arrest warrants since he made that change. This won't happen when I'm President.

name: Kamala Harris
text: Millions of guns are sold every year without background checks. This is dangerous. You might want to know, before someone purchases a gun, if they’ve committed a violent felony. We need a president with the courage to take bold, decisive action to save lives.

text: How do we get voters out to the polls? Invest in community leadership. #SheThePeople2020

name: Kamala Harris
text: Our justice system continues to target and imprison young Black and Latinx Americans at high levels due to outdated, unjust marijuana laws. I’ve said it once and I’ll say it again: we must legalize marijuana across the country.

name: Kamala Harris
text: When my mother got sick, she had the benefit of having Medicare, but not everybody does. High costs should not be a barrier to health care. Medicare for All is the solution.

name: Kamala Harris
text: We need to reduce barriers to voting so more voices are heard at the ballot box. Automatic voter registration works and must be implemented nationwide.

name: Kamala Harris
text: I’m not afraid to stand up to the NRA and the gun lobby to enact common-sense solutions to combat the gun violence epidemic in our country.

name: Kamala Harris
text: Together we stand for Medicare for All, debt-free college, and affordable housing. But we can't do it alone. Your donations power our campaign and ensure we can fight for a better future.

text: Too often, Black parents have to sit their Black sons down and tell them they may be stopped, arrested, chased, or even shot because of the color of their skin. We must reform our criminal justice system.

text: It’s been five years and Flint residents still aren’t able to trust they have clean drinking water. America is one of the wealthiest countries on the planet. It’s a disgrace that we can’t guarantee access to clean water for everyone. I will never forget about the people of Flint.

name: Kamala Harris
text: Right now in America the federal minimum wage is $7.25/hour, averaging about $15,000 a year. When the majority of minimum wage workers are women, we can’t deny the fact that this isn’t enough to feed your family or pay for childcare. Time to raise the wage to $15.

name: Kamala Harris
text: Some will say my plan to combat gun violence is “too bold.” As president, if Congress continues to bury its head in the sand, I will act. Too many people have died for us to wait any longer.

name: Kamala Harris
text: We must take climate change seriously and act with a sense of urgency. The clock is ticking and we can do something about it. I support the #GreenNewDeal because every day we wait is a day we fail future generations.

name: Kamala Harris
text: Loopholes in our system mean millions of guns are sold each year with no questions asked. This is a danger to our families, this is a danger to our communities.

name: Kamala Harris
text:
Our nation faces an unprecedented shortage of teachers. The teacher wage gap is one of the reasons why — and it just got worse. As president, I would enact the largest federal investment in teacher pay in American history.

name: Kamala Harris
text: As the marijuana industry continues to grow, there are people of color sitting behind bars for doing the exact same thing. It's time we changed the system. #SheThePeople2020

name: Kamala Harris
text:
Teachers don’t need a gun. They need a raise. 

We have to give them the resources they need to educate the next generation of leaders.

name: Kamala Harris
text: Nearly 1 million women in the U.S. alive today have been shot, or shot at, by an intimate partner. We’ve had too many tragedies for addressing gun violence to not be a priority.

text: Let’s speak truth to power. Right now in the United States, access to opportunity depends on your race or gender or what zip code you are born in. It doesn’t have to be that way. Let’s build an America where everyone has the chance to succeed. Chip in:

name: Kamala Harris
text:
A stunning statistic: In 2015, 92% of all women killed by guns in high-income countries lived in the United States. 

92%. 

That is shameful. I will close the “boyfriend loophole” and prevent dating partners convicted of domestic violence from purchasing guns.

name: Kamala Harris
text: Every day, 100 Americans are killed by guns. Gun violence is a national epidemic. It’s time we take action. Last night I announced executive actions I intend to take as president if Congress refuses to act.

name: Kamala Harris
text: We cannot wait any longer to keep our children safe. We must act now.

name: Kamala Harris
text: The leading cause of death for young Black men is gun violence. It outpaces the next nine leading causes combined. This is a national tragedy. We need to act. If Congress won’t, I will.

name: Kamala Harris
text: It is clear: Evidence in the Mueller report points to obstruction of justice. The first step of our constitutional responsibility is to start the impeachment process in the House. We must hold this president accountable.

name: Kamala Harris
text:
My plan to stand up to the NRA if Congress won’t:
Mandate near-universal background checks
Revoke the licenses of gun dealers who break the law
Ensure fugitives from justice can’t purchase guns
Close the “Boyfriend Loophole” to prevent domestic abusers from buying guns

name: Kamala Harris
text: In 2017 alone, nearly 40,000 Americans were killed by guns. This is a national epidemic. If Congress fails to act to address it in my first 100 days, I will take executive action to keep our kids and communities safe.

name: Kamala Harris
text: Enough → http://kamalaharris.org/gunviolence .

name: Kamala Harris
text: If Congress fails to act on gun violence within my first 100 days in office, here’s my promise to you: I will take executive action to keep our kids and communities safe. Add your name next to mine to join me in this fight:

name: Kamala Harris
text: If Congress doesn’t pass gun safety legislation in the first 100 days of my presidency, I will take executive action to keep our communities safe.

name: Kamala Harris
text: Republicans in Washington don’t have the courage to stand up to the NRA — but I do. Visit http://kamalaharris.org/gunviolence  to learn more.

name: Kamala Harris
text: Right now we have a president who is putting in place a process for discharging transgender men and women. It is absolutely unconscionable and that is something I would reverse immediately when I am elected president of the United States. #HarrisTownHall

name: Kamala Harris
text: When the chatter among a lot of Democrats was about civil unions, I was marrying same-sex couples at San Francisco City Hall. #HarrisTownHall

name: Kamala Harris
text: Russia interfered in the election of the president of the United States. It's time we strengthen our election systems to prevent the next attack.  This will be a war without blood. And we are not prepared. And we must be.

name: Kamala Harris
text: 100 Americans are killed by guns every single day. Gun violence is a national epidemic and it’s time we take action. Tonight I announced the executive actions I intend to take in my first 100 days as president if Congress refuses to act.

name: Kamala Harris
text: In just one hour I’ll take the stage at our @CNN Town Hall. I can’t wait to discuss the issues that matter — how we can make the economy work for everyone, giving our nation’s educators a raise, and more.

name: Kamala Harris
text: In 99% of the counties in America today, a full-time minimum wage worker cannot afford rent on a one bedroom apartment. That is indefensible. My bill, the Rent Relief Act, would ease the anxiety of rising rents and give workers a much-needed break.

name: Kamala Harris
text: Over 31,000 Stop & Shop workers and their families stood together when their wages, retirement benefits, and health care were at risk — and won. This is a victory for workers everywhere.

name: Kamala Harris
text: At an HBCU, you are told that you can be whatever you want to be — there is nothing holding you back from success. Attending @HowardU was one of the most influential decisions of my life and I love meeting current and former HBCU students on the road.

name: Kamala Harris
text:
Earth Day is a reminder that we only have one planet. There is no Planet B. 

We must address the climate crisis and elect a president willing to stand up to polluters and act to protect our environment. Not just for ourselves, but for future generations.

name: Kamala Harris
text: The New Hampshire voter suppression law is intended to disenfranchise college students from exercising their right to vote. I have signed @jeanneshaheen’s petition to oppose this law to send a clear message to students — your vote matters and must be protected.

name: Kamala Harris
text: Mark your calendar → Tomorrow I’ll take the stage at 10 p.m. ET for a CNN Town Hall to discuss everything from debt-free education to how we can get the economy working for working Americans again. Join supporters who are hosting a watch party:

name: Kamala Harris
text: As president, I will reinstate DACA until Congress can pass comprehensive immigration reform. Dreamers represent the best of who we are as a country. We owe it to them to act.

name: Kamala Harris
text: The federal minimum wage hasn’t moved from $7.25/hour in almost a decade. As president, I will give working Americans the raise they deserve by increasing the minimum wage to $15/hour and making it a living wage.

name: Kamala Harris
text: Adding a citizenship question on the U.S. Census is a blatant attempt to suppress immigrant families from being counted in our nation. Congress must pass the Every Person Counts Act to ensure the integrity of the census is protected.

name: Kamala Harris
text: Fantastic final routine @katelyn_ohashi. Best wishes to you and your family in the future! We’re rooting for you.

name: Kamala Harris
text: Our nation’s firefighters display exceptional courage. Fully fund the Firefighter Cancer Registry, so doctors and researchers can better understand the risks associated with firefighting and prevent unnecessary deaths.

name: Kamala Harris
text:
Easter is a reminder that there is hope and rebirth even in the darkest of times. We must remember that today, more than ever. 

I am horrified by the attacks in Sri Lanka, where so many families were celebrating such a joyous day. Praying for the victims and their loved ones.

name: Kamala Harris
text: We must embrace paper ballots and upgrades to our election infrastructure in 2020. Russia and other foreign adversaries cannot hack a piece of paper like they can a computer. Every voter deserves to have their vote counted. It’s imperative we work now to protect our elections.

name: Kamala Harris
text: Marijuana laws have not been applied & enforced in the same way for all people. Too many lives have been ruined by these regressive policies and while more states are moving to legalize marijuana through ballot initiatives, it is not enough. Time to legalize at the federal level.

name: Kamala Harris
text:
Our nation's leaders should have acted to end gun violence in schools after Columbine. 
After Virginia Tech. 
After Northern Illinois University. 
After Sandy Hook.
After Umpqua Community College.
After Parkland. 
After Santa Fe High School.
Inner City schools.

text: Our country is facing a major housing crisis. In one of the wealthiest countries in the world, millions of Americans are being forced to make tough choices between paying rent on time or taking care of their families. I’ve proposed the Rent Relief Act to ease that burden.

name: Kamala Harris
text:
The teacher pay gap is a national failure that’s holding America back. Our country has failed to give teachers the resources they deserve. My plan would provide a $13k raise for the average teacher. 

I am committed to this fight for our teachers and our future.

name: Kamala Harris
text: Betsy DeVos wants to give teachers guns — I want to give them a raise.

name: Kamala Harris
text: I was raised by a mother who taught us that if you see a problem, you don't complain about it. You do something about it. That's why I'm running for president. We have to stand up and fight for our American values.

name: Kamala Harris
text: Students and young people will play a huge role in this election. From the student loan debt crisis to climate change, every single decision we make affects your future and your voices should be heard. That's why we’re launching Camp Kamala in Iowa.

name: Kamala Harris
text: President Trump keeps playing politics with our health care. If he gets his way and the Affordable Care Act is struck down, millions of Americans could lose their insurance and protections for their pre-existing conditions. Let’s be real: we need a new president.

name: Kamala Harris
text: I am running for president to put our government back in the hands of the people. Our campaign won’t accept a penny from corporate PACs or federal lobbyists. I don’t answer to them, I answer to people like you. Pitch in today before Sunday’s deadline:

name: Kamala Harris
text: Trump has been attacking people with disabilities relentlessly since taking office. From trying to tear down the Affordable Care Act to slashing their benefits and now attempting to eliminate funding for the Special Olympics, it could not be more clear: we need a new president.

name: Kamala Harris
text: The gap between what teachers and people with similar educations earn creates disastrous consequences. Teachers are leaving their dream jobs because they can’t make ends meet. That’s not right. They deserve better. My plan will help us retain and empower teachers.

name: Kamala Harris
text:
Americans deserve to see the full Mueller report, not a four-page summary from Trump’s hand-picked Attorney General. 

This is about protecting the public’s trust in our democracy and government. We need transparency.

name: Kamala Harris
text: More than 11M Americans are spending more than half of their income on housing. That means less money for groceries, medications, bus fares, and other necessities. They deserve relief. The Rent Relief Act would help to ease that burden and put money back in people’s pockets.

name: Kamala Harris
text: People are killed in our streets, in our churches, at concerts, and in our communities. The devastating effects of gun violence demand action. That means ending the gun lobby’s corrupt influence in Washington. We have to speak that truth.

name: Kamala Harris
text: We are working to build a winning campaign and that means every commitment — even the smallest — makes a difference to our fight. Pitch in today and invest in our movement for tomorrow:

name: Kamala Harris
text: When LBJ made a major education investment, he told the country that it was to “bridge the gap between helplessness and hope.” 54 years later, this gap remains — but I am determined to keep building that bridge as president.

name: Kamala Harris
text: This Administration is deliberately ignoring the threat of climate change and favoring polluters over American’s health. We can’t leave our children and their children to deal with the consequences of their inaction.

name: Kamala Harris
text: Vel Phillips was a pioneer in the fight for racial and economic justice. In Wisconsin and beyond, her activism and her legacy lives through each of us as we work toward a future that promises equality, justice, and opportunity for all. #WomensHistoryMonth

name: Kamala Harris
text: The United States is facing a teacher pay crisis. Public school teachers earn 11% less than professionals with similar educations and teachers overall are more likely than non-teachers to work a second job. Read my plan to fix this crisis at http://kamalaharris.org/teachers .

name: Kamala Harris
text: What’s happening at our border in El Paso is unmistakably a humanitarian crisis. Leaving families outdoors in cramped, unsanitary conditions with little or no access to hot food and showers is cruel and a violation of their human rights.

name: Kamala Harris
text: Congress needs to reverse the FCC’s misguided decision to repeal net neutrality protections. Let’s not waste another second longer to pass the #SaveTheNet Act, restore net neutrality, and keep the internet open and accessible for all Americans.

name: Kamala Harris
text: I often get asked "how can we afford this" — but my question is: how can we afford NOT to give our teachers a raise? They're raising our children. Don't they deserve our respect? Don't they deserve to get paid their value?

name: Kamala Harris
text:
It’s unbelievable. The NRA is trying to block the Violence Against Women Act, which helps survivors of domestic and sexual assault, because part of the bill would seek to keep guns out of the hands of abusers. 

Congress must stand up to the gun lobby. Lives are at stake.

name: Kamala Harris
text: Without the protections of the Affordable Care Act, Americans with pre-existing conditions could be denied health insurance and insurance companies would once again be allowed to discriminate based on age and gender. We won’t let Republicans bring us back to those days.

name: Kamala Harris
text: The average teacher salary has gone down over the last decade and too many are working multiple jobs to make ends meet. We’ve failed to give teachers the respect they deserve. That’s why I’ve released a plan to provide the average teacher a $13,500 raise: http://kamalaharris.org/teachers .

name: Kamala Harris
text: On average, Black teachers earn $2,700 less per year than white teachers and women earn $2,000 less than men. That’s wrong. We must do better to narrow those disparities and lift up these teachers.

name: Kamala Harris
text: If we’re going to close this teacher wage gap and pay teachers their worth, we must all raise our voices together. Add your name next to mine to show your support for millions of dedicated teachers across this country:

name: Kamala Harris
text: Thousand Oaks Elementary School was where I first learned the importance of teachers. They’re the ones staying up late to think of creative lesson plans or coming in early to help tutor our kids. I introduced a plan today to increase their pay. They’ve earned it.

name: Kamala Harris
text: It’s clear more is needed to effectively recruit and retain teachers across the country. A federal plan to provide support, training, and professional development is critical to sustaining our education system. I introduced a plan today to do just that.

name: Kamala Harris
text:
From West Virginia to Oklahoma to California, educators are standing up in solidarity for dignity and equity in our classrooms. They deserve a president who supports them. 

Betsy DeVos proposed giving teachers guns. I’m proposing we give them a raise.

name: Kamala Harris
text: Teachers are more likely than non-teachers to work a second job. We all deserve an America where you only need one job to pay the bills. We must close the teacher pay gap.

name: Kamala Harris
text: In 30 states, average teacher pay is less than the living wage for a family of four. The teacher pay gap is a national crisis. Sign your name next to mine if you agree:

name: Kamala Harris
text: Teachers work incredibly hard to build the foundation of our country, one student at a time. That's why I've released a plan to give teachers a raise.

name: Kamala Harris
text: Our children are being raised by two groups of people: families and teachers. Yet, we fail to pay teachers their value. As president, I will make the largest federal investment in teacher pay in U.S. history and give the average teacher a $13,500 raise.

name: Kamala Harris
text:
Trump and his administration are trying to take health care away from tens of millions of Americans — again. 

We must fight back again with everything we've got. And in 2020, we need to elect a president who will make health care a right.

name: Kamala Harris
text: They came. They ran. And they won. Seventeen Black women made history in Harris County when they were elected to the Bench. I’m so glad I got to share a moment with some of them this weekend. It was an honor to witness your sisterhood.

name: Kamala Harris
text: Trump is in Big Oil’s pocket, and they know it. It’s time we put an end to oil companies manipulating our laws and poisoning our planet. Unlike this president, I’ve sided with our environment over special interests — and I’ll continue to do so in office.

name: Kamala Harris
text: Author, activist, and philosopher Grace Lee Boggs dedicated her 100 years striving for racial and economic justice. She also worked to encourage young people to get actively involved in their neighborhoods through the program Detroit Summer. #WomensHistoryMonth

name: Kamala Harris
text:
“[Trump] doesn’t want another single dollar going to the island.” 

The people that are in Puerto Rico are United States citizens. They are in dire need. Denying them assistance is cruel.

name: Kamala Harris

text: Any success we achieve in life is due in large part to the teachers who believed in us and invested in our future. It's time to ensure teachers are finally paid their worth.

name: Kamala Harris
text: FEMA officials must be held accountable for mishandling the personal information of millions of California wildfire survivors and hurricane victims. This is unacceptable.

name: Kamala Harris

name: Kamala Harris
text: Thank you Atlanta for the welcome! From discussing the need for better teacher pay, to how we can protect our communities from gun violence, I’m glad you all were able to join me on this beautiful Sunday afternoon.

text: It isn’t enough to just say our teachers shape the future of our country, we should pay them like it. It’s past time we value and respect their work, compassion, and dedication to our kids.

text: It was an honor to join @RaphaelWarnock and his congregation at @ebenezer_atl this morning. Today’s incredible service on Youth Day showed the power of young leaders who are fighting for our future. Let’s continue to empower and listen to the voices of young people.

name: Kamala Harris
text: Most teachers take money from their own pockets to buy students the supplies they need. They’re the ones creating a special handshake for each student or spending extra time to tutor their students in science or math. But they’re underpaid and overlooked. We have to change that.

text: My first grade teacher, Mrs. Francis Wilson, changed my life and helped make me the person I am today. Teachers do so much and it’s time they were respected. If you had a teacher that made a mark on your life, share your story with me today and I’ll RT some throughout the day.

name: Kamala Harris
text: Still thinking of the devastating flooding in Iowa and Nebraska. My heart goes out to those who have lost homes and businesses. Thank you to the first responders and volunteers who have been working tirelessly in their communities.

name: Kamala Harris
text: One year ago today, people across the country took part in the powerful March for our Lives movement led by our nation’s youth and demanded our leaders in Congress take a stand against gun violence. It’s because of them I’m optimistic we will one day end this horrific epidemic.

name: Kamala Harris
text: One of the biggest health care reforms in half a century became law nine years ago. The Affordable Care Act showed us what’s possible when we fight for health care as a right for all, not a privilege for a few, and create a real pathway for Medicare for All.

name: Kamala Harris
text: I know the impact teachers can have. My first grade teacher, Mrs. Wilson, supported me from my time at Thousand Oaks Elementary School to when I walked across the stage to get my law degree. Supporting our teachers is critical for our students, our economy, and our country.

name: Kamala Harris
text: Today marks three years since my office won a $1.1B judgment for the victims of Corinthian Colleges, who were preyed upon and left with mountains of debt and useless degrees. As president, I'll continue to protect students from deceptive for-profit colleges.

name: Kamala Harris
text:
Our country needs an Administration that supports public education, not privatization.

We need a Secretary of Education who actually has experience in education.

We need a president who stands with teachers, has their backs and respects their work.

name: Kamala Harris
text:
Moments ago, I pledged that at the end of my first term as president we'll close the teacher pay gap with the largest federal investment in teacher pay in American history. 

No teacher should have to work 2-3 jobs to survive. That’s wrong. I’m ready to do something about it.

name: Kamala Harris
text: It feels good to be in Houston. Can't wait to see you at our rally and lay out our vision for a better America, including the need to give teachers a raise. See you soon!

name: Kamala Harris
text: Releasing the Mueller report to the public is about protecting our democracy and the people’s confidence in our elections and government. The White House must not interfere in any way — give the information to the American people.

text: In America, public school teachers are paid about $13,000 a year less than other college graduates. That could be mortgage payments or the cost of groceries for a family for a year. It’s a national failure. It’s time we give America’s teachers a raise.

text: We don’t know many details yet about Special Counsel Mueller’s report. But there is one thing I know: the report must be made public immediately. Add your name if you agree →

text: Americans deserve to know the truth now that the Mueller report is complete. The report must be released immediately and AG Barr must publicly testify under oath about the investigation's findings. We need total transparency here.

name: Kamala Harris
text: Our children should never have to live in fear that their school will be the next one devastated by gun violence. We cannot accept this as normal. Congress must pass universal background checks and renew the assault weapons ban.

text:
Americans are now more likely to die from an opioid overdose than in a car crash. This is a public health crisis we cannot ignore.

As president, I’ll fight to end the opioid epidemic — and take on Big Pharma for fueling this crisis nationwide.

name: Kamala Harris

name: Kamala Harris

Our nation's leaders should have acted to end gun violence after Sandy Hook. 
After Charleston. 
After San Bernardino. 
After Pulse. 
After Sutherland Springs. 
After Las Vegas.
After the Tree of Life Synagogue. 
After Parkland. 
After Thousand Oaks. 

How many more?

name: Kamala Harris

name: Kamala Harris
text: Passing the EQUALITY Act would send a clear message that discrimination against transgender people won’t be tolerated. No one should be fired or dehumanized by their employer simply for their gender identity or expression.

name: Kamala Harris
text: We need a president who will stand up to the gun lobby. We had an assault weapons ban once, and we should have it again. These weapons of war do not belong on our streets, in our schools, or at our houses of worship. This is a fight I will take on as president.

text: Of the 40 million family caregivers in the U.S., one in four are millennials. Guaranteed paid family leave would support families, protect workers, assist those taking on the role as caregiver, and give financial security for future generations.

name: Kamala Harris
text:

Americans are dying in the streets from gun violence, too many are working more for less, and white supremacy is rising around the globe. 

We need a president who will speak truth and fight for the people.

name: Kamala Harris

name: Kamala Harris
text: Americans owe over $1.5 trillion in student loan debt — surpassing credit card debt. We can’t ignore this crisis as it continues to hurt the livelihoods of student loan borrowers and harms our country. It’s vital we make college debt-free. Let’s end the crushing cycle of debt.

name: Kamala Harris
text: When the Supreme Court took up cases on women’s health, I fought to ensure companies provided health insurance that covers contraceptives and protected patients’ access to reproductive health clinics. I did it as Attorney General, I’d do the same as president.

name: Kamala Harris
