text: Let’s make this a more perfect union by fighting for the ideals of our country. All of us. Together.

name: Kamala Harris
text: I will vote for the resolution to block the President’s national emergency declaration. We don’t need a wall, we need to address actual emergencies facing our nation — everything from climate change, to gun violence, to lack of access to health care.

name: Kamala Harris
text: I support the Green New Deal because we need a sense of urgency and a bold agenda to address the climate crisis.

name: Kamala Harris
text: As President, my first priority would be to lift up middle-class families. Almost half of Americans don’t have enough cash to cover a $400 emergency, like a broken car or an unexpected medical expense. That’s wrong. Passing the LIFT Act will alleviate that burden.

name: Kamala Harris
text: Poet Audre Lorde dedicated her life to speaking about the injustices that plague our nation: everything from racism, sexism, to homophobia. Her powerful words remind us that we need to speak out about these, even when others are silent. #BlackHistoryMonth

name: Kamala Harris
text: I support debt-free college because getting an education shouldn’t mean taking on a lifetime of debt. Let’s end this vicious cycle.

name: Kamala Harris
text: It’s outrageous that hundreds of immigrant families are still being separated at the border. My colleagues and I reintroduced the REUNITE Act, requiring immediate family reunification of children who can be safely reunified. This human rights violation must come to an end now.

name: Kamala Harris
text: The Trump Administration is threatening to veto legislation that would require background checks and close the Charleston loophole. As President, I will fight for and sign common-sense reforms to eliminate gun violence.

name: Kamala Harris
text: It’s been seven years since we unjustly lost Trayvon Martin. His tragic death was not just a moment in history — it sparked a movement and his legacy continues to live through our fight for justice. We must be better than this.

name: Kamala Harris
text: Detaining pregnant women who have fled their homes in search of safety is inhumane and unsafe.

name: Kamala Harris
text: Dr. Mae Jemison’s love for science began at a young age. She was only 16 when she started at Stanford University for chemical engineering. Dr. Jemison would go on to break barriers as the first Black woman in space, conducting experiments on weightlessness and motion sickness.

name: Kamala Harris
text:
The day after I announced my candidacy, I shared an incredible letter I received from a young Iowan named Nora, saying I should run for president. 

I was so excited to see Nora and her “Future President” shirt this weekend in Iowa — and hope I get to follow her campaign one day!

name: Kamala Harris
text: Denying climate change won’t make it go away — this crisis calls for real, global action. We need a president who will confront this issue head-on and base decisions on science fact, not science fiction.

name: Kamala Harris
text: Oakland teachers are continuing to strike this week for better wages and smaller class sizes. We must all stand in solidarity with them as they fight for what they deserve, what they’re worth, and what’s best for our schools.

name: Kamala Harris
text: Such a historic night. Congratulations to @ReginaKing, @ItsRamiMalek, Mahershala Ali, and the many other women and people of color who claimed honors at the Oscars. Representation matters.

name: Kamala Harris
text: Big insurance companies and Big Pharma are already hiring lobbyists to try to stop us from passing Medicare for All. But I’ve got news for them: we won’t back down. Health care is a right, not a privilege, and we need a system that puts patients ahead of profits.

name: Kamala Harris
text: Congratulations Hannah Beachler and Ruth E. Carter for making history! For the first time ever, *two* Black women won Oscars in non-acting categories — production design and costume design.

name: Kamala Harris
text: Me Too founder and activist @TaranaBurke has fought to ensure no survivor of sexual assault or harassment is silenced. Her life’s work is not just about awareness, but action — to show survivors they’re not alone, they’re seen, and they’re heard. #BlackHistoryMonth

name: Kamala Harris
text: Systemic inequities have led to mass incarceration and a broken criminal justice system. We need to address this. We should invest in prevention and implement sentencing reforms. That’s what I’ll do as president. Watch our discussion today on @amjoyshow:

name: Kamala Harris
text: We all got to know @AndrewGillum's father from the stories he shared along the campaign trail, and I was delighted to meet his family in person in Florida. Sending my prayers and condolences to Andrew and his family during this difficult time.

name: Kamala Harris
text: When the Mueller report is complete, it needs to be released to the public and Congress must receive all underlying investigative materials, be it a classified hearing or unclassified. Anything less is unacceptable.

name: Kamala Harris
text: We have failed to put resources into our public education system, instead pouring tons of money into a system of mass incarceration. That must end. It’s past time we invested more in the future of our country: our nation’s children.

name: Kamala Harris
text: Our campaign will not accept a dime from corporate PACs or lobbyists — and it’s a very deliberate choice. I’m fighting for the people, not big corporations. Join me in this fight:

name: Kamala Harris
text: Our children should never have to live in fear that their school will be the next one struck by gun violence. This is not normal, and it is not ok. We can’t wait any longer for Congress to pass background checks and renew the assault weapons ban.

name: Kamala Harris
text: As Attorney General of California, I took on the five biggest Wall Street banks during the financial crisis. We won $20 billion for California homeowners and together we passed the strongest anti-foreclosure law in the United States of America.

name: Kamala Harris
text: Fighting for the people means listening to the people. I heard many questions regarding tax fairness, Medicare for All, protecting a woman’s right to choose, and much more at our first town hall in Iowa today. Together, we will strengthen our democracy to work for all of us.

name: Kamala Harris
text: Bottom line: jeopardizing reproductive health care access for millions of women is a crisis. We need to stand firm in our values and speak out against this attack.

name: Kamala Harris
text: Our climate is changing rapidly and we are headed toward a catastrophe of our own making. This is a global emergency and we must act.

name: Kamala Harris
text: What’s happening in Venezuela is a crisis. The people who have fled Maduro’s dictatorial regime deserve safety and protection. As President, I would immediately extend TPS status to Venezuelans. It’s the right thing to do. America must show moral leadership in this hemisphere.

name: Kamala Harris
text: The U.S. must immediately condemn Maduro’s violence against his own people. There is no excuse for this. The Venezuelan military and security forces must demonstrate restraint. Venezuelans deserve a free and fair election and a peaceful transition of power.

name: Kamala Harris
text: Katherine Johnson’s tremendous work with NASA will leave a mark on our history for decades to come. Congratulations on this well-deserved achievement.

name: Kamala Harris
text: The fight for a $15 minimum wage is a fight for fairness, freedom, opportunity, and more. It’s a fight for an equal playing field — and a fight we can win.

name: Kamala Harris
text: As President, I will fight to ensure every child has access to a better education, every family is given a fair shot, and every community is safe from an epidemic of gun violence.

name: Kamala Harris
text: As President, I will fight for Medicare for All. No American should go bankrupt because they can’t pay a hospital bill. Health care shouldn’t be a privilege, it should be a right.

name: Kamala Harris
text: It is indefensible for the White House to walk away from negotiations with California over fuel efficiency standards. Everyone has the right to breathe clean air. It shouldn’t be up for debate: we must protect the environment for future generations.

name: Kamala Harris
text: NEVADA: I will host a town hall in Vegas on March 1 and can’t wait to listen and learn from you. Say you’ll be there→

name: Kamala Harris
text: Former First Lady @MichelleObama has used her powerful voice to encourage children to lead healthier lives and inspire young people to pursue higher education. Her influential work has helped countless Americans fulfill their potential. #BlackHistoryMonth

name: Kamala Harris
text: Don’t miss this: the White House is trying to put a climate change denier in charge of a climate change research panel. It’s absurd — a danger to our planet and our future.

name: Kamala Harris
text: Voting rights are under attack across the country. Let’s counteract that by strengthening access to the ballot box, expanding early voting, and making Election Day a national holiday.

name: Kamala Harris
text: This Administration continues to play politics with public health. No doctor should be silenced and barred from protecting their patient's health. We will fight back against this attack on women.

name: Kamala Harris
text:
IOWA: I’m back on the road to Ankeny and Scott County this weekend. There’s still time to RSVP to attend our town halls. Can’t wait to see you:
https://events.mobilizeamerica.io/kamalaharris/

name: Kamala Harris
text: California is proving you can lead the fight against climate change, raise the minimum wage, and reduce the uninsured rate by 10% — all while having the world’s fifth-largest economy. No matter what the President says, what we’re doing works.

name: Kamala Harris
text: Together, we’re fighting for a nation where reproductive rights are not just protected by the Constitution, but guaranteed in every state.

name: Kamala Harris
text: Want to take a moment to celebrate a Civil Rights icon on his day. @repjohnlewis we are stronger because of you. Happy Birthday!!! #GoodTrouble

name: Kamala Harris
text: We need to create an economy that works for everyone, not just the few. It’s time for a national commitment to good-paying jobs, affordable childcare, and paid family leave.

name: Kamala Harris
text: Oakland-based organizer and Black Lives Matter co-founder Alicia Garza is a powerful voice against police injustice. She created Black Futures Lab to mobilize Black political power and is fighting for millions of domestic workers that live in the U.S. #BlackHistoryMonth

name: Kamala Harris
text: Like most of you, I've seen the reports about Jussie Smollett, and I'm sad, frustrated, and disappointed.

name: Kamala Harris
text: Nearly half of American families do not have enough cash to afford a $400 unexpected expense. It’s time we put money back in their pockets — not big wealthy corporations and the top 1%

name: Kamala Harris
text:
When people say they want to talk about women's issues, my response is always, “I’m so glad you want to talk about the economy!”

With a historic number of Democratic women running for president, I hope all women know the sky’s the limit. : @marieclaire

name: Kamala Harris
text: Teachers invest their time and energy to educate the future of our country, and they deserve our support. Standing in solidarity with the thousands of Oakland teachers who are striking to demand better pay and classroom conditions.

name: Kamala Harris
text: Climate change is a *real* national emergency. We need a leader in the White House who isn't in the pocket of big oil. We need someone who will fight for clean air and water for all Americans.

name: Kamala Harris
text: I’ll join @TrevorNoah on the @TheDailyShow tonight at 11 p.m. ET. Be sure to tune in.

name: Kamala Harris
text: These students were inspired by empowering individuals that forged their own paths and made a difference in our world. Representation matters.

name: Kamala Harris
text: Raised in California, @Venuseswilliams and @serenawilliams’ father taught them to play tennis on courts not too far from the family’s home. The sisters would go on to win numerous Grand Slam titles and pave a path forward for other women in sports. #BlackHistoryMonth

name: Kamala Harris
text: The trauma these children experience will live on for decades to come. It’s absurd that it needs to be repeated: ripping babies away from their parents to put them in cages is inhumane.

name: Kamala Harris
text: No parent should have to think about buying their child a bulletproof backpack to keep them safe at school. Let’s be the generation that finally addresses gun violence epidemic.

name: Kamala Harris
text: The idea that the President of the United States would take Putin's word over that of our intelligence community is deeply disturbing. It’s insulting to the skilled, dedicated professionals who’ve devoted their lives to protecting our nation.

name: Kamala Harris
text: Like our broken cash bail system, excessive fines and confiscation of property lead to the criminalization of poverty. I'm glad the Supreme Court unanimously held that the Constitution's ban on excessive fines also applies to state and local governments.

name: Kamala Harris
text: My Brother’s Keeper helps foster mentorships for boys and young men of color and closes opportunity gaps so they can reach their full potential. Proud that this program celebrated its five year anniversary in Oakland with community leaders from across the country. #MBKRising

name: Kamala Harris
text: Paper ballots are the smartest, safest way to conduct secure elections and protect from voter manipulation. Russia can’t hack a piece of paper. Our nation needs to be ready to protect our election systems against attacks by foreign powers. Now is the time to prepare.

name: Kamala Harris
text: There is an incredible amount of power in the people of our country. We cannot lose our conviction and hope about what we can be as a nation. Let’s hold on to that as we move forward.

name: Kamala Harris
text: IOWA: I’m hosting town halls in Ankeny and Scott County this upcoming weekend. Can’t wait to answer your questions and lay out my vision for our nation’s future. Spread the word and RSVP now →

name: Kamala Harris
text:
“This unbelievable person was robbed from us.”

Josh Pinkard was one of the five lives cut short in last week’s shooting in Aurora, Illinois. This senseless gun violence has touched too many communities across the country. Enough is enough.

name: Kamala Harris
text: A mathematician, Katherine Johnson, was a pioneer of her time, expanding NASA’s use of computers to launch space exploration. She is an inspiration to each of us to boldly be unburdened by what has been & excel to our fullest potential. #ExemplifyingExcellence #BlackHistoryMonth

name: Kamala Harris
text: The top 1% now has 40 times the average American family's wealth. We need to address the income inequality gap and restore economic opportunity to ease the strain on American families.

name: Kamala Harris
text: California is once again leading the way as one of sixteen states suing the President over declaring a national emergency to build his wasteful border wall. It’s time for him to stop playing politics with taxpayer resources.

name: Kamala Harris
text: There is no question that Election Day should be a national holiday.

name: Kamala Harris
text: Let’s speak truth: we’re a society that pretends to care about education, but not so much the education of other people’s children. Every single child deserves to go to a quality school. When we improve their lives and their education, our whole society benefits.

name: Kamala Harris
text: The federal minimum wage hasn’t moved from $7.25 an hour since July of 2009 and yet, the cost of living has gone up since then. I applaud the activists that fought to make a $15 minimum wage possible in New Jersey and Illinois.

name: Kamala Harris
text: We should never bow down to those who have a lot of money because we are afraid that we may not win re-election when people are dying in our streets from gun violence.

name: Kamala Harris
text: Civil rights leader and poet Maya Angelou had an immeasurable impact on the way I view the world and my place in it. While she encountered many hardships throughout her life, her words inspired generations to fight for freedom, equality, and justice.

name: Kamala Harris
text: We need to restore the promise of opportunity in America. Together, we can build an America where everyone has the chance at success. Pitch in today to help us make that a reality:

name: Kamala Harris
text: We’ve seen every horrific tragedy from gun violence imaginable — from first-graders massacred in Sandy Hook to people murdered while attending Bible study. We need to close gun loopholes, pass universal background checks, and reinstate the assault weapons ban.

name: Kamala Harris
text: Humbled that so many people took the time on Presidents' Day to join me in Portsmouth, New Hampshire. Thank you for sharing your stories, thoughts, and hopes for the future of our nation. I can't wait to be back.

name: Kamala Harris
text: I had a great time talking with Granite Staters at @GibsonsConcord this afternoon. Now I'm on to Portsmouth! To everyone braving the snow for our town hall later today: hang in there! I can't wait to see you.

name: Kamala Harris
text: It’s long past time to address bail reform across the country. Too often, poor people sit in jail because they don’t have the money to pay bail, while someone with the same offense but money in their back pocket gets out. This is a serious injustice.

name: Kamala Harris
text: I stand in solidarity with those rallying across the country against the President’s manufactured national emergency. It’s time we address the actual emergencies plaguing our nation: gun violence, lack of access to health care, and climate change.

name: Kamala Harris
text: Teachers are the heroes that future generations depend on. I stand with Oakland teachers as they prepare to strike.

name: Kamala Harris
text: This Presidents’ Day, let’s reflect on the leaders who moved America forward for all. As FDR once said, "The test of our progress is not whether we add more to the abundance of those who have much; it is whether we provide enough for those who have too little."

name: Kamala Harris
text: Funds intended for victims of natural disasters should not be used for the President’s vanity project, the wall. We will fight back against this ridiculous national emergency declaration.

name: Kamala Harris
text: There should never be any obstacles or challenges in order for Americans to exercise their constitutional right to vote. We’ve seen time and again that elections matter. We need to commit with all we’ve got to protect voting rights for all.

name: Kamala Harris
text: Climate change is an imminent threat to our planet unless we correct course. It’s within our power to do so. Now is the time.

name: Kamala Harris
text: Supporting small businesses — and Black woman-owned businesses — strengthens the backbone of our economy. It’s about investment and innovation in our communities. When they succeed, we all succeed.

name: Kamala Harris
text: Transgender rights activist Janet Mock is fighting for justice and dignity while paving the way for others to boldly embrace who they are. Her work has helped empower transgender women everywhere. #BlackHistoryMonth

name: Kamala Harris
text: After the Department of Justice told Deutsche Bank that they needed to help distressed homeowners after the financial crisis, the bank is now turning their back on the most vulnerable.

name: Kamala Harris
text: Congress could use a little more of the WEFE Warrior pledge — kindness, respect, and lifting up others.

name: Kamala Harris
text: The President’s national emergency declaration is completely unnecessary and a waste of taxpayer resources. This is a crisis of his own making.

name: Kamala Harris
text: Dolores Huerta is a trailblazer who inspires me every day. I am thankful for her support and excited to fight alongside her for the future of our country.

name: Kamala Harris
text: Keeping you both in my heart today and every day.

name: Kamala Harris
text: Charleston, it was so wonderful to see you yesterday. I’ll be back to South Carolina a lot, but what a memorable day of reflection and conversation with you all!

name: Kamala Harris
text:
“I’m very enthusiastic about Kamala Harris. I’ll be endorsing her candidacy for president...I think the American people could not do better.” 

Proud to have the support of my friend Governor @GavinNewsom, who has committed his life to fighting for equality & opportunity for all.

name: Kamala Harris
text: After one of the deadliest shootings in our country’s history, Nevada has officially passed a universal background check bill, thanks to @GovSisolak, to chip away at the epidemic of gun violence and mass shootings — proving we can turn pain into progress.

name: Kamala Harris
text: Thank you, South Carolina!

name: Kamala Harris
text: Not everyone has equal access and opportunity to the road to success and we have got to correct that by focusing on everything from homeownership to a meaningful education.

name: Kamala Harris
text: Don’t let the NRA fool you: an overwhelming 97% of Americans support universal background checks to confront gun violence. We owe it to every victim, survivor, their families, and our communities to be stronger and louder than the gun lobby.

name: Kamala Harris
text: Adding a citizenship question to the census is a blatant attempt to undermine the idea that everyone should be counted in America. It’s critical the Supreme Court sides with the people so the census isn’t used as a political weapon by this Administration.

name: Kamala Harris
text: Our health care system is not fair or simple and it is causing people of all ages an extraordinary amount of pain. No one in this country should have to give up everything to survive — we need Medicare For All to bring dignity to millions.

name: Kamala Harris
text: Thanks for the warm welcome, Charleston. Great to meet so many folks from South Carolina for the very first time. Next stop, Columbia.

name: Kamala Harris
text: What would the campaign trail be without amazing food? Stopped by @rodneyscottsbbq in Charleston for lunch. Pulled pork, greens, and cornbread. Rodney, you gotta share these recipes!

name: Kamala Harris
text: My heart is broken for the victims and their loved ones in Aurora. I'm grateful for the first responders who put their lives at risk to keep people safe. We've lost too many lives and seen too many communities shattered by gun violence. We can't let this keep happening.

name: Kamala Harris
text: Earlier today, I spoke out about the need for gun safety reform. Hours later, there was an active shooter in Aurora, Illinois. My heart goes out to the entire community.

name: Kamala Harris
text: Charleston is a vibrant city that has welcomed me with open arms. Can't wait to see everyone at our town hall in a few minutes. : @bradyqg

name: Kamala Harris
text: I visited Mother Emanuel in Charleston earlier this morning to pay my respects to the nine victims of the 2015 shooting and leave some flowers in their memory. We’ve lost too many lives to gun violence — it's far past time to pass commonsense gun safety reforms.

name: Kamala Harris
text: There are two things that shaped who I am today: my family and Howard University. HBCUs are critical to nurture and challenge students and I am thrilled that the Senate passed my bill to preserve and improve historic HBCUs.

name: Kamala Harris
text: We should do something about the actual emergencies that plague our nation — like climate change or health care access — not playing politics in order to build a wasteful border wall.

name: Kamala Harris
text: At a time when this Administration is trying to open up our public lands to mining and drilling, the bipartisan conservation bill that passed the Senate was a major step forward.

name: Kamala Harris
text: Millions of Americans are already living paycheck to paycheck. We shouldn’t punish people who went to school to further their education. That’s not right.

name: Kamala Harris
text: Oakland’s restorative justice program, one of the primary alternatives to traditional school discipline, is in jeopardy. These programs are critical and we should be supporting more programs like these.

name: Kamala Harris
text: Decorated gymnast @Simone_Biles was six years old when she was introduced to gymnastics and insisted her parents enroll her at the gym. Years later, that same persistence would lead her to become the first woman gymnast to win three consecutive World All-Around titles.

name: Kamala Harris
text:
“Valentine’s Day. The last time I saw you alive. A year has been a long time without you. So much has happened I want to tell you about.”

A gut-wrenching letter from Lori Alhadeff, whose daughter Alyssa was killed in Parkland.

name: Kamala Harris
text: Thankful to have the support of my friend and progressive leader, @BLeeForCongress.

name: Kamala Harris
text: Declaring a national emergency over this President's vanity project is ridiculous. We don't need a wall. Instead, we should address the actual emergencies facing our country — everything from gun violence to the opioid crisis.

name: Kamala Harris
text: Hug those you love today. Happy Valentine's Day!

name: Kamala Harris
text: Today marks one year since the horrific shooting at Marjory Stoneman Douglas High School, yet Congress has failed to act on any meaningful legislation to prevent another mass shooting. This isn’t a question of left or right, it’s about protecting our children from gun violence.

name: Kamala Harris
text: BREAKING: Our anti-lynching bill, which would make lynching a federal crime, just unanimously passed the Senate. Lynching is a dark, despicable part of our nation's history and I'm hopeful this measure will swiftly pass the House.

name: Kamala Harris
text: It’s outrageous that lynching still isn’t considered a federal crime. Congress tried and failed near 200 times between 1882 to 1986. About to ask the Senate to unanimously pass our anti-lynching bill. Let’s right this wrong.

name: Kamala Harris
text: No American should ever go bankrupt or be without health care in one of the wealthiest countries in the world. We need Medicare for All — and we need it now.

name: Kamala Harris
text: We’re not accepting a penny from corporate PACs or federal lobbyists, which means your donations really do make a difference. If you can afford it, chip in now:

name: Kamala Harris
text: After @lucymcbath’s son Jordan was shot and killed, she turned her pain into action, becoming an advocate for common-sense gun safety reform and running for Congress — and winning. We need more ‘mothers on a mission’ like Lucy in Congress. Our children are worth fighting for.

name: Kamala Harris
text: Schools. Places of worship. Movie theaters. Banks. No matter where you are, you deserve to feel safe from gun violence. Mass shootings that barely make headlines cannot become our new reality. We must pass universal background checks and ban assault weapons.

name: Kamala Harris
text: I’ll be back on the road later this week to South Carolina for town halls in Charleston and Columbia. I look forward to answering your questions and discussing our vision for the future. Be sure to RSVP so we know you’re attending →

name: Kamala Harris
text: A record number of Americans behind on their car payments is just the latest sign that more and more people are struggling in our broken economy. We need to do right by them.

name: Kamala Harris
text: No more political games: we must permanently reauthorize the Violence Against Women Act to ensure survivors of sexual assault and domestic violence have access to the care they need.

name: Kamala Harris
text: From focusing on the LIFT Act, a real tax cut for the middle-class, to Medicare for All, we’re fighting on behalf of all Americans who’ve been left behind or deeply hurt by this Administration’s atrocious policies.

name: Kamala Harris
text: Black women in America are dying at a rate 3-4x higher than white women from pregnancy-related complications. It's tragic. When you look at it, this isn’t an issue about education. It isn’t about socioeconomics. It’s literally racial bias in our health care system.

name: Kamala Harris
text: No mother or father should ever have to sit down with their son and tell him that he may be stopped, arrested, or killed because of the color of his skin. This shouldn’t have to be a reality for parents in America.

name: Kamala Harris
text: Madam C.J. Walker became a self-made millionaire and an advocate for women’s economic independence in the early 20th century. Her tremendous tenacity to succeed on her own is a phenomenal story of adversity and empowerment. #BlackHistoryMonth

name: Kamala Harris
text: Time after time, gun safety bills have failed in the NRA-controlled Congress. Enough. We need to pass reasonable reforms to ensure our communities and our schools are safe. Proud to co-sponsor this bill.

name: Kamala Harris
text: Our campaign is about lifting folks up, empowering them to organize, and creating a vision of America in which everyone can see themselves. Join us today at http://kamalaharris.org .

name: Kamala Harris
text: For many families, $500 can make all the difference in being able to get through the month. I'm focused on passing the LIFT Act to ensure middle-class families can do more than just get by.

name: Kamala Harris
text: I unequivocally stand with the teachers striking in Denver and hope for a quick resolution.

name: Kamala Harris
text: Our American values are under attack. Babies have been ripped from their parents at the border. A tax bill passed that benefits corporations and the top 1%, while millions of middle-class families struggle to pay the bills. We’re better than this.

name: Kamala Harris
text: We’ve seen a horrific number of school shootings — from Sandy Hook to Parkland —  and the devastating impact losing classmates can have on students. For the sake of our children, we need reasonable gun safety reforms. Now.

name: Kamala Harris
text: William Barr has shown that he won’t put the American people first. We need an Attorney General who will defend independent investigations from political attacks, embrace a smart on crime approach to public safety, and ensure equal justice. I will vote NO on his nomination.

name: Kamala Harris
text: After being rejected from American aviation schools because of her race and gender, Bessie Coleman taught herself French and went to Europe to receive her international pilot’s license. She paved the way for a flying school in her name after her untimely death. #BlackHistoryMonth

name: Kamala Harris
text: Let me be clear: it’s time we legalized marijuana at the federal level. Marijuana laws are not applied or enforced in the same way for all Americans, many whose lives have been ruined by these regressive policies. We must change the system.

name: Kamala Harris
text: We must ensure that sexual assault survivors get the care and services they need to begin to heal. Last week, I joined my colleagues to reintroduce the bipartisan Survivors’ Access to Supportive Care Act, which would improve and expand their access to medical care.

name: Kamala Harris
text: We can’t allow climate change to shape our environment, define our existence, and destroy our planet. Big oil and major corporations can no longer hold our fate in their hands. It’s on us to reclaim our future. #GreenNewDeal

name: Kamala Harris
text: This Black History Month, I’m taking a moment to reflect on all the phenomenal American heroes who have built America from its foundation and still work every day to make this country stronger, better, and more free. Heroes like Mrs. Shelton.

name: Kamala Harris
text: Medicare for All will ensure that every American has access to health care from the day they are born. No one should ever have to go bankrupt, or even die, simply because they can’t afford to pay their costly medical care.

name: Kamala Harris
text: The average tax refund is down about $170 compared to last year. Let’s call the President’s tax cut what it is: a middle-class tax hike to line the pockets of already wealthy corporations and the 1%.

name: Kamala Harris
text: Thank you, @GavinNewsom, for not playing politics with members of our National Guard. This move by the President is just political grandstanding and we cannot play into this stunt.

name: Kamala Harris
text: Always a great time joining the @breakfastclubam with @cthagod and @djenvy, chatting about bail reform, legalizing marijuana, and what we can do to ensure everyone has a fair shot at the American Dream. All that was missing was @angelayee.

name: Kamala Harris
text: My mother was a pioneering breast cancer researcher and I learned from her just how important it is to lift up and empower women and girls in science, who are often underrepresented there and in other STEM fields. #WomenInScience

name: Kamala Harris
text: Known as the “High Priestess of Soul,” Nina Simone’s iconic voice, life, and career called out racism, inequality, and the need for social justice. #BlackHistoryMonth

name: Kamala Harris
text: Excited to be back in the studio with @breakfastclubam! We talked politics, my time at @HowardU, criminal justice reform, and more! Tune in tomorrow at 7 a.m. ET: https://www.iheart.com/live/power-1051-1481 …

name: Kamala Harris
text: “Since Tel’s death, my only goal is to get people to stop and think — and commit to doing something to end this horrific epidemic of gun violence...It’s too late for my son but hopefully not too late for yours.”

name: Kamala Harris

name: John Hickenlooper
text: When you’re running for president, it’s important to take time to reflect not just on where we’re going as a country, but where we’ve been. Taking an honest look at our past is the only way to ensure that we don’t repeat it.

name: John Hickenlooper
text:
Words cannot describe how breathtaking and heartbreaking the @mempeacejustice is. 

The juxtaposition between the appallling injustices displayed and the name's tribute to peace and justice is a sobering reminder of our troubled past and our current responsibility.

name: John Hickenlooper
text: Our progress is measured by growing freedom of conscience, mutual respect and empathy towards others. We must find the time and temperament to listen, learn, and rebuild communities. It is urgent that we not lose faith in each other, and never stop building our temple of justice.

name: John Hickenlooper
text:
And a great country should acknowledge its mistakes. Slavery is the nagging, unrelenting shame of America. We must own our past and acknowledge the shame, the sin, the injustice, and the ongoing consequences of enslaving an entire race of people.

And we must apologize.

name: John Hickenlooper
John Hickenlooper
text: We must acknowledge that our criminal justice system is rooted in structural inequality, from slavery to government-sponsored discrimination in housing. From voting suppression to the war on drugs - all used to control people and limit their political power.

name: John Hickenlooper
text: Today, we face a crisis of faith and division. From the assaults on minorities, to the demonization of immigrants, and the rising tide of anti-semitism, and the terror and anxiety in our cities between police and neighbors, as MLK said, there is indeed a fierce urgency of now.

name: John Hickenlooper
text: We banned solitary confinement for inmates with mental illnesses, and ended the practice for longer than 15 days. With these reforms, in just a few years we dropped solitary confinement from 700 to 18 inmates.

name: John Hickenlooper
text: In CO, we made same day registration and mail-in ballots happen so that more people can vote. We legalized recreational marijuana and changed the focus of sentencing for drug use to rehabilitation and treatment. We granted clemency and commuted sentences for hundreds of people.

name: John Hickenlooper
text: We fought back on the damaging impact of racial bias in policing. We did it because our basic American compact says: People have the right to be safe, unafraid, and secure in their communities.

name: John Hickenlooper
text: We worked to reduce lethal force and police bias. We changed the way the police handled issues of misconduct, required all officers to go through crisis de-escalation training. We established the Office of Independent Monitor and a Civilian Oversight Commission for misconduct.

name: John Hickenlooper
text: During my time as Mayor, our strength was rooted in our diversity, reflecting the richness of Denver. More than 50% of my cabinet leadership were people of color and 60% were women. Our success had little to do with me, and everything to do with the people around me - my team.

For every dollar men make, women make 80 cents.
African American women make 61 cents.
Native American women make 58 cents.
Latina women make 53 cents.

Let's pass the Paycheck Fairness Act, and address the systemic sexism and racism that is clearly at play.

name: John Hickenlooper
text: Just as we responded to the crisis of polio and the space race, we need to bring the private and public sector together to solve this climate crisis and save the only planet we have.

name: John Hickenlooper
text: The federal government also must play a very active role through smart regulation and well-calibrated tax policy to shape the markets in which these firms compete.

name: John Hickenlooper
text: I am not suggesting that industry can do it alone. My version of a Green New Deal would also involve historic federal investments and incentives in electric storage, modern transmission and science to nurture the industries that will serve as the pillars of the clean economy.

name: John Hickenlooper
text: To achieve the kinds of innovations needed to tackle the climate crisis, government must not shun the private sector, but rather must work closely with industry and our nation’s great research universities to find solutions and scale them rapidly to meet our ambitions.

name: John Hickenlooper
text: Example: the resolution seeks a job guarantee, with full benefits, for every person in the United States. This and other provisions would produce a massive expansion of government that would likely be far too complex to execute effectively in the urgent time frame we are facing.

name: John Hickenlooper
text: In addition to technological barriers, the AOC-Markey resolution sets the Green New Deal up for failure by shifting away from private sector decision making and entirely towards government - including several provisions with little connection to reducing greenhouse gas emissions.

name: John Hickenlooper
text: The resolution sets unachievable goals. We do not yet have the technology needed to reach “net-zero greenhouse gas emissions” in 10 years. That’s why many wind and solar companies don’t support it:

name: John Hickenlooper
text: Some versions of the Green New Deal, such as the resolution from AOC and Senator Markey that the Senate is set to vote on this week, express laudable aims, but also take an approach that limits our prospects for success.

name: John Hickenlooper
text: That is why I support the aims of the “Green New Deal” -- the concept that we should launch multiple major federal initiatives to tackle climate change and reorient our economy around clean energy. But given the stakes, it is also imperative we approach it correctly.

name: John Hickenlooper
text: @realdonaldtrump withdrew our country from the Paris Climate Accords. He is expanding drilling on public lands. He is forfeiting our country’s leadership, changing our national symbol from the eagle to an ostrich, burying our head in the sand in the face of this global threat.

name: John Hickenlooper

name: John Hickenlooper
text: I also believe that we absolutely must achieve universal medical coverage, so that people can change jobs, change careers, or start new businesses like I did, without worrying whether they will have a gap in health insurance or access to a retirement savings vehicle.

name: John Hickenlooper
text: That's why a national plan for the American workforce would also increase the minimum wage to $15 per hour, rethink the employment system so that it supports people in the "gig" economy, and create paid family and medical leave.

name: John Hickenlooper
text: The traditional definition of a job is shifting in the future, but today, we need to make sure work really pays and that people have adequate benefits.

name: John Hickenlooper
text: A national strategy would mean a historic investment in skills training and apprenticeships. It would enlist labor unions, good corporate citizens, and civic organizations to join an effort that ensures people have the skills companies need to drive our economy forward.

name: John Hickenlooper
text: I am calling for a national strategy for the American workforce. America only works when the economy works for everyone, especially for the nearly 70% of Americans who will not graduate with a four year college degree.

name: John Hickenlooper
text: Today, new jobs are disproportionately low-wage and low-skill. They are less secure and pay less than before. In our "hour glass" economy, we have large swaths stuck at the bottom, a hollowed out middle, and a top growing with sky-high incomes and wealth.

name: John Hickenlooper
text:
It's time for a national plan for the American workforce that helps the 70% of people who will not graduate with a four year degree.
 
I'm calling for a historic effort to drive our 21st century economy forward - for everyone.

No one person can heal the fractures in America today. But if enough of us accept the challenge, if we work hard enough, we can make the impossible, possible. 

Together, we can turn this winter of division into a season of hope.

name: John Hickenlooper
text: Being a pragmatist doesn’t mean saying ‘no’ to bold ideas; it means knowing how to make them happen. That’s my record. And that will be my promise as President.

name: John Hickenlooper
text: I am a dreamer and a do-er. And we need both to make real progress. Not just big ideas, but making them happen. Finding common ground when it seems like there’s nothing there but mountains between us.

name: John Hickenlooper
text: It’s one of America’s great talents, building dreams tomorrow we didn’t know were possible today.

name: John Hickenlooper
text: We’ll undo years of efforts to disenfranchise African American voters and Latino voters and even young voters. And end this assault on the foundations of our democracy.

name: John Hickenlooper
text: We’ll renew our commitment to the fundamental strength behind American success. It’s right there in the Great Seal of our country: "Out of many, one."

name: John Hickenlooper
text: "Let me tell you, when I am president we will declare that healthcare is a RIGHT"

name: John Hickenlooper
text: Along the way, I learned something that @realDonaldTrump never figured out: it isn’t how many times you yell “you’re fired,” but instead, how many times you say “you’re hired.”

name: John Hickenlooper
text: I understand I’m not the first person in this race or the most well-known person in this race. But let me tell you: at 4 syllables and 12 letters, “Hickenlooper” is now the biggest name in the race.

name: John Hickenlooper
text: It’s time to end this American crisis of division. It’s time to bring all Americans together. And that’s why I’m running to be President of the United States of America!

name: John Hickenlooper
text: This isn’t about unity for unity’s sake. America stops working when we work against each other. Our country stops making progress when we hunker down on opposite sides of continental divides – Blue vs Red, rich vs poor, urban and rural.

name: John Hickenlooper
text: We have every right to live in a land that’s the home of hope. But these days, that’s not how it feels in America. It feels like we’re living in a heaving crisis, years in the making, spawned by dysfunctional politics. Defined above all by this president.

name: John Hickenlooper
text: "John and I fought the NRA. It was a tough fight, and we still have the scars to prove it. But in the end John Hickenlooper signed into law a bill that required background checks for all gun buyers!" - CO State Representive @Sully_720

name: John Hickenlooper
text:

name: John Hickenlooper
text:
I didn't start my business alone. I didn't revitalize downtown Denver alone. And I certainly didn't lead Colorado alone. Progress isn't an individual effort, it takes great teams -- and that's what we're building with this campaign.

Join us: http://www.hickenlooper.com

name: John Hickenlooper
text:
30 years ago, @Wynkoop was just an idea. We scrubbed toilets, sanded floors, and brewed through the night. We dreamt it and then we did it.

Today, I stood here as a presidential candidate. Starting from scratch. Same grit. We are dreaming it, and together, we’ll do it. Giddy up!

name: John Hickenlooper
text:
One million dollars in just 48 hours - wow! No corporate PAC money. All grassroots contributions. 

Your support goes a long way... from creating signs to supporting our fantastic team to helping us get our message out there. 

Let's keep it going! http://bit.ly/2NHfiYZ

name: John Hickenlooper
text:
Despite appearances, I've got 2020 vision.

Read more here: https://medium.com/@johnhickenlooper/im-interviewing-for-president-here-s-why-4408d1eb3ea0 …

name: John Hickenlooper
text:
We're on the verge of hitting a BIG fundraising milestone! Don't hedge on this, help us hop over the finish line. Donate what you can: http://bit.ly/2HdtKXw  
- Team Hedgehopper

name: John Hickenlooper
text: When I lost my dad at 8, I learned to live by my mom's guiding words: “You can’t control what life throws at you, but you can control how you respond.” Many of you are countering our crisis of division with courage and kindness. Know that I’m listening, learning, and inspired.

name: John Hickenlooper
text: ICYMI: I'm asking you to interview me for President. Our country is in crisis, and we need someone who knows how to bring people together and get things done. This is my record, but I've never done it alone. Join me: https://bit.ly/2HdtKXw

Chip in at: http://bit.ly/2NHKFmf

name: John Hickenlooper
text: A strong and sustainable economy can't be built with smoke and mirrors. Under my watch, Colorado jumped from 40th in job creation to the #1 economy in the nation. Workforce development programs and educational initiatives have been the backbone of creating opportunity for all.

name: John Hickenlooper
text: When we stand tall for all we believe in and stand up against all that divides us, America will be stronger than ever. Contribute now to help us build a different kind of campaign.

name: John Hickenlooper
text: Equality, opportunity, security, and dignity for all Americans. Anyone who threatens that, threatens the fabric of America. Bottom line. In 2012, facing long odds, I called a special session with a Republican legislature to pass Civil Unions. And we got it done the next year.

name: John Hickenlooper
text: This country is a web of interconnected communities. Yesterday, one of our own was devastated by horrifying tornadoes. Alabama, we know we can't get back the lives lost, but we can - and will - help you recover and rebuild. We are so sorry, and we are here for you.

name: John Hickenlooper
text: Beating Donald Trump is essential, but it's not sufficient. We need lasting progressive change.

name: John Hickenlooper
text: I've stood up to bullies all my life, including the NRA. When gun violence shattered Aurora, CO in 2012, they tried to drown out those of us calling for action. We fought back and became the first Western state to pass universal background checks and ban high-capacity magazines.

name: John Hickenlooper
text: Climate action can't wait. We must rejoin the Paris Agreement and transition to a renewable economy. In CO, I got industry and environmentalists together to set some of the strictest methane regulations in the US, taking the equivalent of 320,000 cars off the road each year.

name: John Hickenlooper
text: Healthcare: it's a right, not a privilege. That's not just rhetoric, that's something I worked to make a reality as Governor of Colorado. We expanded Medicaid, created a health exchange, and now, nearly 95% of Coloradans have healthcare coverage.

name: John Hickenlooper
text: A lot of people are hearing about me for the first time and asking me about what I believe in.

name: John Hickenlooper
text:
I'm running for President and we're kicking things off with a Rocky Mountain-Style rally in Denver! Come join me, @NRateliff, @iamsuch, and more this Thursday in Civic Center Park starting at 6 PM. ⁣⁣

RSVP now for details and to secure your spot: http://hickenlooper.com/kickoff

name: John Hickenlooper
text:
If you had told me at this age I'd someday be an entrepreneur, I would have laughed. If you had told me I'd get into politics, I wouldn't have believed you. ⁣⁣
⁣
But today, this Geologist, Brewer, Mayor, and Governor is submitting his application to be your next President.⁣⁣

name: John Hickenlooper
text: We need a leader who can bring people together and get stuff done. As a successful entrepreneur, Mayor, and Governor, I’ve proven that I can build and lead amazing teams of talented people- a key ingredient to effecting real progressive change. I hope you'll join me.

name: John Hickenlooper

name: Jay Inslee

Denying climate change is not a strategy. Delaying climate action is not an option.

Our country has incredible capability when we have a shared vision -- and there's no better, more necessary or more urgent common purpose than defeating climate change.

name: Jay Inslee
text: It’s abundantly clear that the United States has led the world in carbon emissions. Now we must become the leader in fighting climate change -- and elect a leader who will get it done.

text: This was not a "couple of Facebook ads." The Russians not only purchased online ads but also, according to DOJ, hacked into state election databases and stole sensitive voter information of 500,000 people. This was an attack on our democracy.

text: Can’t believe I have to keep saying it: I believe in science. I just wish this administration did too — rolling back air pollution regulations is a direct threat to our health and our planet.

name: Amy Klobuchar
text: After numerous attempts to sabotage people’s health care, the number of Americans without insurance has RISEN under the Trump Administration. I am working to make sure all Americans have access to affordable health care.

name: Amy Klobuchar
text: The patent for insulin was granted nearly a century ago for $3 to make sure the medication remained affordable. So why are pharmaceutical companies allowing costs to skyrocket? I have a plan to lower prescription drug prices that we could get done now.

name: Amy Klobuchar
text: People in every corner of America should have access to broadband — I helped introduce a bill with my colleague @PattyMurray that takes an important step in that direction. As your president, I’ll work to connect every household to the internet by 2022.

name: Amy Klobuchar
text: Thank you to the big crowd who came out to the Waterhouse in Peterborough, New Hampshire this morning. And I loved the shirt!

name: Amy Klobuchar
text: Today is #EarthDay and I’m thinking about Fran and Jason whose house was devastated by the flooding in the Midwest this year. We must tackle climate change head on — that’s why I will rejoin the International Climate Agreement on Day One of my presidency.

name: Amy Klobuchar
text: Pleased to see an agreement for Stop and Shop workers that gives them the benefits they have earned. A victory for @UFCW and workers' rights!

name: Amy Klobuchar
text: I stand w/ @JeanneShaheen opposing voter suppression in New Hampshire & across the country. The last time I checked people don’t want to give up their freedom to vote. We could make it even easier if we passed my bill to register every eligible young person when they turn 18!

name: Amy Klobuchar
text: Family Easter hike to the top of New Hampshire’s Pack Monadnock! The Wapack Trail was a little muddy but wet tennis shoes can always dry.  We are the only ones up here and it is beautiful!

name: Amy Klobuchar
text: Thanks to First Congregational Church of Walpole, New Hampshire for taking in our family for a wonderful Easter service and coffee hour today.  Nice sermon by interim Minister Rev.Dr. Stinson. The church is looking for a minister in a beautiful town so call the search committee.

name: Amy Klobuchar
text: My prayers on this Easter Sunday are for the families of those killed and wounded by terrorists in the horrendous massacres in churches and other places in Sri Lanka.  Religious freedom is a human right that will never be defeated by hate.

name: Amy Klobuchar
text: Happy Easter!  Wishing everyone a day of faith and new beginnings. I always remember my mom on Easter and her egg tree and many traditions.  Here she is with Abigail many years ago. And no, I’m not making Abigail wear that Easter hat today!

name: Amy Klobuchar
text: Want a reminder to tune into Amy’s CNN Town Hall on Monday at 6CT? Sign up here and we’ll send you a note >> http://bit.ly/2Xw4DnH

name: Amy Klobuchar

name: Amy Klobuchar
text: Rebuilding America's infrastructure means investing in commuter rail to improve accessibility for our workers and prepare for the demands of a 21st-century economy.

name: Amy Klobuchar
text: As the daughter of a newspaperman, I grew up knowing just how important the free press is. Freedom of the press is essential to our democracy and I will always defend it.

name: Amy Klobuchar
text: Easter candy I never knew existed: gummy carrots, bunny corn and fried eggs.  Chutters, Littleton, New Hampshire.

name: Amy Klobuchar
text: Remembering the 13 killed and 24 wounded in the tragic shooting at Columbine High School. Twenty years have passed, but we haven’t made twenty years of progress on gun violence prevention. It’s time to pass gun safety legislation.

text:
Congrats to Minneapolis’ own @lizzo for her #1 album #CuzILoveYou which includes a really good line: 
“Woke up feeling like I just might run for president. Even if there ain't no precedent.”

name: Amy Klobuchar
text: First Page of Mueller report says that Russian government interfered in 2016 presidential election “in sweeping and systematic fashion.”  So despite the endless doubts cast by the President, this happened. Case made for my bill for backup paper ballots and post-election audits.

name: Amy Klobuchar
text: Black women are dying from pregnancy-related complications at 3x the rate of white women. We’ve got to recognize that this is a crisis and work to fix the system. #BlackMaternalHealthWeek

text: At the Heartland Forum in Storm Lake, Iowa today with a simple message: I will never leave rural America behind. My ideas? An agenda for rural America that includes housing, health care, broadband, education, strong farm and antitrust policies.

text: Last night I went all in with @chrislhayes on my #1 budget priority: fixing America’s crumbling infrastructure.

name: Amy Klobuchar
text: Over half of our schools need repairs to be considered in “good” condition. Just look at some of the schools in Baltimore that didn’t have heat in the dead of winter. We need to update the physical and digital infrastructure of our crumbling schools.

name: Amy Klobuchar
text: Last night I spoke until we closed down the Senate, reading 100 letters from people whose preexisting conditions would get them kicked off insurance w/o ACA. By announcing the repeal they actually became the party of “taking away people’s health care!”

name: Amy Klobuchar
text:
The letters I read tonight are just a small window into the fears of millions of Americans if the Affordable Care Act is eliminated. 

This isn't about politics, this is about people. And I will fight on their behalf to the very end.

name: Amy Klobuchar
text: In 2015, Jen donated a kidney to a stranger. Without the Affordable Care Act’s protections, she would have a pre-existing condition that could cause her to be denied or charged more for coverage.

name: Amy Klobuchar
text: As an educator, Elizabeth has seen the importance of the mental health coverage guaranteed by the Affordable Care Act. If the Affordable Care Act is eradicated, she worries about her students.

name: Amy Klobuchar
text: Jeffrey takes medication every 24-hours to stop the advance of his MS. He says that the Affordable Care Act has “allowed me to remain a productive wage earner for me and my family.”

name: Amy Klobuchar
text: Noel was able to recover from a chronic illness while staying on her parents’ health care plan. She’s worried that she’ll be punished for her pre-existing condition when she gets her own health care plan if the ACA is repealed.

name: Amy Klobuchar
text: Mike says, “My wife and I are uninsurable without the ACA.”

name: Amy Klobuchar
text: At 29, Chris was diagnosed with an aggressive form of cancer. Before the ACA, he wasn’t able to purchase health care insurance. If the ACA is repealed his family worries his life will be shortened.

name: Amy Klobuchar
text: Debbie is self-employed and runs two businesses. She says, “If the ACA is repealed and there is no marketplace for me to purchase insurance, I will be forced to close my businesses.”

name: Amy Klobuchar
text: Kathy needed 24-hour infusions for 5½ days during each round of chemotherapy during her battle with cancer. She writes, “Now that the ACA is up in the air, I feel like I’m fighting for my life again!”

name: Amy Klobuchar
text: Kate calls her son, "the baby that almost didn’t happen" after battling cancer. She wrote, "Because of the ACA, I faced a future of hope."

name: Amy Klobuchar
text: Because of the Affordable Care Act, Delaney is able to get mammogram screenings to see if she carries the same genetic trait that several of her relatives have.

name: Amy Klobuchar
text:
The Trump Administration supports totally undoing the Affordable Care Act. 

I’m headed to the Senate floor to read the letters of 100 families from across the country who would suffer if these protections went away.

text: We must invest in creating a universal flu vaccine that could protect against all strains of the flu virus and offer longer lasting protection. I’ve joined @SenMarkey @SenTinaSmith & others in introducing The Flu Vaccine Act to support this critical research.

name: Amy Klobuchar
text: Good discussion at today’s @amprog antitrust event with @RBReich & @neeratanden. When big businesses merge and drive out the competition, prices can go up and consumers often lose. I spoke about this last night with @hardballchris on @hardball.

name: Amy Klobuchar
text: We need to pass Senator @PattyMurray’s comprehensive child care proposal to ensure affordable, high-quality child care for families across the country. I’ve also introduced legislation to address the national shortage of affordable child care, especially in rural areas.

name: Amy Klobuchar
text: Good to be on @hardball with @HardballChris to talk about a positive economic agenda for this country: bringing down the cost of Rx drug prices, moving an infrastructure package forward & taking on the growing number of mega-mergers that can result in higher prices for consumers.

name: Amy Klobuchar
text: Thanks to my team members who braved the cold to door knock for @EricGiddens4IA! If you’re in this Iowa district, be sure to vote in the upcoming special election on March 19!

name: Amy Klobuchar
text: PSA to the White House: We need fewer climate deniers and more solutions.

name: Amy Klobuchar
text: The Administration’s policy at the border is putting lives in danger. It’s past time for comprehensive immigration reform.

name: Amy Klobuchar
text: The Administration’s new tax code and self-inflicted shutdown has left families across the country looking for answers at tax time. Americans deserve so much better.

name: Amy Klobuchar
text: Happy birthday to my friend and colleague @TinaSmithMN !!     (that’s it for my birthday emojis).

name: Amy Klobuchar
text: Congratulations @NASA & @SpaceX on this historic launch!

name: Amy Klobuchar
text: Rising sea levels are threatening America’s farms. We must take action immediately to address this devastating situation.

name: Amy Klobuchar
text: Because they are.

text:
A cool thing to celebrate this #WomensHistoryMonth: the record number of women serving in Congress. 

(Now, let’s get to work to make it 50%!)

name: Amy Klobuchar
text: We are celebrating Women’s History Month with some incredibly strong women. And we are ready to elect more.

name: Amy Klobuchar
text: OK, this photo taken at CPAC of President grabbing flag after embracing falsehoods of Kim Jong Un (& before that Putin & S.A. Prince) & after dissing Warmbier family, Justice Department & former FBI Director Mueller just says it all #PictureWorthAllWords

name: Amy Klobuchar
text: We should be making it easier for everyone to vote, not harder. Glad to see New Hampshire Democrats defending the Granite State’s tradition of voter participation.

name: Amy Klobuchar
text: Thanks to Fred and Cindy Warmbier for standing up in memory of their son Otto. The lesson? The President, in turn,  should be standing up to dictators like Kim Jong Un and Putin and the S.A. Prince.  Not flattering them by denying the clear truth of his own intelligence forces.

name: Amy Klobuchar
text: Good to see Minnesota-based @3M committing to a sustainable future!

name: Amy Klobuchar
text: It’s telling to see whose word the President trusts: Putin and Kim Jong Un. Who does he doubt? His own intelligence officials

name: Amy Klobuchar
text:
Time to make history for #WomensHistoryMonth, and celebrate four women senators running for President. Thanks to my friends  @KamalaHarris @SenGillibrand and @ewarren 
Just think...it wasn’t that long ago that we didn’t even have four women in the Senate!

name: Amy Klobuchar
text:
We should be supporting our transgender troops. Anyone brave enough to serve our country deserves our full respect.
http://time.com/5540716/transgender-troops-congress-military/ …

name: Amy Klobuchar
text: I voted against Mr. Wheeler’s nomination to lead the @EPA. We should not have someone who has worked to undo vital health protections as the person tasked with protecting our environment.

name: Amy Klobuchar
text:
New @VanderbiltU study names Amy most effective Dem Senator

“[Sen. Klobuchar] is the only minority-party senator to break the overall top five since 2002, and is only the second minority-party senator to do so since Sen. John McCain did it in 1994.”

name: Amy Klobuchar
text:
Exactly one year ago I sat across from the President during a meeting on gun safety at the White House where he said he supported expanded background checks nine times. Nothing has been done. 

Mr. President — the American people deserve a leader who can deliver.

name: Amy Klobuchar
text: Apprenticeships provide critical real-world skills — all while paying students. Glad to see more industries adopting this pathway to success.

name: Amy Klobuchar
text: A lot can happen when you work to find common ground and prioritize solutions. Thank you so much to my staff who work so hard for the people of our state and country.

name: Amy Klobuchar
text: Today I met with some of the inspiring students from March for Our Lives to discuss how we can make it easier for people to vote. That includes passing my bills to automatically register every eligible person when they turn 18 & give everyone the option of same day registration.

name: Amy Klobuchar
text: Asked Secretary Perdue today about problems with the Boundary Waters Canoe Area Wilderness (BWCAW) reservation system. He said it would be fixed by March 4th.

name: Amy Klobuchar
text: Questioned Secretary Perdue at the Ag Committee today about the vaccine bank (one of my Farm Bill provisions), dairy, E-15 and conservation.

text: Elijah Cummings says it best at the Cohen hearing: “As a country we are so much better than this.” @RepCummings

name: Amy Klobuchar
text: The Moscow Trump tower issue is real: Mr. Cohen acknowledged that he lied under oath to Congress about a Trump Tower project in Moscow, saying he was trying to protect Mr. Trump. “I am not protecting Mr. Trump anymore,” he said.

name: Amy Klobuchar
text: This is even a bigger deal:  Cohen has alleged that Trump knew in advance that the anti-secrecy organization WikiLeaks planned to publish hacked Democratic National Committee emails.

name: Amy Klobuchar
text: This is a big deal: Michael Cohen says President Trump was involved in a hush money scheme. He brought checks to Congress to prove it.…

text: If a foreign government is backing a Facebook page, we should be able to know that. We also need to pass my Honest Ads Act to get disclaimers and disclosures on on-line paid political ads across all major platforms.

text: We need to invest in our infrastructure again. It would bring good paying jobs, help us get goods to market, and make sure we're not sitting in traffic jams!

name: Amy Klobuchar
text: This national emergency order is unconstitutional.

name: Amy Klobuchar
text: Make no mistake: foreign adversaries will once again seek to interfere in the 2020 election. We must do everything we can to secure our elections before 2020.

name: Amy Klobuchar

text:
Insulin has tripled in price since 2002, and it’s making diabetics sick with worry — and just plain sick.

Pharmaceutical companies must be held accountable.

name: Amy Klobuchar
text: The science on climate change is clear. What’s unclear is why the President is considering wasting taxpayer money to try and prove otherwise.

name: Amy Klobuchar
text: Thanks Sarah for your good work and for sharing what is happening in Georgia. Our democracy is run by us and if people can’t vote it isn’t our democracy!

If you're ready to join this team, sign up now: http://amyklobuchar.com

name: Amy Klobuchar
text:
In Georgia, I sat down with leaders working to stop discriminatory voter suppression. We cannot allow the voices and votes of Americans to be stolen from them. 

And it was good to see @staceyabrams and Jimmy Carter!

text: In Iowa, I talked with people about about bridging the rural/urban divide at the sold out Ankeny Area Dems Winter Banquet. Because in the words of Paul Wellstone, “We all do better when we all do better.”

text: Over the last four days, we’ve been to Iowa, Georgia, South Carolina, and New Hampshire — and it has been an incredible journey.

name: Amy Klobuchar
text: Yes Lady Gaga! Great speech

text: Another packed house party — this time in Concord, NH! Thank you to everyone who braved the winter weather to come be a part of this campaign.

text: Rain or snow, we’re on the go. Great house party in New Hampshire today.

name: Amy Klobuchar
text: Banks are making billions, while workers are losing out. It’s time for a tax policy that puts middle class families first.

text: Long overdue recognition for trailblazer and inspiration, Katherine Johnson. Thank you for your tremendous contributions to science and our country.

name: Amy Klobuchar
text: When I say we're building a homegrown campaign, I mean it. Thank you to the hundreds of people who came out in Columbia, SC for our house party!

name: Amy Klobuchar
text: I’ve asked the Dept. of Education to immediately address the backlog of federal student loan forgiveness requests from borrowers who have been cheated or defrauded. Students should never have to worry about these scams as they look to improve their lives & careers.

name: Amy Klobuchar
text: This move would devastate critical health care providers — we must stand up and speak out.

name: Amy Klobuchar
text: The time for studying is over.  The time for action is here. The science is clear — our world is warming. Instead of addressing it, the President has added a climate change skeptic to his panel to examine the impact warming is having on our planet.

name: Amy Klobuchar
text: Good to be keynoting the first sold out @AnkenyAreaDems event.  Had a great time and so impressed by the work you did in 2018 electing @RepCindyAxne @hamatson with more to come! Thanks @marymcadams and the rest of the team. Thanks @bagniewski !!!

name: Amy Klobuchar
text: This is extremely concerning. Our adversaries tried to sow division in 2016 and undermine our democracy and it’s happening again. No matter which campaign is being targeted, we should all be on the side of working to prevent these hits from happening.

name: Amy Klobuchar
text:
During his nomination hearing, I asked Attorney General Barr to commit to releasing the Mueller findings. He did not. 

Now is the time to do the right thing.

text: More proof that Sackler and Purdue Pharmaceutical made deliberate decision to hook people on OxyContin just to profit off their addiction.  Now they should pay for their treatment.

text: As a former county attorney, I have seen the devastation caused by opioid abuse. My new bipartisan legislation with Senator Portman would require states to use prescription drug monitoring programs before prescribing powerful Rx drugs.

name: Amy Klobuchar
text: There’s no question about it — the federal minimum wage must be increased to $15 an hour.

name: Amy Klobuchar
text: Prescription drug prices are out of control. We need to stand up to the pharmaceutical companies and bring costs down.

name: Amy Klobuchar
text: Now more than ever it’s critical for Attorney General Barr to commit to releasing these findings to the public.

name: Amy Klobuchar
text: Yep!

text: We need more participation in our democracy, not less. That’s why I want to pass a bill to automatically register every eligible person to vote when they turn 18.

Lots of delicious soup too!

text: Thank you so much for your neighborly kindness, Wisconsin! I’m so grateful to the people of Eau Claire for coming out today.

name: Amy Klobuchar
text: Thanks to everyone for turning out big time in Eau Claire!  My mom grew up in Wisconsin (still home to my Aunt Jane and Uncle Dick) and yes, we have a cheese making heritage in Monroe and beyond. To quote the Wisconsin motto “FORWARD!”

name: Amy Klobuchar
text: Almost there and ready for Eau Claire!  (It rhymes).

text: Governing from chaos once again (and this time at the expense of the Constitution, the Congress, the will of the people and...oh yes...our nation’s security needs): In Wielding Emergency Powers, Trump Paves a Dangerous Path Forward

name: Amy Klobuchar
text: We are all thinking of those who lost loved ones in Aurora, Illinois today.  We remember that the victims went to work today just to do their jobs...as did the officers who put themselves right in the line of fire to save others.

name: Amy Klobuchar
text: States should not be able to purge “inactive voters” from the voting rolls, an act that disproportionately hurts minority or low-income voters. My SAVE VOTERS Act with @SherrodBrown protects voting rights by ensuring that states cannot purge eligible voters. Let’s pass it.

name: Amy Klobuchar
text:
Both sides of my family arrived in America with nothing but a suitcase, looking for a better life for their families. Their story isn’t so different from people working towards opportunity today.

It’s past time for comprehensive immigration reform.

name: Amy Klobuchar
text: Not getting what you want to fulfill a campaign promise/chant is not a national emergency.  Taking money from real needs and emergencies is what will create an actual emergency.

name: Amy Klobuchar
text: Our government must be prepared to fight the threats of tomorrow, especially cyberwarfare.  That’s why I’ve introduced new bipartisan legislation with Sen. Thune aimed at bringing more cybersecurity expertise to the federal workforce.

name: Amy Klobuchar
text: I put the digital revolution front-and-center in my announcement speech. From privacy to cybersecurity, this is a pressing public policy question that needs strong leadership.

name: Amy Klobuchar
text: We’ve come a long way. Happy Valentine’s Day, John!

name: Amy Klobuchar
text: We’re tired of being governed by chaos. The Congress has spoken on a bipartisan basis.  Not getting what you want to fulfill a campaign promise/chant is not a national emergency.

name: Amy Klobuchar
text: We must follow their example and get to work. There is a consensus in this country that we need commonsense gun safety legislation. I’m ready to work across the aisle to get it done.

name: Amy Klobuchar
text: On the anniversary of the Parkland shooting which claimed 17 lives, students everywhere are refusing to stay silent. Since that day, 1,200 kids have died from gun related violence. Students have written an obituary for every single one of them.

name: Amy Klobuchar
text: My statement on AG nominee William Barr:

name: Amy Klobuchar
text: Today we honor Rep. John Dingell & fitting that it’s on Valentine’s Day—he loved Debbie so very much & also, of course, his country. As we say goodbye, I’m reflecting on his legacy of fighting for what’s right with a big smile & a twinkle in his eye. He got a lot done that way.

name: Amy Klobuchar
text:
I promise you this: As your President, I will look you in the eye. I will tell you what I think. I will focus on getting things done. That’s what I’ve done my whole life.

This was just one of the many tricks of the Republican tax bill and why I didn’t vote for it.

The Big Pharma companies think they own Washington.

text:
Science is on my side, @realDonaldTrump. Looking forward to debating you about climate change (and many other issues). And I wonder how your hair would fare in a blizzard?  

Everyone else can join my team and contribute at http://amyklobuchar.com

name: Amy Klobuchar
text: Let’s join together, as one nation, indivisible, under God, and pursue the good.

text:
I’m asking you to join us on this campaign. It’s a homegrown one.

I don’t have a political machine. I don’t come from money. But what I do have is this: I have grit. 

Join us: http://amyklobuchar.com/donate

name: Amy Klobuchar
text: Stop the fear-mongering and stop the hate. We may come from different places. We may pray in different ways. We may look different. And love different. But we all live in the same country of shared dreams.

name: Amy Klobuchar
text:
There are insidious forces every day that are trying to make it harder for people to vote, trying to drown out our voices with big money.

It’s time to organize. Time to galvanize. Time to take back our democracy. 

It’s time, America!

name: Amy Klobuchar
text: I stand before you as the granddaughter of an iron ore miner, the daughter of a teacher and a newspaperman, the first woman elected to the United States Senate from the State of Minnesota, to announce my candidacy for President of the United States.

name: Amy Klobuchar
text:
We are all tired of the shutdowns and the showdowns, the gridlock and the grandstanding. 

Today we say enough is enough.

http://amyklobuchar.com

name: Amy Klobuchar
text: Thank you @GovTimWalz and @LtGovFlanagan for being here today and for your kind words. I'm excited about the work we've done together and where we go from here.

name: Amy Klobuchar
text: I’ve been friends with @TinaSmithMN for many years and now we’re colleagues in the Senate. Thank you, Tina, for being here today and for always having my back.

name: Beto O'Rourke
