text: “Democrats are frantic to throw something else at the President. That’s why you saw those 81 subpoenas. It’s ridiculous. Just because your still upset over an election that happened 2 1/2 years ago, you should not be allowed to ruin people’s lives like this.” Lara Trump, @FoxNews

name: Donald Trump
text: I agree with Rand Paul. This is a total disgrace and should NEVER happen to another President!

name: Donald Trump
text: “The Lisa Page (FBI) transcript also confirms earlier reporting that Page testified Russian Collusion was still unproven when Special Counsel Robert Mueller was appointed.” Catherine Herridge, @FoxNews  In other words they appointed someone when there was (and is) no crime. Bad!

name: Donald Trump
text: “Double Standard - Former FBI lawyer (Lisa Page) admits being told to go easy on Clinton.”  Very unfair!  @FoxNews

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: Tonight I’ll be on @allinwithchris to talk about how it’s never been more important to defend our constitution and fight for our democracy. Tune in to @MSNBC at 8 PM ET!

name: Elizabeth Warren
text:
There are three inescapable facts from the Mueller report that Mitch McConnell can't hide:
1. A foreign government attacked our elections in order to help Donald Trump.
2. Trump welcomed that help.
3. Trump tried to obstruct the investigation into his actions.

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: Mitch McConnell is protecting and defending Donald Trump—not our Constitution or democracy. Congress needs to do its job and start impeachment proceedings now.

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: Mitch McConnell took the same oath of office as I did: To protect and defend the Constitution of the United States—not to protect and defend Donald Trump. Every elected official should read the Mueller report. Then Congress should do its job and begin impeachment proceedings.

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: Looks like a great walk—wish Bruce and I could have joined with Bailey! #WinWithWarren

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: My plan would wipe out student loan debt for millions of Americans—and I’ve got a calculator to show you how much you’d save.

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: Any efforts to address climate change must include our public lands. That’s why on the first day of a Warren administration, I will sign  a total moratorium on all new fossil fuel leases, including for drilling offshore and on public lands.

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: Our grassroots team is growing! Over half of our staff is on the ground in the early primary and caucus states, and I need your help to keep up the momentum. Chip in $5, or whatever you can, to power this grassroots campaign.

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: Somebody’s ready for spring.

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: Ramadan Mubarak! Bruce and I send our wishes for a blessed and meaningful month for all who observe.

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: My 2nd grade teacher, Mrs. Lee, told me that if I worked hard, I could be a teacher, too. That changed my world, and I’m still grateful. Thank you to our teachers across the country who fight every day so that our kids have the opportunity to succeed. #TeacherAppreciationWeek

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: Last week, I re-introduced legislation that would provide Puerto Rico with a path to comprehensive debt relief. We won’t stop fighting until the people of Puerto Rico get the respect they deserve. Add your name here to say you’re with me on this:

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: I heard you loud and clear! Baby onesies are available on our online store (perfect for your pint-sized persisters). http://shop.elizabethwarren.com

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: Dominic, Kanu, Morgan, and Madeline all have big goals they want to reach—but student loan debt is holding them back. It’s time to address this problem head on, and that’s what my new plan does.

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: It does! And you can see exactly how much debt would be cancelled by using my new calculator: http://elizabethwarren.com/debt

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: Sixty-four percent of Florida voters approved an amendment to their state constitution that would restore voting rights to ex-felons—but Republicans are working hard to undermine the will of the people. It’s outrageous.

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: .@JulianCastro is right—no person is illegal, and our laws should reflect that. I admire his smart ideas on reforming our immigration laws. We should all pay attention to them.

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: Our grassroots movement is growing in South Carolina. Follow @SCforWarren for #TeamWarren updates from SC and information on how to join our fight. Let’s do this together!

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: Thank you, Osage and Mason City! Had a powerful conversation today about how we can level the playing field for working families in Iowa—and across the country.

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: Woo-hoo! I’m grateful that you’re dreaming big and fighting hard in Indiana.

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: No spoilers!

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: I'm thrilled that the courts are holding Republicans accountable for their disgraceful partisan gerrymandering. But if we truly want to break their grip on power, we'll need to elect Dems across the country, up and down the ballot *before* redistricting.

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: It’s possible! Let’s keep growing our movement to make it a reality.

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: I’ve got a plan to cancel student loan debt for over 95% of Americans with student loans—and a calculator to help you figure out how much of your debt would be cancelled. Try it out and let me know how it goes! http://elizabethwarren.com/debt

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: Dreaming big, fighting hard, and living proud!

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: Grateful down to my toes for every single person in this movement. Let’s keep fighting hard!

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: Yesterday, I stopped by our Win With Warren organizing house party in Iowa Falls—and oh boy, was there some great energy in the room. Iowa is in this fight all the way.

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: Women should be able to control our own bodies. Our rights aren’t just threatened in Alabama —all across the country, safe, legal abortion access is under attack. You bet I’ll keep fighting to protect it.

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: Thank you, Ames!

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: How much of your student loan debt could get canceled under my new plan? Give our new calculator a try: https://elizabethwarren.com/debt  #CancelMyDebt

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: No one understands Iowa Democratic politics quite like Jan Bauer does. I’m grateful we had the opportunity to chat today about this grassroots fight and the work she does to grow this movement!

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: John Kelly pushed for family separation while in the White House. Now he'll profit off of separating mamas from their babies. It’s immoral, and under my plan to #EndCorruptionNow it would be illegal for someone like Kelly to do this.

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: It was great talking to you, @ZachWahls. I’m inspired by your dedication to the people of Iowa.

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: HBCUs have had to do more with less, and that’s wrong. We need to call out the discrimination that led us to this point, and we need to live up to our obligations. That means we need to start investing in HBCUs.

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: I've got a plan to cancel student loan debt for 42 million Americans—and we've got a new calculator to help you figure out how much of your debt would be cancelled. Give it a try & tell us how much of your student loan debt will be cancelled. #CancelMyDebt

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: Right now, Wall Street is squeezing Puerto Rico. We must do better by our fellow U.S. citizens. That’s why I have a plan to provide comprehensive debt relief to Puerto Rico so it can rebuild and thrive.

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: Grace, I’m so glad to have you on our team.

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: The flooding across eastern Iowa is just one example of how climate change is affecting us in real time. It’s our moral obligation to fight for our planet before it’s too late. Thank you for stepping up and helping the community, Karen!

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: A hostile foreign power attacked our democracy. The president welcomed that attack, obstructed the investigation into it, & is now cozying up with the leader who orchestrated it. Congress needs to do its job, stand up for our national security, and begin impeachment proceedings.

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: Health care is a human right, and we fight for human rights. #MedicareForAll

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: Grace from New Hampshire is absolutely right. My new plan to cancel student debt for 95% of Americans and make public college free would level the playing field for all of our students—not just a select few.

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: About a third of US student loan debt is held by people over the age of 40. The student loan debt crisis is a burden on all of us, and my plan to cancel debt for 95% of Americans with student loan debt helps everyone get ahead.

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: Candidates for president don’t always go to Utah or Tennessee or Alabama because they aren’t battleground states. But this is a 50-state campaign, and I'm traveling to every corner of our country because I’m running to be president of the entire United States.

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: The flooding in Davenport and across eastern Iowa is heartbreaking. Climate change is here, and it’s up to us to act.

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: On Yom HaShoah, we pause to remember the millions of victims of the Holocaust. This year, Remembrance Day falls in the shadow of yet another attack on a synagogue. We must keep fighting anti-Semitism, bigotry, racism, and hate.

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: I missed Shannon on the first try, and then I saw her tweet asking to call her back—so I did. I’m deeply grateful for Shannon and her dedication to this grassroots movement.

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: En Estados Unidos, se necesita un liderazgo que respete a todos sus ciudadanos—y en el caso de Puerto Rico, el respeto significa poner las vidas de millones de ciudadanos por encima de los márgenes de ganancia de Wall Street.

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: Puerto Rico shows us a clear example of how well the federal government works for Wall Street and how poorly it works for everyone else. I believe we should fight back—and treat Puerto Rico with respect.

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: Crippling student loan debt is holding families back. My new plan would change that for Valerie from South Carolina, and millions of other Americans across the country.

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: Esta legislación establecería una avenida para el alivio comprensivo de la deuda de Puerto Rico. Puedes leer todos los detalles aquí.

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: Los ejecutivos de Wall Street ven la desesperación en la isla como una oportunidad para obtener ganancias—y eso me da asco. Por eso estoy presentado nuevamente el Acta de Alivio para los Territorios Estadounidenses.

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: El Congreso tuvo la oportunidad de romper con el control de Wall Street. En vez de hacerlo, aprobaron una legislación llamada PROMESA, estableciendo una junta de supervisión fiscal que exigió recortes a servicios básicos, coartando la posibilidad de recuperación para PR.

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: Sin embargo, por causa de su estatus único, esas avenidas legales no están a su alcance. Gran parte de la deuda está en manos de Wall Street, quienes intentan exprimir hasta el último centavo de ganancia.

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: Si Puerto Rico fuera una corporación grande o una ciudad en los Estados Unidos en este tipo de crisis financiera, podría declararse en bancarrota: pagando parte de su deuda, liquidando el resto y así comenzar a reconstruir.

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: Los huracanes Irma y María devastaron a Puerto Rico y a los millones de ciudadanos estadounidenses que viven en la isla. Queda claro que la respuesta de la administración de Trump fue inefectiva, pero una de las mayores limitaciones frenando la recuperación recae en su deuda.

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: Wall Street executives see the island’s desperation as just another opportunity to make a profit—and it makes me sick. That’s why I’m re-introducing the U.S. Territorial Relief Act to provide Puerto Rico with a path to comprehensive debt relief.

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: Much of Puerto Rico’s debt is held by Wall Street, which is trying to squeeze out every last penny of profit. Congress had a chance to break Wall Street's grip. Instead, they passed PROMESA, imposing an oversight board which has slashed services, hindering the recovery.

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: If Puerto Rico were a big company or an American city in this kind of financial trouble, it could file for bankruptcy, pay some of its debts, discharge the rest, then start rebuilding. But because of its unique status, those legal options aren’t available.

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: Hurricanes Irma and Maria devastated Puerto Rico and the millions of U.S. citizens who live there. The Trump Administration's response was slow and ineffective—but one of the biggest constraints holding back the recovery has been Puerto Rico's debt.

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: My three big brothers served in the military: Don Reed and John joined the Air Force, and David joined the Army. I’m glad I got to talk with and listen to military families in Nevada on Saturday. They deserve better and you bet I’m going to keep fighting for them.

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: Hate has no place in our country. The threat of white nationalism is real. And when I'm president, the Justice Department will prosecute domestic terrorists to the full extent of the law.

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: The American people know we must take bold steps to address our student debt crisis. By asking the top 0.1% to pay their fair share, we can cancel student loans for 42 million Americans. That wouldn’t just help our students, it would help all of us.

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: Unions built the middle class, and unions will rebuild the middle class. I’m grateful I got the chance to talk with @SEIU members in Nevada last weekend.

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: Covering our eyes won't change the facts. It's long past time to bring our troops home from Afghanistan.

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: Since today is Bailey’s birthday, here’s a little something to celebrate! Our team has Bailey-themed bandanas and a lot more at our online store: http://shop.elizabethwarren.com

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: May is Asian Pacific American Heritage Month—an important time to honor #AAPI Americans and their history. I’m grateful for the AAPI leaders across the country who are driving the fight for big, structural change in their communities. #APAHM

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: Donald Trump isn’t king, and no one is above the law. We know Barr's deceptive "summary" was intended to protect the man in the White House, and Congress should begin impeachment proceedings against the President.

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: This is outrageous. We need answers on how @DHSgov obtained surveillance data from family separation protests and how that data was used.

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: AG Barr is a disgrace, and his alarming efforts to suppress the Mueller report show that he's not a credible head of federal law enforcement. He should resign—and based on the actual facts in the Mueller report, Congress should begin impeachment proceedings against the President.

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: It’s Bailey’s 1st birthday! Bruce and I are so grateful for this sweetie and the gentleness he brings into our lives. Happy birthday, boy. You make my heart happy.

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: On #MayDay, I’m thinking about our country’s long history of workers making their voices heard and demanding change—just like the Lawrence, MA mill workers did over a century ago. The Bread and Roses strike inspires me to this day, and reminds us to keep fighting for our rights.

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: I've read the Mueller report, and one thing is very clear: Donald Trump is the most corrupt president in our lifetime, and Congress should begin impeachment proceedings. No one is above the law. Not even the President.

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: I'm heartsick for the victims of the #UNCC shooting and their family, friends, and classmates. Schools should be a safe haven for students and faculty, but again we see a horrific act of violence on a school campus. Enough is enough.

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: Special Counsel Robert Mueller's letter objecting to the Attorney General's characterization of his report confirms what we already suspected: Barr's "summary" was a willfully deceptive interpretation intended to protect the man in the White House.

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: Free public college. Universal child care. Affordable housing. Yep, I’ve got a plan for all that—and more. But it starts with growing our grassroots movement so we can win in 2020. Chip in what you can and you might get a call from me to say thanks.

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: This is a campaign of ideas—and you bet I have a lot of them. It’s about identifying what’s broken and how we’re going to make the structural change to fix it.

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: Some giant companies make billions of dollars in profits but pay $0 in corporate income tax. My Real Corporate Profits Tax would make big and profitable companies pay their fair share and ensure none of them ever pay zero taxes again.

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: Thank you, Ady. I’m so grateful to call you my friend. We’re in this fight together.

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: Karen from New Hampshire has seen first hand how students are getting crushed by mountains of student loan debt. By making public colleges free and canceling student debt for 95% of Americans, we’ll do good by our students and our economy.

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: Every year that Washington keeps working for the rich and the powerful, Medicare is more likely to come under attack. Enough is enough. We need to protect and expand Medicare. #MedicareForAll

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: It was great meeting you, too. Unions built the middle class and unions will rebuild the middle class. I’m with you all the way.

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: I’m not taking PAC money or donations from federal lobbyists. I’m also not schmoozing with wealthy donors behind closed doors. That’s why I need your help. Help hit our April fundraising goal and chip in to our Official 2020 Campaign.

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: Black women are 3 to 4 times more likely than white women to die from pregnancy or childbirth-related causes. A major reason? Racism. It's time to hold health systems accountable for protecting Black moms.

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: If you own a home, you’re already paying a wealth tax—it’s called a property tax. I just want the ultra-rich to pay a wealth tax on the diamonds, the yachts, and the Rembrandts too.

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: Our democracy is not for sale, and neither is my time. That’s why this campaign is powered by grassroots donors. We have less than 48 hours to hit our April fundraising goal—will you chip in what you can?

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: It was great to be in Las Vegas again this weekend to talk about how we’re going to fight for big, structural change. See you again soon!

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: She used to lobby for a Ukrainian oligarch. Now the Trump administration wants to give her a plum job at the Treasury Department. Under my plan to #EndCorruptionNow, it’d be illegal for former lobbyists like her to work for our government.

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: What would it be like to have a woman in the White House? I think it’d be great—and the crowd in Cedar Rapids last week agreed.

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: Women should be able to control our own bodies. Full stop.

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: Outrageous. Filing taxes should be simple and free. Big financial corporations like TurboTax shouldn’t be able to scam consumers like this—and my Tax Simplification Act would fix that.

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: For most candidates, “call time” means calling wealthy donors and asking for money. Not me. I’m spending “call time” thanking small-dollar, grassroots donors who give what they can. Chip in what you can, and you might get a call from me to say thank you: http://elizabethwarren.com/chip-in

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: Busy weekend in Iowa and Nevada. Somebody was waiting for me to come home!

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: Unions built America’s middle class and unions will rebuild America’s middle class. Thanks @SEIU and @CAPAction for inviting me to speak at the #WorkersForum!

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: Thank you, Iowa, for the warm welcome and for helping make Bruce’s birthday weekend truly special! We look forward to seeing you again soon.

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: I was proud to take the #WeAreIndivisible pledge—now let's do the work we need to do to defeat Trump in 2020.

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: I'm heartsick for the victims of today's horrific attack at the Chabad of Poway and their families. No one should ever have to face hatred and violence in a place of worship. It's on all of us to stand up to the rising threat of anti-semitism, racism, and hate.

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: As I told @JoyAnnReid, we've got to get organized, get mobilized, and build a grassroots movement if we want to make big, structural change. And we'll need a president who is willing to fight for it every inch of the way.

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: On her birthday, we remember activist and civil rights hero Coretta Scott King. Her powerful voice continues to resonate across the country—and we will never let anyone silence it. Nevertheless, we persist.

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: The food—and Bruce—were both better than ever. Happy birthday, sweetie.

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: I ordered him a huge lunch, and he wolfed down every bite. At the end, he said he loved it. Right then, I knew this was a guy I could live with forever. This week we were back in Houston for She the People, and we went back to Ninfa’s.

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: The first time Bruce came to Houston to meet my family, I picked him up at the airport and drove him directly to my favorite Tex-Mex place, Ninfa’s on Navigation. He’d grown up in Massachusetts and everything in this part of the world was new.

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: Today is Bruce's birthday, so yesterday we celebrated with cake. I’m very lucky to have him by my side this weekend in Iowa—and for all of life’s big adventures. Happy birthday, Bruce!

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: Surprise, surprise. The man in the White House wants to give a top government job to another one of his rich buddies. Barry Myers is a walking conflict of interest who doesn't belong anywhere near @NOAA.

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: I’m so glad to have you on our team, Dan!

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: Here's my plan: We fight side by side, @MajorPhilebrity.

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: On #LesbianVisibilityDay, I want to be clear: You matter. We see you. We won’t stop fighting until everyone is free to love without fear or discrimination.

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: People come up to me, introduce themselves, and then tell me how much student loan debt they have. Their debt is keeping them from buying homes, starting businesses, and pursuing the careers they want. It's time to cancel the debt that is crushing an entire generation.

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: Universal child care. Affordable housing. Student loan debt cancellation and universal free college. Yup, I’ve got a plan for that—and more.

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: Coastal communities have made it clear: No more offshore drilling that hurts our planet. On day one of a Warren administration, I promise to sign a total moratorium on new offshore drilling.

name: Elizabeth Warren
text:
This week at @_shethepeople, I was asked if I’m afraid voters will think white male candidates are “safer” than voting for a woman.

I’m not afraid—not by a long shot.

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: Today, I’m thinking about the Iowans whose lives were torn apart by intense flooding this spring, and the first responders who are helping keep people safe. Climate change is real—and we need big, structural change to tackle it head on.

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: Yesterday’s meet and greet in Linn County was a meaningful one. People are fired up for big, structural change.

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: Today I’m rolling out a plan to improve our military housing, protect families from abuse, and hold private developers accountable. The very least we owe those who proudly defend our country and their families is a safe, affordable place to live.

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: Military families have been living with lead paint, faulty wiring, ceilings collapsing, and mice infestations. Mold has taken over entire rooms. Kids are getting sick from living in these homes. That's not how we should treat our servicemembers—and it needs to stop now.

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: A handful of private developers have taken over 99% of domestic military family housing. Driven by short-term payoffs and with no meaningful oversight, contractors have failed to maintain the homes they were entrusted with—and families are suffering the consequences.

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: The legacy of racist redlining practices still haunts Black and Brown communities. It’s wrong. Yesterday at #SheThePeople2020, I talked about my new housing plan that would level the playing field for communities of color.

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: New Hampshire is getting squeezed by our country’s opioid epidemic. Last month I had the opportunity to visit Friendship House, an opioid treatment center in Bethlehem, and had powerful conversations with patients about how we can end this crisis.

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: I wanted to be a teacher since 2nd grade. Here I am with my doll collection—I used to line them up and play “school.” Later, I had the chance to be a special education teacher and a law professor because America invested in kids like me. We need to invest in kids again. #TBT

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: More proof that Amazon has too much power. Tech monopolies hurt small businesses, innovation, and consumers. #BreakUpBigTech

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: Thank you for a great conversation, @JoyAnnReid.

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: Five years. An entire generation of children has lived all or most of their lives without access to clean, safe water. Activists like @LittleMissFlint have been fighting tirelessly for Flint—but we must do better to ensure no community ever faces a crisis like this ever again.

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: Donald Trump’s White House is a product of a system that’s rigged in favor of the rich and the powerful. But this is our time to change that. Join our fight to win in 2020 and return the power to the people: https://elizabethwarren.com/fight

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: This is despicable. A young life was lost and a family is grieving because of anti-LGBTQ+ comments like these. My thoughts and prayers are with the friends and family of Nigel Shelby. To the LGBTQ+ community: You are loved. You matter. You are deserving.

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: Climate change is real and it is here—just ask farmers in Iowa who have felt the change in growing seasons, excessive flooding, and about $2 billion in damage to communities. We need real solutions like a #GreenNewDeal—and we need them now.

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: There is a student loan debt crisis, and it’s holding an entire generation back—from reducing home ownership rates to forcing students to drop out of school before getting a degree. It’s unacceptable and I want to change that. #CancelMyDebt

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: In Iowa, I met family farmers who are getting squeezed by decades of policies that favor giant agribusinesses like Bayer-Monsanto. Time for better policy choices . Learn more about my plan to level the playing field for America’s family farmers: https://elizabethwarren.com/farmers

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: Giant agribusinesses like these have too much power, and family farms are getting hurt. My plan to level the playing field for America’s farmers tackles consolidation in the agriculture sector head on.

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: This is a slap on the wrist—a fraction of the profits Facebook makes in a year. Facebook is a repeat offender & fines like this won’t stop them from breaking the law & violating our privacy again. It's going to take big, structural change. #BreakUpBigTech

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: I’m so grateful for the work that @MOVE_texas does to register and turn out voters—it was so good to meet these powerful women and thank them for their work!

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: What a powerful room. Honored and grateful down to my toes. Thank you, @_shethepeople!

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: We have to right the wrongs for communities of color. And that starts by addressing the legacy of discrimination in our country.

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: Black moms in our country are dying from childbirth-related causes 3-4 times more often than white moms. Any meaningful solution to our maternal mortality crisis must address structural racism as a root cause of this problem. My new idea would tackle this crisis head on.

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: Grateful to be part of such a powerful conversation at #SheThePeople2020 this afternoon. Our country needs to do better by women of color—and for me, it starts with addressing and tackling the Black maternal mortality crisis head on.

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: We've done this in other areas of health care. Let's do it here. If providers deliver quality care to Black moms, they’ll make more. If they don’t, they’ll make less. Don't just observe and debate racism in health care. Make providers pay until this crisis is fixed. #SheThePeople

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: Advocates are forcing Black maternal mortality into the conversation. There are important ideas on the table. Here's mine: Hit health care providers in their wallets. Make it unacceptable for providers to tolerate our high rates of moms dying—especially Black moms. #SheThePeople

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: The evidence all points in the same direction. The mistreatment of Black and Brown women around maternal health is the direct result of institutional and structural racism. We need bold solutions to the epidemic of maternal mortality in America. #SheThePeople

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: Moms in our country are dying from childbirth at rates almost 40% higher than in other wealthy countries—and the Black maternal mortality rate is 3-4 times higher than it is for white moms, across all income levels. We have to call it out. #SheThePeople

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: The treatment of women and infants is a direct reflection of the values of a society—and the U.S. has the worst maternal mortality rate in the developed world. It's a national disgrace. Today, I talked about my idea to fix it. #SheThePeople

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: Student loan debt is holding back an entire generation and crushing families—but we can change that. José María, Eva, Jayme, Alexandria, Tasha, Alicia, and Michael have big plans for what they could do if we cancel their debt.

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: We need to start fixing our higher education system so it better serves everyone—including communities of color. That's why my plan invests a minimum of $50 billion in HBCUs and Minority-Serving Institutions (MSIs).

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: I’m grateful for the conversations we had in Keene and Weare last weekend about the future of our country. We're going to do this together!

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: We need to act on climate change before it’s too late. That’s why I’m making a promise. On the first day of a Warren administration, I’ll sign a total moratorium on all new fossil fuel leases, including for drilling offshore and on public lands.

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: We won’t go back on women’s health—not now, not ever. The Trump administration's gag rule is immoral, dangerous, and illegal. Period. #ProtectX

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: Go, Jane!

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: It was great meeting Ricardo at @AllenUniv in South Carolina yesterday. I’m grateful that young people like him are in this fight all the way to cancel debt for 95% of Americans and make public colleges free.

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: Young people in our country, like Aubrey from Utah, are getting absolutely crushed by student loan debt. It doesn’t have to be this way and I’ve got a plan to tackle the debt crisis head on.

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: I want every girl to grow up knowing that they can fight from the heart—and that they can win. So when I meet a little girl on the campaign trail, I say: “I’m running for president, because that’s what girls do.” And we pinky promise that they’ll remember.

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: When Amazon can tilt the online marketplace in its own favor, small businesses see an immediate impact in their profits. That can be absolutely crushing, it's not fair, and I’m fighting to end that.

name: Elizabeth Warren

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: This campaign isn’t like the others. I don’t get my money from PACs, corporate lobbyists, or fancy fundraisers. This movement is 100% powered by the people: Small-dollar donors who chip in $10 here, $5 there. Will you join our fight?

name: Elizabeth Warren

name: Elizabeth Warren

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: This is a campaign about ideas and big, structural change. This is what we’re fighting for—and we’re just getting started.

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: Our corporate income tax rules are riddled with loopholes, exemptions, and deductions. Even companies that tell shareholders they have made more than a billion dollars in profits can end up paying no corporate income taxes. I want to tackle that problem head on.

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: To ensure every corporation pays their fair share,  we need a new kind of tax that big companies can’t get around. That’s what my new tax idea would accomplish.

name: Elizabeth Warren

name: Elizabeth Warren

name: Elizabeth Warren
text:
I guess Rep. Brady is fine with 60 of the biggest corporations in the US paying $0 in taxes on a combined $79 billion in profits—while the rest of us pay federal taxes to fund our military, our roads, and our bridges.

I'm not, and my Real Corporate Profits Tax would fix that.

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: My new idea, the Real Corporate Profits Tax, would fix some huge holes in our corporate tax code. Giant companies like Amazon shouldn’t be able to get away with paying $0 in federal corporate income taxes. Add your name if you agree. http://elizabethwarren.com/corporate-taxes

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: So today I’m proposing a new idea: Tax the *real profits* very large American companies report to their investors—no loopholes or exemptions—and let’s make this year the last year any company with massive profits pays zero federal taxes.

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: Big corporations have lobbied relentlessly to fill our corporate tax rules with so many loopholes and exemptions that even when they report a billion dollars in profits to their investors and the public, they can report much lower “profits” to the IRS—and pay no taxes on them.

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: If you've already filed your taxes this year, chances are you paid more than a lot of the big corporations. They made hundreds of millions of dollars in profits this year—but many of them won’t pay a dime towards keeping our country safe and our economy strong.

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: Wishing a happy #NationalSiblingsDay to my three big brothers: Don Reed, David, and John. All three of them answered our country’s call to serve. I’m eternally grateful for their service and the service of all our men and women in uniform.

name: Elizabeth Warren

name: Elizabeth Warren

name: Elizabeth Warren

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: We need to rebuild unions in this country. That's why I’ve proposed a new law banning states from passing so-called right to work laws that destroy labor unions. It will make sure that unions have a front-and-center seat at the table in any trade negotiation.

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: Unions have always been the backbone of our country—and I’ll always fight for them.

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: In life, there are some people who have more money. There are some people who have less money. But everybody should have an equal share of our democracy—no matter how much you donate. Let’s keep fighting hard, and if you’re able, make a donation today:

name: Elizabeth Warren

name: Elizabeth Warren

name: Elizabeth Warren

name: Elizabeth Warren

name: Elizabeth Warren

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: But we need to go further. From Equifax to BP, top executives across the country have overseen corporate conduct that has done real harm to American families—and walked away without any jail time.

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: Congress should start by enacting the Ending Too Big To Jail Act I introduced last year. This bill would make it easier to hold executives at big banks criminally liable for scams.

name: Elizabeth Warren
text: It’s been 10 years since the financial crash cost millions of people their homes, jobs, and savings. But not one big bank CEO has gone to jail. It’s time to reform our laws to make sure that corporate executives face jail time for overseeing massive scams.

text: Where there is love, anything is possible. Where there is love, nature organizes itself. Where there is love, life selfcorrects. One of the greatest evils ever foisted onto humanity was the thought that this has nothing to do with politics.

name: Marianne Williamson
text: Whether it’s a personal relationship or political policy, the key to right action is to act in passionate service to love. #marianne2020

text: About universal healthcare, free college & cancelling college loans, many ask how we can pay for it. We begin by repealing huge tax cuts to richest individuals & corps, plus absurd subsidies. $27B last year to fossil fuel companies?! Amazon made $100B & paid 0 in federal taxes?!

name: Marianne Williamson
text: Our current political malfunction  is an outgrowth of the environment from which it emerged: a society that had put aside its heart, conscience & political principles in favor of craven economics. Only way to  remove the lower manifestation is to retrieve the higher consciousness

name: Marianne Williamson
text: Forget the political dog & pony show; it’s toxic and silly and can only produce more of the same. Enter instead what’s emerging from the American heart: the deep waters of a collective yearning to pull ourselves out of the downward spiral into which we have descended as a nation.

name: Marianne Williamson
text: Only love has the ultimate power to triumph over hate. Only a political movement genuinely rooted in love for our country and love for one another will have the power to override the  primal forces of fear that have been harnessed by this president.

name: Marianne Williamson
text: You can’t sort of kind of decide to change your life & you can’t sort of kind of decide to change your country. If we want peace, if we want a sustainable planet & we want to fundamentally lessen unnecessary human suffering, we need to change our entire perspective on government.

name: Marianne Williamson
text: USA need to re-purpose our economy. Auto industry workers would love being told their jobs being repurposed  for developing green transportation systems, oil industry workers would love being told their jobs being repurposed for developing green energy systems & on down the line.

name: Marianne Williamson
text: Many in America either support Israel while minimizing the human rights concerns of Palestinians, or support Palestinians while minimizing legitimate security concerns of Israel. We need a President who deeply appreciates the importance of both. Not either/or, but both/and.

name: Marianne Williamson
text: We can question the behavior of Israel without joining forces with those who would destroy it. That is the balance most needed now: to take on the conversation in a way that honors both human rights of Palestinians as well as legitimate security concerns of Israel. Both matter.

name: Marianne Williamson
text: External changes on the level of the issues is important, but it’s not enough; we also need spiritual changes on the level of the heart. One doesn’t preclude  the other. Here is the Issues section from my site:

name: Marianne Williamson
text: Having perpetrated the wars In Vietnam & Iraq, both of which were catastrophic military misadventures, the US in the 21st-century should be the greatest purveyor of peace. Right now we do more to prepare for war than to wage peace; this will change or more catastrophe lies ahead.

name: Marianne Williamson
text: Americans are awakening to the need for our nation to take a deep moral inventory. Then we will address the injustices in our economy, the state of our children, the state of our earth, our moral debts to be paid & our responsibility to wage peace from a much more powerful place.

name: Marianne Williamson
text: A better version of the same old is still the same old same old, inadequate to the task of forging a sustainable future for the 21st-century. Incremental changes will not save us from the consequences of our errors. We need a national commitment to deep moral & political repair.

name: Marianne Williamson
text: 3) Children are full citizens of the US, with “unalienable rights to life, liberty, & pursuit of happiness”. Millions of children living in America’s “domestic war zones” cannot pursue happiness, and we should rescue them no less than if they were victims of any other disaster.

name: Marianne Williamson
text: 2)If someone neglects a child it is considered unethical at best & criminal at worst. So what is a society that neglects the trauma of millions of American children? This should be seen as a humanitarian crisis, because it is.  It is immoral that we are not helping these children

name: Marianne Williamson
text: 1) Millions of American children are trapped in schools without adequate school supplies to teach a child to read. If a child can’t read by 8, chances of high school graduation vastly decreased & chances of incarceration vastly increased. We have simply normalized their despair.

name: Marianne Williamson
text: We need an integrative approach to politics just like we have an integrative approach to medicine, realizing that what we do with our minds is as important to our health as what we do to our bodies. America needs to change our hearts as much as we need to change our policies.

name: Marianne Williamson
text: Corporate greed has not just corrupted America's economic system; it has highjacked our value system. It has turned us into a transactional rather than a relational society, in which selling to one another is given more primacy than loving one another.

name: Marianne Williamson
text: We need much more than small random acts of kindness now; we need huge, strategized acts of doing the right thing. Where some have harnessed fear for political purposes, we can harness the power of love.

name: Marianne Williamson
text: Trump looked out and saw a lot of fearful, angry people, and thought, "Wow, we could change the country with that." I look out and see a lot of decent, loving people and think, "Wow, we could change the world with that." Game on.

name: Marianne Williamson
text: Our defense strategy doesn't plan for future peace, but only for future war. Even Donald Rumsfeld said we must learn to wage peace. Peace-creation strategies, domestically and internationally, are much less expensive & more effective than sole reliance on methods of brute force.

name: Marianne Williamson
text: Our economic system doesn't aim for abundance 10 years from now;  it steals from the future by squeezing profits from the present, too little used to provide for future good of workers or environment. For future economic vibrancy, we need do much more for our young people today.

name: Marianne Williamson
text: Peace isn't the absence of war; war is the absence of peace. We must do much more to wage peace - by expanding economic opportunities for women and educational opportunities for children around the world, plus doing everything we can to diminish unnecessary human suffering.

name: Marianne Williamson
text: Small random acts of kindness not enough; we need huge strategized acts of doing the right thing. We need a Dept of children & Youth to address the chronic trauma of millions of American children; reparations; & a new, robust partnership between peace creation & war preparedness.

name: Marianne Williamson
text: One of the biggest problems in the US today is that Americans have been mentally trained to expect too little from their government, to feel helpless rather than empowered to change it when the government has let them down. Our biggest opponent is emotional exhaustion. Awaken now

name: Marianne Williamson
text: A Dept. of Childhood & Youth would co-ordinate all efforts - medically, culturally, educationally, nutritionally, artistically - to ensure the U.S. is a wonderful place for a child to live. Today we have millions of children at risk: this needs to radically change & we can do it.

name: Marianne Williamson
text: Our economic system was established when women had little or no voice in the public sphere, & taking care of children was considered "women's work." Today we do have a voice, & our first order of business should be ensuring we take better care of children.

name: Marianne Williamson
text: In order to have a thriving economy & society 10 years from now, we should take better care of our 10 year olds today. Millions of our children live w/ chronic trauma! That is why, when president, I will establish a cabinet level position called Secretary of Childhood and Youth.

name: Marianne Williamson
text: Our economic system has nothing to do with creating economic prosperity ten years from now. It leaches from the present by routing the majority of profits to a small group of people at the expense of most everyone else. This can and must be changed.

name: Marianne Williamson
text: In order to be on the DNC debate stage in June, I need 65,000 individual contributors. Even $1 will do. Please do this, and ask your friends to do it, so my campaign can override the institutional resistance to genuinely new ideas.

name: Marianne Williamson
text: The most important #WomensHistoryMonth is the history we are making NOW. This is our time & we need to use it well -  to genuinely birth a new age of partnership: between male & female, humanity & nature, head & heart. We need to create a new world and not just mimic the old one.

name: Marianne Williamson
text: Govt acting as a handmaiden to corporate conglomerates that put short-term profits before people does worse than "not help." It actively harms us, by denying health care, denying education, impoverishing farmers, destroying land, poisoning food, and increasing war. #marianne2020

name: Marianne Williamson
text: American people are emotionally exhausted, and do not want another 2-yr psychological civil war. Nor do they need me to tell them who or what Trump is. I plan to tell them instead how wonderful our lives could be & explain how as a nation we can get there.

name: Marianne Williamson
text: Dems who think all we have to do  is defeat Trump are blinded by their anger. If that’s all we do, the forces he represents will be back in full force in ‘22 & ‘24. Let’s break the chain entirely, submitting to Americans a compelling vision of a more peaceful and properous future

name: Marianne Williamson
text: We're in the midst of a breakdown - emotionally, politically, economically, environmentally. It's like a skidding car; you have to let go and let nature realign it. We all have to enter a deep place within ourselves now, in order to summon the forces that will repair the world.

name: Marianne Williamson
text: Adding to already extreme wealth inequality, a massive wave of destruction (white collar & blue) will hit the job market over next 10-15 yrs due to automation. Every American should read Andrew Yang's "The War on Normal People."We must rethink our entire economic system, quickly.

name: Marianne Williamson
text: They never talk about "a plan that would lead to" cutting taxes for the richest Americans, invading a country, etc. Yet it's always "a plan that will lead to" universal health care, "a plan that will lead to" reparations, "a plan that will lead to" anything like justice for all.

name: Marianne Williamson
text: "Race-conscious policies" and "some kind of reparations" are like when fossil fuel companies talk about how much they care about the environment. Sometimes we just need to guffaw.

name: Marianne Williamson
text: The status quo has a brilliant way of protecting and perpetuating itself; it simply co-opts disruptive language.

name: Marianne Williamson
text: Medicare 4 All, free 4-yr tuition, $15 hr min, cancellation of most college loan debt shouldn’t be seen as extreme positions in the richest country in the world. We’ve been trained to expect too little, reduced to haggling for things that should be considered everyone’s right.

name: Marianne Williamson
text: My campaign is radical? — No, democracy is radical. Love is radical. The American experiment is radical. Repudiating aristocracy  is an ongoing struggle, but we’ve done it before and we will do it again. Of the people. By the people. For the people. #marianne2020

name: Andrew Yang
text: I understand the passion and frustration with the Electoral College.  For those who wish to change it, again, our challenge is to win the election in 2020.  Focus on that and when we win we will be in better position to have these conversations.

name: Andrew Yang
text: If I were to advocate for any change it would be to make states award electors proportionally instead of winner-take-all. This would lead candidates to campaign everywhere and not just the ~12 battleground states. I believe Americans would appreciate this change a great deal.

name: Andrew Yang
text: Third, it runs the risk of making Democrats seem like we are losing elections by the rules that have been in place for decades so we need to change the rules. That’s a very unprincipled place to be.  We need to win an election by the rules we have before we call for any changes.

name: Andrew Yang
text: Second, the incentives would drive candidates to campaign in high-density cities and big media markets.  It would skew both campaigns and policies against lower-density rural areas in a very direct way.

name: Andrew Yang
text: First, getting rid of the Electoral College would require a Constitutional amendment. This would be a non-starter with many legislators whose states would lose electors.  It’s an impractical conversation to raise.

name: Andrew Yang
text: I think Democrats calling for getting rid of the Electoral College are off-base for a few reasons. Of course I get the beauty and simplicity of saying “whoever gets more votes wins.” It seems like the essence of democracy and has a strong innate appeal.

name: Andrew Yang
text: New Policy #16 - Reverse Partisan Gerrymandering. Politicians in both parties like to make districts ‘safe’ for incumbents. Unfortunately this makes them more responsive to primary challenges from the extremes of their own party and increases polarization
